{"name":"Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who use the Force sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a “Magic” sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even create powerful relics with imbued power.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.LgWBmhk15bGWcpSj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0AnQjFiuzSMzRh4W"}
{"name":"Psychic Rush","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some psionicists can occasionally activate a psionic power with less effort. A psionicist with this Edge can spend a Prophecy Shard to Short a power by d6 Power Points without any penalty applied to the arcane skill roll.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.SqSQjmmOwU9wasmV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0FQqPZbQXkbUvR7Y"}
{"name":"Limited Edition Model","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The vessel is a special, one-of-a-kind model, either by design or bey piecemeal. It gains one of these Pilot Edges, usable only by the pilot in this craft. The Trademark Weapon must be the craft of the pilot.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Trademark Weapon Edge, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.n6bl0LAYVusDCUTY"}},"_id":"0H9Q9R6pzIeMe3W8"}
{"name":"Ebb And Flow","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While the hero is under the effects of Liquid Courage, his movements are highly unpredictable.</p><p>His Pace in combat is reduced by 2, but attacks against him are made at –2 (as long as he can reasonably move about and isn’t suffering any Encumbrance or Minimum Strength penalties)","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Liquid Courage"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.LieMtAlbIrj44ANk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0Ia57T2c4yaxUgwE"}
{"name":"Getaway Driver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This wheelman has perfected the art of slipping away from pursuer during a car chase in an urban environment using parking ramps and dark alleys to lose a tail. Getaway Drivers may attempt to Flee a Chase one card sooner than usual.","notes":"Wiseguys page 56","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Driving d8+, Smarts d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.8ZdALCCcrNLXLjmY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0aBoSE1HpsydS7qb"}
{"name":"Smooth Talker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can speak any language you know with complete fluency and do not suffer any penalties as a non-native speaker. Additionally, you may adopt regional accents and use idioms of any language you know, including your native tongue. When language can reinforce a cover, this adds a +2 to your disguise rolls.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.csYp8967j06VXxsE"}},"_id":"0iLDHE0UVaF9PjOT"}
{"name":"Power Of The Land","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Ties to one’s preferred terrain run deep, allowing the character to draw power from it. The character gains 3 additional Power Points that remain while in the preferred terrain or until used. Also, the character regains 1 Power Point every 30 minutes while within the preferred terrain (or every 15 minutes if Rapid Recharge is also possessed.)</p><p>This Edge need only be taken once to apply to all of a character’s preferred terrains (if more than one.)","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background, Preferred Terrain"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.NgB623oMJhb8AyMn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0k6M6oMSaYz6nfgh"}
{"name":"Ghost","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This agent is trained to use subterfuge in hostile situations. He receives +2 to all Tricks.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 23","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Ag d8, Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.8f44znPqzl2cUE1X"}},"_id":"0nF7PxKuZpwvGaOW"}
{"_id":"0nyP3KBjh9znXdgk","name":"Improved 'hose 'em Down","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Gunners with Improved Hose ‘Em Down can suppress an area covered by three Medium Burst Templates. The three templates must be adjacent. Ammo consumption is tripled.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.75uWV4TXJfmDELFd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Master Summoner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero’s custom summoned allies gain an additional number of build points (from Chapter 4, Making a Friend) to allocate equal to your Rank (1 for Novice, 2 for Seasoned, and so on). If you are using an ally from the core rules or from this document, you can select additional enhancements for each of your hero’s allies from that chapter when you gain this Edge, or whenever they learn a new ally. These points can be re‐allocated each time your hero gains a Rank.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Spirit d8+, Occult d8+, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.tucinmEsyuEaxKTK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v74x6k6usus","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0pWxDPYDVAN5aL8y"}
{"name":"Gone Native","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When immersed in a foreign culture for long periods, Rippers invariably adopt some of the habits and customs of their hosts.<p>Frazer’s Fighters are particularly known for the affectations they adopt after living in and around Egypt and the Middle East for years on end. While these traits don’t endear them to polite London society, they help the Fighters blend and integrate with the native populace more easily, and withstand the native climate better than other foreigners.<p>Characters who have Gone Native are acclimated to the local environment, ignoring one point of penalties when resisting <i>natural</i> Fatigue from environmental effects. The character also gains + 2 Persuasion with the locals but is still considered an Outsider (unless she also has World Traveler).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.ioPbVsURG5LjY4SZ"}},"_id":"0u7uH8QZGCaKMpER"}
{"name":"Strategema Master","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Zackdorn game of strategema can be mastered only by those with a split-second ability to assess a tactical situation and eke out every advantage. You gain +2 to all Gambling checks, as well as to Knowledge (Tactics) checks when leading one side during a Mass Battle.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Knowledge (Tactics) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.1uoUEgefezNb4uTK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"103MFdP8LDfIpom7"}
{"name":"Will Weaver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has mastered her magical abilities sufficiently that she doesn’t need the mnemonics of spoken words and gestures to make her will reality. She doesn’t need a free hand to use her abilities, and can cast spells without speaking aloud. There are still visible displays of power around her when she uses her abilities, however, and any effects of her powers are just as visible as ever.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Arcane Background (Gunmage, Miracles, Sorcery, or Wizardry), Seasoned, Knowledge (Arcana) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.jiI7Dr0V575T2Dtr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"10IoEQEJFGADNESH"}
{"name":"Imbue Item","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Magewrights in Eberron understand and can manipulate magical energy in such a way that enables them to quickly imbue items and constructs, including living constructs, with infusions (powers imbued on objects). Imbue Item is the Eberron name for the Gadgeteer Edge. This version of the Edge is limited to the following powers (as with the Gadgeteer Edge, different trappings can be applied each time the magewright casts an infusion on an item): arcane protection, barrier, boost/lower Trait, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, elemental manipulation, environmental protection, light, protection, repairing, smite.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Magewright), Magewrighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.cm0yxuO3OJQhCRPx"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"12Q6PIVYTWbgAFp9"}
