{"name":"Atmospheric Acclimation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Travelers who have spent substantial time in Thin or Dense Atmosphere (see page 26) can learn breathing techniques to negate its ill effects. This Edge may be taken twice, once for each kind of atmosphere. Doing so allows the character to operate normally in that environment—he doesn’t have to make Vigor rolls.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.dSRwddTELCuYdGes"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"19WeHhPqkd8WNVGM"}
{"name":"Legal Protection","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Somehow, your hero’s police file has a little red line across it that makes beat cops think twice before they haul you in on minor crimes. The character gains a +4 Persuasion bonus when dealing with the security forces in his or her home area.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.2Z1xgOTT2oiy2zFb"}},"_id":"1A5hYdKqmITD7gYa"}
{"name":"Scout","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your traveler has learned to spot warning signs and trust his instincts in the wilderness. Anytime the Game Master rolls a random encounter while traveling planetside, your spacer may make a Notice roll (–2). If he’s successful, he spots the hazard, creature, or situation at the earliest possible opportunity. This likely gives his party time to avoid the threat, or at least approach it on its own terms. Your hero also gains a +2 to Notice rolls made to avoid surprise (see Savage Worlds) in tactical situations.","notes":"The Last Parsec - Leviathan","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"7"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.spsvPWmMn9lCYk8z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"1CgufbK7GPPKMt3X"}
{"name":"Data Chips","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent is cybernetically enhanced to accept direct data relays via memory cards and gains two additional defining interests. Unlike other defining interests, these may be reassigned at the beginning of any session if the agents are not in the field.<p><b>Example 1: </b>St. John is about to embark on a mission into Eastern Europe. He gets chipped with Knowledge (Romania) and Knowledge (Russia), providing him a general overview of both countries.<p><b>Example 2:</b> Helena, also chipped, decides she’d rather focus on Russia, because she thinks that’s where events will lead them, and takes Russian (Pidgin) and Russian Folklore.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.AHCL9S7HyvIfHGrt"}},"_id":"1Ne0FKftwykmKimG"}
{"_id":"1RxoFF0dnfngwgM8","name":"Art Of War","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some commanders have an intuitive grasp of strategy and tactics, and keen insight into the minds of their enemies. They easily outmaneuver and outfight more mediocre opponents.</p><p>Characters with the Art of War Edge are the ones whose quotations end up in the history books. Your character adds +2 to Knowledge (Battle) rolls during Mass Battles.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.UpSLHRnTRisl6AFH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"1fiGmc3kg3WKeopn","name":"Arcane Background (Grifter)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 35\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Backlash: </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">A grifter who rolls a 1 on his Spellcasting </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">die (regardless of his Wild Die), is automatically </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">Shaken (but see </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-weight: bold;\">Overdose</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, below).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Available Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Blind, bolt, boost/lower trait, </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">confusion, damage field, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">arcana, disguise, dispel, drain power points, fear, havoc, invisibility, intangibility, light/obscure, numb, pummel, quickness, slow, slumber, smite, speed, stun, succor, teleport, wall walker. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16.000000pt; font-family: 'AmericanCaptain01';\">Special rules: </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">&bull; </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Indulgence:</span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">A grifter must indulge in his particular </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">vice at least once a day to keep his conduit to the </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Hunting Grounds open. If he does not, he recovers Power Points at a rate of 1 point every 3 hours instead of the usual 1 per hour. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">&bull; </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Magic: </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Grifters may use Edges that require Arcane </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Background (Magic), except Wizard (see </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">). </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">&bull; </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Overdose: </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">A grifter who rolls a 1 on both his Spellcasting and Wild Die suffers a particularly powerful form of Backlash. He must roll on the </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 11pt;\">Overdose Table on page 52.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kpIxabfUw3Gv9r2u"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Push The Envelope","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot learned to use the craft as a means to defend itself in combat; add Handling to Toughness.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.6jNn4HcpHFO6hTQx"}},"_id":"1pHcL7kVDynF0PTU"}
{"name":"Faction Luminary","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero’s words and opinions carry great weight among other Rippers. Unless a lodge or faction is hostile to your character’s lodge or faction for some reason, the respected individual gains +2 Persuasion rolls with friendly Rippers and their allies, and Favors cost one point less (to a minimum of 1) with all Rippers and allies.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Faction Defender, Status 4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.B3fSRlXphz3PiVyz"}},"_id":"21s4hNjLM0XaOGWO"}
{"name":"Master Forger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent makes flawless forgeries, receiving +1 to all Forgery rolls and +1 to Notice rolls to detect fakes. This stacks with the Forger Edge","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Forger"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.VtdW1AJmMqmeVEXx"}},"_id":"25ChRROUgRaiFc1V"}
{"name":"Lunge","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A lunge allows a swordsman to extend the reach of his weapon. The character gains +1 Reach to his weapon. He may not use this Edge with First Strike, Frenzy, or Sweep.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.1WnPGfe4aFMDYn9Q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"268BrcEPXxGyIFdG"}
{"name":"Goodfella","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Only men of Italian descent, who have proven themselves to be both loyal and profitable to La Cosa Nostra, may have this honor bestowed upon them.</p><p> A Goodfella has made his bones and got straightened out. He is privy to secrets only members of the brotherhood have access to. This prestigious title grants the gangster the Streetwise Edge. If the character already has this Edge, he can choose another Social Edge as long as he meets the requirements.</p><p> As a made man, he also gets a bunch of things for free. His clothes are swag, and when he goes to a restaurant, it’s on the house. Associates kick money up to him as well. Therefore, it takes a month for his Wealth die to go down a level if he fails to gain Rewards during that time period (instead of a week), and he only has to kick up 25% of his earnings instead of 50% (see La Cosa Nostra in Chapter Two).</p><p> Furthermore, a Goodfella is considered untouchable. Other members of La Cosa Nostra won’t lay hands on him unless they have permission (see Omertà in Chapter One). This protection also extends to other shady Underworld individuals who won’t initiate hostilities count on the whole mafia family to exact revenge on the transgressor.</p><p> All that said, the life of a gangster comes with money and power, but at the expense of responsibilities. Therefore, the mobster gains the Vow (Major—Omertà) Hindrance. This doesn’t count toward the maximum number of Hindrances he can take, nor does it provide bonus points for character creation.","notes":"Wiseguys page 52","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, male, Italian heritage on the father’s side"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.ef5RCChVNuOHrJtX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2FhVeuhVWY3z3aSN"}
{"name":"Speed Load","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have learned to reload a firearm quicker than most. Once per turn, if you don’t move on your turn, you can reload a firearm that can be reloaded as an action without incurring the multi-action penalty. If you are using a weapon that requires a full round or more to reload, the time required is reduced by 1 round (if it’s normally 1 full action to reload, it’s reduced to a normal action instead, which isn’t further reduced by this Edge).","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Agility d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.tGnTylxj53MZPIBt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2JmDMwxjtEGqdC8L"}
{"name":"Combo Strike","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When fighting with two melee weapons, you can sacrifice all attacks with one weapon for the turn and roll a single attack roll with the other weapon. If you hit, roll the damage dice for both weapons and a single Strength die. For example, your hero attacks a target with two daggers (each Str+d4). She elects to use Combo Strike and makes a single attack and hits. She rolls Str+2d4 for damage and treats that as a single damage roll. This cannot be used with abilities that give you additional attacks on your turn, such as Frenzy, Rapid Attack, or Sweep.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Agility d8+, Fighting d6+, Two Fisted"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.e5ZYXPThgLNHIyOP"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2Vp4TQEBKrJfDuEu"}
{"name":"Multitasker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character excels at scheduling her time and interests. Each semester, she may choose two Extracurricular Activities instead of one, gaining the benefits and any drawbacks of both.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.zLu9Ij6OYN6TxMDM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2Wg4PFnkQqjmdHsI"}
