{"name":"Relic","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has a physical item granting one power. The power may be of any Rank, but the agent suffers a -1 penalty to his roll for each difference between his Rank and that of the power. Using the power requires the appropriate Knowledge skill (Divine, Mystical, or Paranormal) depending upon its power source. Should it be lost or stolen, the agent gains a replacement focus at the start of a new mission, subject to his Director’s approval. If a modified result of 1 or less is rolled on the skill die, the device won’t function again for a d6 hours.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.4RtuMib7Cjdfelwi"}},"_id":"2enfLCJQWhlKGoKo"}
{"name":"Banshee Born","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character is a human born and raised on Banshee. The living planet connected with her on a spiritual level, allowing her to take any Edge or ability usually reserved only for anouks. Furthermore, when her time comes, she’s more likely to become a Guardian (see Guardians on page 74).</p><p>Some Banshee Born have the Outsider Hindrance, but it’s not mandatory . Occasional colonists may see her as having “gone native,” and the most ignorant and racist of the lot may occasionally use this as an excuse for violence, but most don’t know or care.</p><p> Anouks are slightly more favorable to Banshee Born humans—add +1 to Persuasion rolls with dealing with them.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Human"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.PemEzycYIRLDbTEM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2kwEZe44jMxeTsLu"}
{"name":"Gunner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to an- ticipate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in ground vehicles. The character’s Fast Targets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed for ground vehicles.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Driving d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.8p8RhUSJzzqhnlIQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2yqup7Ouu2KorsnK"}
{"name":"Lackey","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’ve gained the services of a reasonably loyal minion. They are an Extra (not a Wild Card), although you may spend your own bennies on them if you wish.<p>Create your lackey as described in the Minions section. If they are killed or dismissed, you attract a new lackey in 2d6 days.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Charismatic or Fearsome Reputation"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.CSG6eBrnRj9e3hw2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"34JJTGAB2XKhgaLq"}
{"name":"Charms & Wards","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Witch hunters spend their days tracking down witches, hags, and rogue priests, and know how to prepare certain minor charms, tattoos, symbols, and even odors or ointments to ward off their evil eyes.<p>Black magic (and Special Abilities that mimic such power) used against the hero suffers a –2 penalty to the arcane skill roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Witch Hunter)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.lhBjTB5tYmPTmE1W"}},"_id":"3JiNiqN1F6VBBTKa"}
{"name":"Empty the Clip","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can fire all the remaining bullets in your automatic weapon with a normal Shooting roll by spending a benny. You must have at least half a clip remaining to use this Edge. You must declare whether you’re firing in a Small Burst or Cone template before you roll. Targets then must make an opposed Agility roll against the Shooting roll or they suffer standard damage for the weapon type.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"L, Rock and Roll!"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.WLBOd4JVAsDtWzm3"}},"_id":"3UyIIB3gKW7hFO4h"}
{"name":"Sensor Ghost","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Believing caution is the better part of valor, you make the most of stellar bodies, cloaking devices, and your enemies’ sensor blind spots to keep your vessel hidden until the moment you choose to strike. You gain +2 to your Stealth, Tracking, and Notice scans which relate to detecting enemy ships or traps. The bonuses only apply to rolls made while operating a starship.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Smarts d6; Stealth d8; Tracking d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.O7GwEZI8P0VDwhf3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"3ZRF8SPnP5NOaSI2"}
{"name":"Salvager","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When every screw and bolt matters, one can’t be too thrifty. This Edge allows a character to double the value of spare parts he can salvage from an item and save up to 75% used spare parts in case of a failed gunsmithing attempt.","notes":"Junkyard Arsenal page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Notice d6+, Repair d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.junkyard-arsenal.0AluHY9mwVNl9Ypi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vn8z4u52a2","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Junkyard Arsenal","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"3cHiRMSJ5jBqWcEy"}
{"name":"True Grit","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This grizzled spacer has seen some things that’d make others’ eyes pop like they were decompressing. He ignores all penalties when making Fear checks, and if failed, gets one free reroll on the Fear Effects table if he chooses.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Grit, Spirit d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.EPAUngMAGXKLLhkd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"3dFVRZ5qdRVJKcOs"}
