{"name":"Disarm Mastery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent excels at removing an opponent’s weapon in melee combat. He makes an opposed Fighting roll against his opponent. With a success, the adversary drops his weapon. With a raise, the opponent is Shaken and the weapon flies 1d4 random inches away or the agent may elect to take it if he has one or both hands free.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 22","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Fighting d8, Unarmed Combat (Basic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.VLBy14vtMoOwjZ9y"}},"_id":"4kytdv3CdcNrz57M"}
{"name":"Maccabeus Security & Investigations","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the MSI gain +2 to Notice Rolls, and +1 to Fighting rolls (they have a strong emphasis on hand to hand.)","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the MSI, Seasoned."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.HhivN3kIdzZ3BgdM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"4o378lcjhr4sZopp"}
{"_id":"4xtpQbvrUvoIaqsX","name":"Spiritualist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Spiritualism began in the 1840s, with the Fox sisters of Rochester, New York demonstrating the ability to talk with spirits and get answers in the form of mysterious rapping noises. Though the Fox girls later confessed they were making the noises with their toe joints, others flocked to investigate the “new science” of spiritualism.</p><p>Spiritualist powers derive from sensing and communicating with spirits, chiefly those of the dead. With the the war, there is no shortage of corpses with which to communicate.</p><p>Spiritualists add +2 to Faith rolls when invoking the banish, divnination, grave speak, or spirit shield miracles. (See Chapter Six for descriptions of the new powers.)</p><p>In addition, when conducting a séance (via the grave speak power), the spirit may not lie. If it doesn’t wish to answer for some reason, the caster must win acontestofPersuasionversusSpirit(adding+2for this Edge). This consumes one of the spell’s rounds of questioning, whether it’s successful or not.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"27"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.vZJhsMrBjG9ite9J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Necromancer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p><p> The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the zombie power at Novice level (rather than its normal Veteran Rank requirement).</p><p> Second, when casting zombie, the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p><p> A Necromancer may never have more than twice his Spirit die in permanent undead servants.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 5","notes":"Horror Companion, page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.0lH4Rjvk0fSbSCfE"}},"_id":"4yYhBrrr1gQyrkCE"}
{"name":"Breaking & Entering","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’ve got a talent for bypassing security and sneaking past guards. Firstly, this Edge gives a +2 bonus to Stealth rolls when trying to get into a guarded building or compound. Secondly, you get to know the difficulty of the test before you roll the dice. For example, if you come to a locked, alarmed door, the GM must tell you the difficulty of disabling the alarm before you roll, so you know whether to make the attempt or back off.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ag d6, Sm d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.Lh7kXDGpmCcgM06x"}},"_id":"57mQnENPbefqaOrm"}
{"name":"Fire At Will","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Subtlety and precision are all well and good, but sometimes what you need is to lock and fire as many photon torpedoes as you possibly can in less than ten seconds. You may fire one weapon system per round without incurring a multi-action penalty.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Shooting d6; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.Ld09bWAkaekOErLy"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5CrdeRA3l1IXCUYU"}
{"name":"Shifter Acrobatics","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your shifter’s heritage makes you even more agile and light-footed. When shifting, he adds +2 to Athletics rolls related to climbing, jumping, balancing, Tests, and Maneuvering (see Chases in the Savage Worlds core rules).","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Cliffwalk, Longstride, or Swiftwing), Athletics d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.AQvJvMKUBr2cK2wq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5GAXULbPG2oDxBX1"}
{"name":"Mind Over Machine","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The technomancer gains the benefit of a Vehicle Control Rig, despite not having the cyberware. The technomancer must still connect to a vehicle with a Jockey Adapter or a remote control deck. This may be used in conjunction with the Skinlink Edge to control vehicles and drones without cyberware.","notes":"Sprawlrunners - Technomancers page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Drive d6+ or Pilot d6+, Technomancer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.sprawlrunners-technomancers.ZypwVx4U3PM7FJrC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2v6g1l9drn8","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Sprawlrunners: Technomancers","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5N7iBaS8R0zR1VOD"}
{"name":"Gunsmith","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Through natural talent or vast experience, this character has become very adept at making weapons in suboptimal conditions. He gets a free reroll on all rolls related to manufacturing, upgrading or salvaging weapons. If the setting allows for it, gunsmiths can raise funds with their Repair skill (as the Performance skill in Savage Worlds)","notes":"Junkyard Arsenal page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Repair d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.junkyard-arsenal.zQzFFE25SznVSyAn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vn8z4u52a2","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Junkyard Arsenal","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5Qa1USHw22FSsMip"}
{"name":"Vulcan Nerve Pinch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Make a touch attack called shot to your opponent’s vitals (cannot be a wild attack). Roll unarmed damage, but don’t apply it: instead, the victim must roll Vigor equal to the damage or immediately fall unconscious for 2d6 rounds. Does not affect energy beings, androids, Borg drones, or other creatures with a highly alien nervous system.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Fighting d8; Knowledge (Biology) d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.x6xLpjfYCsg4hIPl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5VBF3qxdx9PssrV1"}
{"name":"Brutality","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero uses the weight and inertia of his weapon to great effect.</p><p>When wielding a melee weapon with two hands, the hero increases its damage die one type (Str+d10 becomes Str+d12).</p><p>In addition, on a raise, before damage is rolled, he may choose to either push the target 1” away, or have them fall Prone, or deal an additional +2 damage to them. This also applies to free attacks","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.YdQIWD5eaaNkInK4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5WZqRUKOH5UmDyes"}
{"name":"Shadow Veil","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some assassins become so intimately familiar with shadows, they begin to rely on their aid any time they practice their trade. These shadowy assassins learn to deal devastating damage to their targets if they remain patient and let the shadows slowly find and exploit the target’s weak spots. </p><p>To use this ability both the attacker and the target must be in an area of Dim or darker illumination and a maximum of the assassin’s Spirit die in inches apart. The assassin can place a veil of shadow on a target once each turn as an action (applying the usual Multi-Action penalty). They may continue to place further layers of the veil, one for each Rank they possess. When they decide to strike, they can add +1 bonus to the damage of a successful attack for each layer placed, as long as the target hasn’t moved outside of Spirit reach and the illumination level hasn’t improved above Dim.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.efDQLFPtHLMF3Blo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5puhVww7mVoVjXVN"}
{"name":"Animalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero may ignore 2 points of penalties (including Multi-Action and Shorting) to activate powers that affect, summon, or transform into animals.</p><p> Moreover, the base Duration of shape change and animal weapon are increased to 5 minutes (the Trapping must remain related to animals).","notes":"Fantasy: Tomes and Prayers page 47","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Arcane Background (any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.pGIpbTxVQpFZJUxH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5swTi73jz7XoreQG"}
{"name":"Road Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Select one maneuver with a penalty that is allowed by a ground craft. When performing this ground craft maneuver you have a +2 to your roll but only to cancel out part of or the entire penalty. This bonus cannot increase your roll beyond your normal, unmodified ability.</p><p>You cannot apply this Edge to the so-called unnamed maneuver unless an entirely new one is outright designed and named.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Driving d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.Ox7cwMmrcUaQbnJn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"633g8nb6F1SShrFV"}
{"name":"Improved Analyze Shield Harmonics","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Analyze Shield Harmonics, but AP is increased to +8. If you gain a raise on the Knowledge (Astronomy) roll, your crew may also beam through the target’s shields.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Analyze Shield Harmonics"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.vwe4WAfWhs2l0HP0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"66NFhKgZ6OHMgS8b"}
{"name":"Harrowed","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some spacers are just too tough to lie down and stay dead when their time comes. The price they pay is an eternal battle for their own souls with demonic “manitous.”In return, the treacherous creatures grant their host’s unlife and incredible powers.</p><p>Harrowed aren’t common anywhere, particularly the Faraway system, but a few have risen from Banshee’s soil over the years.</p><p>You can read up on the Harrowed in No Man’s Land (page 76). The Edge may only be selected at character creation, for obvious reasons. You can’t take it later...at least not on purpose.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.jIg03rgdbcwW59pm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"68HbjrmHsT7jacGL"}
{"name":"Medium","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can now hear your spirit guardian. In addition to making communication easier, the spirit guardian can act as a “translator” to speak with other spirits. Unlike grave speak, no spirit is summoned nor required to answer truthfully, though spirits are more favorably disposed to the character. The hero has +2 Charisma when dealing with spirits.","notes":"East Texas University page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Spirit Guardian"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.56NMkUPCOYjr7ZxJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6CAlJhQIYjEN04gl"}
{"name":"Precision Bladework","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You wield a blade with deadly precision, relying more on accuracy than brute force to bring down your foes. When using a bladed weapon that inflicts Str+d8 damage, you cause +d8 damage on a raise instead of the normal +d6. This increases to +d10 if your weapon inflicts Str+d6 damage, and +d12 if your weapon inflicts Str+d4 damage. The benefits of this Edge only apply to Fighting and Throwing attacks made with bladed weapons.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Assassin or Urban Ranger, Notice d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.wKYumYTLljIzbV7t"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6NuJs1jFd9GuM8d7"}
{"_id":"6NyPNUspqNCz8Vey","name":"Medic!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A soldier with this Edge can get wounded soldiers up and fighting again in seconds. If the medic can get to a wounded non-Wild Card by the end of the round in which he was wounded, he can make an immediate Healing roll at −2. If the roll is successful, the victim is merely Shaken instead of wounded.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.7Vwi3hffRE23S48s"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Arcane Chemist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Ripping and distilling extracts from monsters is something of a specialty for this hero. When making extracts, a Ripper with this Edge creates twice as many doses as usual.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Science d6,  Rippertech d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.e36sNzI2yZZyZaen"}},"_id":"6O7usUoZelnUs346"}
{"name":"One Of The Chosen","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your investigator gains either a +1 to attack rolls vs. supernatural evil or they suffer a –1 penalty to attack rolls to hit him—your choice. You may take this Edge a second time but only after achieving a new Rank to gain the other ability.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 7","notes":"Horror Companion, page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.8W63UXvv0DgOIOf2"}},"_id":"6TxBjN8qIVxwkBxD"}
{"name":"Close Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal. Close fighters move inside most weapons’ reach, adding a bonus to their Parry equal to the enemy weapon’s Reach +1 for that particular foe. No bonus is granted if the foe is unarmed or using a knife or other small weapon.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.oNVp0XjtUK03Qpuf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6V6yLF9YBOmrmisW"}
{"name":"Cascade Crushers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Cascade Crushers were founded by a former SWAT officer and detective. They’ve got some of the best training when it comes to combining modern police work with monster hunting.</p><p>When making Research rolls related to monsters, Cascade Crushers gain +2 to the roll.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Cascade Crushers."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.ApHkqyXHxjCa0k1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6Z5BW7PkBSkHw4l4"}
{"name":"Favored Bond","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have a warjack or warbeast that has served beside you for a long time, and has practically become a part of you, responding to your thoughts almost before you’re aware of directing the thing. It’s a part of your legend. It starts each session with two Bennies of its own, which it can spend just like any other Wild Card, in addition to your Bennies. If you are bonded to a warjack, your warjack’s cortex is considered to be one step higher in quality while bonded to you. If you are bonded to a warbeast, your warbeast cannot attack you while frenzying, and you gain a +2 bonus on the opposed roll to control its frenzy.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Warcaster or Warlock, ‘jack or beast to bond with"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.VnZEXcGYtJuTBScX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6g0fiOK60ZZKyANi"}
{"name":"Unarmed Combat (Advanced)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent’s Unarmed Combat damage increases to Str+d6. This damage is not restricted by a lower Strength die type, so even a character with a d4 Strength would do d4+d6 damage with this Edge.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 25","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Fighting d8, Unarmed Combat (Basic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.sxCDO2ptsn4M3K9M"}},"_id":"6pM7oYiUZ56qd0Ca"}
{"name":"Skill Chip","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge makes the agent “chip-friendly” — he may take any one skill at d6. The skill may be reassigned at the beginning of each new mission.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.sBZr5cI6boVqd8Ha"}},"_id":"76xs5hyDSdwERxI4"}
{"name":"Van Helsing Institute","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Members of the VHI gain +1 to attacks and damage against any Undead, and +2 to Occult rolls that involve Undead.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the VHI, Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.n8abc3jdqrET4bOE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7EMeNXoza6TgkthZ"}
{"name":"Pt Consulting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"PT Consulting is the second biggest monster hunting firm in the US.They’re slick, corporate, well-equipped, pretentious assholes who can back up their talk.</p><p>PT Consulting Team Members gain +2 to Persuasion, except when dealing with non-PT Consulting Monster Hunters.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into PT Consulting."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.SZhYEc9a0f7Mvz6z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7JvAW80uShruAyfX"}
{"name":"Field Tester","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has been chosen to test prototypes in the field for the Vault. Your character gains an additional 2 Resource Points to spend on spytech or SUDs. A 1 on the skill die when using this equipment causes it to malfunction or act in an unexpected way – as determined by the Director. These points may only be used before a mission and may not be saved for Field Requisitions.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Tradecraft d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.BsD2LePRfctF5uKY"}},"_id":"7Rq2j5PYhGiFtMla"}
{"name":"Notorious","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This individual has earned a measure of renown and prestige in the criminal underworld and the media through some iconic deed she’s performed or her overall reputation. You and the Don should work together to determine the circumstances of your character’s ascent to prominence and give her an equally memorable and impressive nickname to match.</p><p> Your character’s reputation strikes fear into the heart of her enemies and commands the respect of her peers. She gets one free reroll on Intimidation rolls when dealing with denizens of the criminal underworld, and doubles the dirty money she earns from racketeering. However, there’s a drawback to that. Notorious gangsters are often the target of up and coming criminals looking to rise through the ranks.","notes":"Wiseguys page 53","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.4dYCgEdB8nOdjZEr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7T3ijPei4xpWGSsn"}
{"name":"Untouchable","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This slippery character can’t be touched by law enforcement—even the Feds. Local police know it’s not worth even trying to arrest him. Federal agents may try to detain the Untouchable, but must have something ironclad to accuse him on, and even then he has immunity from prosecution.","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Above the Law"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.75gMr67lgbJSbtNi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7WEIntMCbAB0Xuf1"}
{"name":"Wrasslin’","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This bruiser has perfected the art of wrasslin’. He can deliver a beatdown and entertain the crowd at the same time. A colorful costume and mask come with the territory, but he’s just as effective without the props and crowd.</p><p> When the wrassler succeeds on an opposed Test, he gains additional benefits on top of the normal results. With a basic success, he can perform the Disarm or Push maneuver as a free action. With a raise, he can make a free attack or initiate a grapple as a free action. If he’s already engaged in a grapple, he can inflict Strength damage.</p><p> For the benefits of this Edge to apply, the wrassler must be at an appropriate proximity to the target by the end of his turn, or employ an alternative means to interact with the target which meets the Don's approval (such as throwing a chair to attempt a Disarm).","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+, Taunt d6+, Martial Artist"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.mDv5soH6xTRhAZcj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7bapkjK8da7ZuGWs"}
{"name":"Improved Kiss Of Death","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Kiss of Death, but the assassin also has access to Knockout, Lethal, or Paralysis poison (choose one). Every attack made with this poison causes the attacker to be Fatigued. This Edge can be taken multiple times, gaining access to a different poison type each time.","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Kiss of Death"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.h5rg8cEkiNCDslTm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7d5mBAzmtfQU9o2u"}
{"name":"Wandslinger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Wandslingers deal instant punishment for an opponent’s mistakes. Once per round (if not Shaken or Stunned), the character receives a Free Attack against one failed arcane skill roll against him. This takes place immediately and must be a Wandslinging attack without Modifiers, using one of the following powers (provided he has them and the opponent is in Range): <i>blind, bolt, dispel, entangle,</i> or <i>slumber</i>. The Power Point cost is applied as a penalty to the Wandslinging roll.<p>These mages also ignore the penalty to disarming with Wandslinging skill and the penalty to Strength when resisting such an attempt (see page 3).","notes":"Wand Magic page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.hzoX42h0P8XdkUBr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7gP1yKS2bHzXdXPX"}
{"name":"Spirit Guardian","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The spirit of a departed friend or loved one looks out for you. It could be your last roommate mauled by a werewolf or even the dog you had in the Sixth Grade. You can see the spirit and it can hear you, but it cannot communicate other than with basic gestures. A grave speak ritual does allow communication with the spirit.</p><p> The guardian provides a +2 bonus to opposed rolls with other spirits as it helps fend them off, but it can also serve more subjectively at the Dean’s whim, guiding the hero away from trouble, to friends in need, etc. The spirit is bound to the character and cannot travel farther away than its Spirit die type in inches unless prevented by a ward (use the standard ghost stats on page 91, adapted by the Dean for the specific spirit).","notes":"East Texas University page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.UZV7nkosqSxM2A3J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7jxSWK9glODJdaCK"}
{"name":"Master of Disguise","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This charlatan is capable of disguising himself as a completely different person and acting as if a member of any other social class.<p>Creating a disguise normally takes 15 minutes and a disguise/makeup kit. Disguising one’s self as a higher social class also requires the appropriate clothing (lower class clothing might be faked by disheveling better clothes).<p>A disguise may be created without a kit at a –2 penalty, and it may be done more quickly (1d6 rounds) by taking a –2 penalty as well (these may be combined to do a fast disguise with no kit at –4). Those who know the character in his other guise may make an opposed Notice roll as detailed under Alternate Identity.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Alternate Identity, Performance d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.kxEGCJzjunzUVOQC"}},"_id":"7qec6QewinOwh8tk"}
{"name":"Evasive Maneuvers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The enemy ship is firing everything she’s got, but nothing seems to land as you loop, scissor, and roll out of the way. As long as you are piloting the ship, enemies subtract 1 from their Shooting rolls to hit (also applies to torpedo locks). Additionally, if you choose to flee combat, the length of the Chase is reduced by one round (typically from 3 to 2, but it’s the GM’s discretion).","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Piloting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.TT9OD1MG1Suw7hbB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"82f9rZ5wIZbhSUbd"}
{"name":"Notorious","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Inmates with this Edge have made names for themselves either as dangerous people or as close friends with dangerous people. While among a population who are aware of their reputation, they have +2 Notoriety.","notes":"The Last Parsec - Irongate","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.suDZRA9wPPlugSwj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"89A3HSpO5Png7jKp"}
{"name":"Up Close and Personal","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When engaging an adjacent opponent with a firearm, the agent uses a TN 4 rather than the target’s Parry. It may not be used with Empty the Clip.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 35","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"L, Gun Fu"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.eZUTqOWYCamtAdRf"}},"_id":"8KgAzoIIWlJqepxZ"}
{"name":"Preferred Terrain","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is most at home in a particular type of wilderness terrain chosen when this Edge is selected. While in the preferred terrain, the character’s cover is always considered one degree higher than normal so long as they have unrestricted movement. The character also gains +2 to Notice rolls if these conditions are met.</p><p>The bonuses from the character’s Woodsman Edge also apply in the preferred terrain type.</p><p>Suggested terrain types include desert, forest, jungle, frozen wastes, hills, marsh or swamp, mountains, plains, tundra, and open water.</p><p>The Gamemaster may allow characters to change their preferred terrain, but doing so will require months (if not years) of living primarily within that terrain, adapting and studying it in every detail.</p><p>A character may have more than one Preferred Terrain Edge.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Woodsman, Knowledge (Nature) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.aq135oAd405hW8uK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"8bvrHNDF6CWoqqmV"}
{"_id":"8lEjzR51RsjQTKYS","name":"National Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The soldiers of each nation in the Great War had an “identity” associated with them. Americans were “lucky,” British were “plucky,” and the Russians seemed fatalistic for most of the conflict. Soldiers with this Edge make this identity iconic by choosing one of the special abilities below. Characters from other nations can choose any of these abilities with the approval of the WM. • ANZAC Camaraderie: The troops from Australia and New Zealand defined the identity of their people by facing the tremendous casualties and horrible conditions during the Gallipoli campaign with their unique concept of “mateship,” reflecting the qualities of loyalty, equality, and friendship. ANZAC troops add +2 to Spirit rolls if adjacent to an ally.</p><p>• British Pluck: The British “stiff upper lip” made them incredibly resilient under even the most dreadful circumstances. “Tommys” add +2 to Spirit rolls made to resist Fear and Intimidation. It does not add to Spirit rolls to recover from being Shaken.</p><p>• Canadian Heart: As Britain’s largest Dominion, Canada was an important part of the Allied war effort. Canadian soldiers are eager to prove themselves, and get +4 on Trait and damage rolls when dealt a Joker rather than +2.</p><p>• French Élan: The French Army began the war planning to attack along the whole front, relying on French fighting spirit to overcome the enemy’s superior numbers. Even after the debacle of the first weeks, some of that spirit remained. If a Frenchman with this Edge spends a Benny to make a Trait roll, his Wild Die increases one die type, usually to a d8. This is different from the Elan Edge (see Savage Worlds), though the two work together for particularly proud individuals.</p><p>• German Efficiency: German troops get some of the best training in Europe. A character with this Edge treats all Trait requirements for Combat Edges as one die type less, though Rank requirements remain the same.</p><p>• Russian Fatalism: Many Russians seemed resigned to inevitable suffering, whether in the trenches, in captivity, or dealing with shortages at home. Yet they struggled on, until one disaster too many sparked revolt. Russian characters with this Edge ignore one level of wound modifier, which stacks with Nerves of Steel and Improved Nerves of Steel.</p><p>• US Luck: The American Doughboys joined the war to “make the world safe for democracy” and certainly appeared to have fortune or fate on their side. As evidenced by Sgt. York, “Yanks” would sometimes succeed at near impossible tasks. Whenever the character spends a Benny to make a roll, he ignores up to −2 points of penalties. Upper Class Requirements: Novice Your character is “well-born” and may have a noble title, or be heir to one. In the early 20th century, the prerequisites of nobility aren’t as impressive as they once were. Upper Class characters get a +1 Charisma bonus whenever dealing with other aristocrats or with lower-class individuals from their own society who support the traditional order. They get a −1 Charisma penalty when interacting with revolutionaries and others who support social change. Upper Class characters don’t get any bonus to wealth, but they do have connections to the “Establishment” which can give them some minor special privileges. A junior officer of “good family” might wind up being invited to dine with the General and his staff, and is more likely to be given a sympathetic hearing if he goes outside the rules. American characters can’t take this Edge.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"21"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.T1lxeDrmAtZubQkr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"In A League Of Your Own","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Through years of experience and practice, this character has attained a degree of expertise unparalleled in her professional field. Her Wild Die becomes a d8 (if she has the Master Edge in a Trait it becomes d12) when she makes a Trait test involving her non-combat related field of expertise. A burglar’s Wild Die is a d8 when sneaking (Stealth) in a house or building, defeating surveillance (Notice, Repair, or Stealth) and cracking a safe (Thievery). A cleaner gets this advantage when removing evidence from a crime scene (Healing), the professional Texas Hold ‘Em player uses the Edge when playing her favorite game (Gambling), and a getaway driver is likely a step ahead of the cops in a car chase (Driving) after a heist. The Don has the final word on what constitutes appropriate use of this Edge.","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.1v8p3PJc50jlfHkf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"8lr7vjzrbUUlNuGM"}
{"name":"Trapstone","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Crystals and gemstones are able to hold onto magical energy for extended periods of time. Some Petramancers can use this unique property to \"pre-load\" stones to trigger powers by adding unique Power Modifiers to their Arcane Devices. All Power Points (including Modifiers) are held in the device until released, making them unavailable to the creator (unless and Artisan Device, see blow). </p><p>• Trigger (+2, Instant Powers Only): Anyone, other than the creator, who touches the gem activates the power using the creator’s Petramancy skill! If the roll fails, only 1 Power Point is spent. The device must have sufficient Power Points to activate the embedded power (including the modifier). This occurs on each subsequent touch until the Power Points are exhausted. </p><p>• Proximity Trigger (+4, Instant Powers Only): Anyone, other than the creator, who passes within a Small Burst Template (Medium Template on a Raise) activates the power using the creator’s Petramancy skill! If the roll fails, only 1 Power Point is spent. The device must have sufficient Power Points to activate the power (including the modifier). This occurs on each subsequent pass until the Power Points are exhausted.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.1Yrz9EgBZZ7000ix"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7wj2fq58w9r","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"8o3sghM9ZatMKBsq"}
