{"name":"Cybermonk","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"For your hero, cybernetics aren’t simply useful technology or a way to gain an advantage over opponents in combat. She follows a martial path known as the Way of the Augmented Warrior. To her, cybernetic implantation is deeply philosophical, perhaps even religious; it is a means of ascension to a new form of being. Your hero finds ways to overclock her cybertech beyond standard limits, achieving amazing results and becoming a living weapon.</p><p>Your hero can overclock her cybertech for one additional round every other rank she has before she needs to make a roll to avoid gaining a level of Fatigue. See Cybermonk Push Duration (see next page) for more information. Rules for pushing cybernetics are explained on page 83.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Martial Artist, Agility d6+, a minimum number of cybertech augments equal to two points of Strain."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.pGrOWuWmztHO5jbu"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9GnbEo4Rx35dP2bZ"}
{"name":"Dogfighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to anticipate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in aircraft. The character’s Fast Targets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed for aircraft.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.UtnIephF5N6DWeRp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9H52i3UH71qQGzpx"}
{"name":"Wolfen Jaeger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Wolfen jaegers are specialist slayers, focusing their attention on removing the threat of werewolves from the world. They are most often Old Worlders, but others can learn their tricks as well.<p>Wolfen jaegers gain +2 to resist the effects of a werewolf ’s howl and ignore the Go for the Throat ability of any creature. They also add +2 to Notice, Stealth, and Tracking when hunting werewolves and normal wolves as well. This stacks with other Edges such as Woodsman.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Notice d6, Stealth d6, Survival d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.DXy6L9MxQubTgZgb"}},"_id":"9bBXx1d38h7gFGkK"}
{"name":"Tattoo Companion","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A special tattoo, infused with shadow, covers a part of this hero. The tattoo shows a creature similar to an animal. The shadows seem to swirl as if alive.</p><p>The exact companion is chosen from the options below when the hero gains this Edge and cannot be changed once choosen. The shadow creature can be called at any time and will appear at the hero’s side as a free action once per hour. It may return to the tattoo as a free action whenever adjacent to the hero. If the companion is Incapacitated, it automatically returns to the tattoo, and must remain there for at least a week.</p><p>When called from the tattoo, the creature looks almost normal, but more sinister, otherworldly, or slightly off. It often inspires fear or revulsion among the common folk. Each companion receives the following special ability: </p><p>• Shared Mind: It can communicate with the tattooed hero as if using mind link.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Vigor d6+, Occult d8+ or Shadowcraft d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.RU4mw0XVC69AXTiz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9f4kHbxQLlDmkUgT"}
{"name":"Multifaceted","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero can combine trappings from two types of gems that have access to the same power to create a unique magical effect by inserting them in the same object (e.g. Ruby and Sapphire might be combined to create \"Blue Flame\" ). Multifaceted powers add +2 to damage and are –1 to resist in addition to gaining any Synergies related to either trapping - including Weaknesses.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Petramancy), Petramancy d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.3xkUBACrkikdOw9h"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7wj2fq58w9r","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9jg8XQQ5TORxciTh"}
{"name":"British Supernatural Service","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"BSS members are trained in media relations, obscuring information and hiding the supernatural. They gain +2 to Persuasion Rolls and can spend a Bennie to give d6x5 targets the Doubting Thomas Hindrance (this Hindrance is temporary, though 24 hours is usually enough for folks to forget and move on. It just...helps speed up the process.)","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the BSS"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.jYjeoR3B7UM7kNNT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9mMbCGZ3vG9AJHBP"}
{"name":"Gun Fu!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Heavily trained in close quarters gunplay, you know gun fu. When using pistols against a target’s Parry, she has +2 to Shooting and +2 to pistol damage. This benefit only applies to such close range combat, not to attacks from further than adjacent.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Martial Artist, Fighting d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.6clDV7NZJYo0uhXo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9s7sjd3geLN6j3eD"}
{"name":"Derby Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character has mastered the art of fighting on roller skates. She does not treat them as an Unstable Platform and can use them as weapons which cannot be Disarmed (and without any improvised weapon penalties) while wearing them. This leaves her hands free to hold other items or weapons.","notes":"Wiseguys page 53","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Athletics d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.66RsEml1mhtlMTMP"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"9zipFCgmpre4ofPW"}
{"name":"Child Of Khyber","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A Child of Khyber gains an Aberrant Dragonmark Arcane Background, but when she activates a dragonmark power, she may automatically apply a single Ritual effect as if she had successfully completed a Ritual to activate the power.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Dragonmark race, d12+ in any two skills, cannot have Arcane Background (Dragonmark or Aberrant Dragonmark) or Heir of Siberys"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.fwHbjGGMPXoyLUYW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"A4CWbSaEjKmehsCK"}
{"name":"Rapier Wit","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your mind is a finely honed weapon, and your tongue is as sharp as your blade. You receive a +2 bonus to Smarts tricks and Taunt checks, as well as to Smarts rolls when resisting the taunts and tricks of others. If you roll two or more raises on a Taunt or Smarts trick, you get a free Fighting attack against the same target, as long as they are already within melee reach.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8, Taunt d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.bzJjStS5scQx8Bnj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"A8M8arC1FcTVyU32"}
{"name":"Superior Defense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has mastered special defensive techniques. When using the Defend maneuver, his Parry is increased by +4 (instead of +2). If using the Full Defense maneuver, add +2 to his Fighting roll to determine the Parry score.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 24","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Ag d8, Block"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.PTQT8FPmjEhrMAat"}},"_id":"A9K9WmsydQo62GKY"}
{"name":"Wave Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Select one maneuver with a penalty that is allowed by a watercraft. When performing this watercraft maneuver you have a +2 to your roll but only to cancel out part of or the entire penalty. This bonus cannot increase your roll beyond your normal, unmodified ability.</p><p>You cannot apply this Edge to the so-called unnamed maneuver unless an entirely new one is outright designed and named.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Boating d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.076btsi0g116o0SE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ACemQx8m5Uj7oAXy"}
{"name":"Rune Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This mage has discovered secret knowledge that allows him to carve a power rune into his wand (and he does so every time he attunes a new wand). He picks a non-damaging power he knows. As long as he is wielding the rune wand, the mage may cast the power with Range reduced to Self as a free action once per turn. The Selective Modifier may not be applied. The wielder spends Power Points as usual.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, AB (Wand Magic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.HC4Dp3tDgNnwo0xG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"AV9UkF2CnicHtjYs"}
{"name":"Gizmo","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has found a piece of working Weird Science technology, either from the arsenal of a mad genius, the depths of a ruined temple or from some other obscure source, and can use it as if they have the Arcane Background (Weird Science). The hero did not create it but has been granted access to it for some reason. Perhaps they found it, were gifted it, or earned it somehow.<p>The device is created like a normal Weird Science gadget, but using it requires a skill other than Weird Science (for example, Shooting for a Weird Science weapon, Piloting for a Weird Science vehicle, Notice for a Weird Science detector, etc.). If damaged, the gizmo can only be repaired by a Weird Scientist.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 78","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 78","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.CufMpIDXpA5s0Va8"}},"_id":"AYsoQmNWdD2oaJcA"}
{"name":"Don’t Get ’im Riled!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Heroes with this Edge are a mean and surly lot. They add their current Wounds to any Fighting damage rolls, to a maximum of +3.</p><p>A hero with three Wounds, for example, adds +3 to his melee damage. It has no effect on ranged or thrown attacks.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.p0VzDVKA0kauvh47"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Abza0RPuGliEdxkV"}
