{"name":"Internalized Backlash","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has learned to channel his raw bursts of magical energy into himself rather than endangering the world around him, and loses the Explosive Backlash limitation on his sorcerer abilities. Instead, when he rolls a 1 on his Focus die, he becomes Shaken, as he pulls that burst of uncontrolled energy into his own body rather than allowing it to lash out at the world around him. This is optional; a sorcerer who has learned to control these outbursts may find it useful to allow them to explode forth in times of danger. Learning this edge is considered a necessary first step in a sorcerer’s training by most magical academies; most won’t accept a sorcerer among their ranks who is a danger to everyone around him.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Arcane Background (Sorcery), Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.Kj2Nwfsham0PdVuE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"AmnKoelbl03iJlvN"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Telepathy)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\">Arcane Skill: Telepathy (Smarts)</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\">Starting&nbsp;<a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-color: initial; padding: initial; white-space: initial; word-break: initial; margin: initial; color: var(--red); text-decoration-line: underline; border: initial initial initial;\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"swade-core-rules.swade-rules\" data-id=\"WaqU65ZxvBkQ0pKc\">Powers</a>: 2</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-color: initial; padding: initial; white-space: initial; word-break: initial; margin: initial; color: var(--red); text-decoration-line: underline; border: initial initial initial;\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"swade-core-rules.swade-rules\" data-id=\"I3euc03IC9TAW83S\">Power Points</a>: 10</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are many telepathic races in Star Trek, such as Vulcans and Betazoids. Players of those races may take the Arcane Background (Telepathy) edge, which works exactly as Arcane Background (Psionics) in Savage Worlds, except that telepaths' available powers are limited to...</p>\n<p><em>Blind, confusion, disguise, fear, invisibility, puppet, mind reading, slow, slumber, and speak language.</em></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mfAVN2iGJ81Ybtcc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_h360mwewe9","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"AoOFtcOQjC2WK0Wk"}
{"name":"Cage Breaker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are practiced in the art of War Driving, the art of hacking network signals from a distance. You can hack a network without needing to be inside the building so long as the building is within range of your Personal Area Network. Additionally, you ignore 2 penalties to Hacking rolls (or get a +1 to Hacking rolls if there are no penalties) during Dramatic Tasks when hacking a network.</p><p>Note: This Edge does not work with a Hacking Rig unless the Hacking Rig has a WIFI module installed. See page 130 for more information.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Hacking d12, Hacker"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.q6b16zHQT333aYw9"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"AoXalXO8SCTD8i2j"}
{"name":"Moxie","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero can cut a challenger down to size with a few sharp words, or turn a thug’s threats into a laughing matter with only a phrase or two. She adds +2 to all Taunt rolls and can use Taunt in place of her Smarts or Spirit when resisting a Test of Wills.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Taunt d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.kndGkve8PEaOqDM0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ArolSNtSord7AJM7"}
{"_id":"AxnntpQDFkVBxjSX","name":"Death Before Dishonor","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character has led his men to many victories and they have come to abhor retreat as a stain on their honor. A leader with this Edge adds +2 to Spirit rolls when rolling for his troops’ Morale in a Mass Battle.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.JGkyhezxhdQJp19x"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Lunge","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A lunge allows a swordsman to extend the reach of his blade. The character gains +1 Reach to his weapon. He may not use this edge with Frenzy, Sweep, or any effect providing a free attack (First Strike, Counterattack, etc).","notes":"Flash Gordon page 40","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.MebM4q49NkxYX6y7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"B2wmT47sxGXwfkMM"}
{"name":"Down-to-Earth","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is of sound mind and not prone to flights of fancy. Although the supernatural is still frightening, he or she has the good sense to remain rooted in reality. A character with this Edge is more likely to be able to deal with the many horrors of the Cabal and can better resist rippertech’s harmful effects. Modify this hero’s Reason by +1.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.kARGTEGbUa8Uya9L"}},"_id":"B92LS5px4cavcz8d"}
