{"name":"Psychometry","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When touching an object (non-living thing), your character may attempt to gain impressions or visions linked to its past. To do so, make a Spirit roll at –2. Success grants a basic impression of an important or traumatic event centered around the object, and a raise provides more details. For example, a success might flash the image of a knife being plunged into a body. A raise reveals the knife’s wielder wore a ring with a cat’s eye stone.","notes":"East Texas University page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Aura Reader, Spirit d10, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.cyXeDbu5t1faIXnB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"BvyB0X5UU6iCfpYe"}
{"name":"Speed Freak","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A hero may attempt a Driving, Piloting, or Boating Test (as appropriate) with a -2 penalty to coax more speed out of a vehicle. Success increases the vehicle’s Top Speed by 10% (rounded down to a minimum of +1”) and Acceleration by +1” for the round. If used during a chase, the hero may attempt to gain 3 additional Range Increments with the Push maneuver by accepting a –6 penalty to their Driving, Boating, or","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Ace"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.supxE49ouVlf55iW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"BwzAXA8oayCU8JeD"}
