{"name":"Rippertech","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"To paraphrase Friedrich Nietzsche “beware when fighting monsters lest you become one.”<p>Your monster-to-be may start with up to half her total Reason in rippertech (round up). This reduces Reason the appropriate amount.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.N3uUBwxnXhA7uiGe"}},"_id":"C69OwxxX3zIPTtNL"}
{"name":"Artillerist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When rolling deviation for a missed area effect attack, such as a grenade, alchemist’s bomb, or mortar shell, your hero can roll twice (both direction and distance) and choose which roll to use.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d6+, Shooting d6+ or Throwing d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.mCx0Q5AUgQfdLYB2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CDzcpiG1Fm9an8MO"}
{"name":"Tomb Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who battle dead things in tight spaces have learned special techniques to take advantage of their confines. Frazer’s Fighters are famous among the Rippers for their battles Egypt’s crypts and tombs, but any close quarters combatant may take this Edge.<p>The hero gains +1 to Parry for each wall within 1” (2 yards) of his position, up to a maximum of +3 if his back is against a dead end or cul-de-sac.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.flWGD5THfR2ENI3M"}},"_id":"CF6X4LHaCcCOi7qX"}
{"name":"Focus Fire","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Marksman Edge affects all of the shooter’s ranged attacks on his turn, as long as she fires no more than a Rate of Fire of 1, doesn’t move, and targets the same foe.</p><p>Also, when the hero successfully hits a target for the second time in the turn, the target immediately becomes Vulnerable","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Marksman, Athletics d10+ or Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.30yehP5x3JSeYBGR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CSaVJavFHL6YP3fQ"}
{"name":"Re-route Systems","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Pilot switches up how the craft’s systems respond to threats, piloting, combat, and so forth by re-routing systems processes. As such, the Pilot may add the craft’s Handling bonus to any non-combat Trait roll while at the helm.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Pilot d6, Electronics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.5pwA6YPf74TUwj1D"}},"_id":"CgGNXjDSvcnWmnwR"}
{"_id":"Cj3mSaXzOT412jVe","name":"Hose 'em Down","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Machine gunners with this Edge can employ Suppressive Fire to control a larger swath of the battlefield. When using a braced medium or heavy machine gun, the gunner can suppress an area equal to two Medium Burst Templates. The second template must be adjacent to the first, in any direction, and the weapon uses twice as much ammunition as normal.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.mRuQdo20wdxmvPZj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"The Heracles Foundation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the HF gain +2 on all Soak rolls, and the Overconfident Hindrance. They tend to take after their namesake in subtle ways.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the HF"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.qYbfFkH3lkxxF01l"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CqirQPaCvv89Zy0L"}
{"name":"Explosive Ally","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When one of your hero’s conjured creatures is Incapacitated, it explodes into bony shards, erupts into golden light, or otherwise ends violently as appropriate to its trappings, dealing 2d6 damage to all creatures adjacent to it. This damage can be Evaded.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, summon ally or zombie"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.Em7tKX5LbQsbHCvH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v74x6k6usus","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CvOSABDzcSJtXn67"}
{"name":"Burning Heart","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This mage throws all caution to the wind to take down his opponents.</p><p> At the beginning of his turn, he may choose to make himself Vulnerable (until the end of his next turn) to apply a –2 penalty to rolls to resist or avoid powers he casts this turn (this does not affect opponent’s rolls to shake the effect off on their turn), and to increase his powers damage by 2.","notes":"Fantasy: Wizards and Mystics page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any), Strong Willed"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.6ukxMc1YSDvgXdFd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"D1IAat2rTCPfY61U"}
{"name":"Above The Law","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Police cannot detain this character. Even if arrested, he cannot be held or charged unless he is caught redhanded committing a felony. Federal agents can take someone with Above the Law into custody, but he must remain in Federal custody or else be released.","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.swBxSfNuJ4vOrqfh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"D34rLhfKjiGCxB7r"}
{"name":"Arcane Warrior Adept","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The mage is comfortable in armor, and can weave her magic despite the restrictions of metal rings and bindings. She ignores 3 points of Arcane Fatigue from metal armor.","notes":"Dungeon Delvers Toolkit page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic), Strength d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.dungeon-delver.VPSmKadMlPjZkRLT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1v14jf8cc2e","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Dungeon Delver","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"D6kQld1O8yfadQ8S"}
{"name":"Long Shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some shooters can see a far target as if it were right in front of them. If a shooter does not move in a round or has aimed the previous round, the range of his ranged weapon is now doubled. Targets at long range are treated as if they have +1 armor.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Marksman, St d8, Shooting d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.tC0Wvcw1krVbnmsZ"}},"_id":"D74HWFGZxYXFKrMm"}
{"_id":"D81CEEDUkKft3mmb","name":"Talented","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’re gifted. In fact, you might even be good enough to make a living at it, kid! Choose a Performance specialization each time you take this Edge. You get +2 to all your rolls with the chosen specialization. Also, in general, you’re able to find a nightclub or theater willing to give you the stage once a week. Whenever you do, you earn $5 x the total of your skill roll in box office receipts, cover charges, and/or tips.</p><p>This Edge doesn’t guarantee you fame. That, you still have to earn the hard way.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.d7XycBYQBUOXYAnh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Tower Of Will","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some people know their minds better than others and have trained to keep it that way. A character with this Edge may add +2 to any attempt to resist being mentally controlled by unnatural means, whether by a creature’s Special Ability, magical artifact, or magical spell. The +2 bonus also applies to resisting Tests of Wills.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.ylbqMo0ruCuV4jwl"}},"_id":"DAffvwd1IEx2e2Nq"}
{"name":"Picard Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A clever (and daring) pilot may ‘pump’ the warp engines for a split-second in order to confuse her foes by seeming to appear in two places at once.</p><p>Roll Piloting, opposed by the enemy commander's Smarts. With a success, the enemy vessel receives 1 fewer initiative cards on the next round. With a raise, the enemy commander is also Shaken. With a failure, your ship flounders in space, receiving 1 fewer initiative cards on the next round.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Ace; Knowledge (Tactics) d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.kxmE8act6wLiEYGf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DH9okd0LaRYWBL9W"}
{"name":"Monster Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is completely immune to Fear checks from one broad type of creature, such as ghosts, werewolves, vampires, or constructs. If applied to spellcasters, it includes the fear spell as well.</p><p> The Game Master is the final arbiter of whether or not the Edge applies to a particular horror.</p><p> The Edge may be taken multiple times, each applying to a different creature type.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.HbOEdkD8H5pY0213"}},"_id":"DQXEQHYpvX3ltA74"}
{"name":"Magic Laundry","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"It doesn’t seem to matter what scrapes this suave hero gets into or what he is wearing, his clothing is always immaculate with minimal effort. This agent can take a crumpled shirt from a saddle bag, give it a shake, and it will look as though it has just been pressed. Had a tussle with some cultists on your way to dinner? No problem. Just give that jacket a wipe down with a handkerchief and it will look as good as new.<p>Agents with Magic Laundry gain +1 to Persuasion and Taunt rolls when appearance is a factor, +1 to Stealth rolls when blending in to a crowd is important and looking dirty or unkempt would make the agent stand out, and +1 to Stealth rolls when using <b>Vanishing Act.</b><p>Magic Laundry also gives +2 to Repair rolls to mend items of clothing. With a Raise, the repair is so good, the item looks like new.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Secret Files of Section D, page 8","notes":"Secret Files of Section D, page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6uwu6resjqd","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Section D","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.tsbnB08oqznjXOtN"}},"_id":"DSnDnBkcf1XS8BA7"}
{"_id":"DfOKKhJRKlktMYbw","name":"Veteran Of The Concrete Jungle","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A Veteran of the Concrete Jungle has been walking the mean streets for a while now. She’s done a lot and seen more. She starts at Seasoned Rank, which means she has four Advances to spend immediately after character creation.</p><p>Such experience comes with a price, though. If you decide to take this Edge for your shamus, draw a single card from the Action Deck and show it to the GM. He’ll compare it to the table on page 50 to see what your hero faced in the past. Be warned—the results can be extreme, ranging from serious maiming to insanity.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 11","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Occult d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.qUJx1m5UHMX4cjv3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mipxyqx0ib","path":"Fantasy Edges","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Enhance Spirit Weapon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">The warrior adept is able to improve her Spirit Weapon with two additional Feature slots. Each time this Edge is </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">taken the hero may completely re-imagine their weapon, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">which means all Features and Flaws can be re-allocated or changed. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Enhance Spirit Weapon may only be selected once per </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Rank. If taken at hero creation, this counts as the Novice selection, and this Edge cannot be taken again until the character reaches Seasoned Rank. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Source:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\"> The Warrior Adept, page 2</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Warrior Adept)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.A58IkTqgPRFg3DEh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2ppcwdakcbx","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Dg8JmvsAOEbpJTQw"}
{"name":"Mentalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Constant contact with multiple minds gives this Force User an edge when it comes to forcing or resisting Force assaults. They may add a +2 to opposed Force rolls, whether they are using their powers against a foe or defending against a rival.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Smarts d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.ZdkZVaVjHBLijgUj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DqwoJrLE08hiuFdU"}
{"name":"Bio Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Bio Hunters destroy the biological horrors (biohorrors) that infest numerous areas, either by accident or intent. As a cleaner, you deal with all manner of strange creatures on a daily basis. To successfully combat these creatures, you need to have a broad understanding of their biology and iron nerves. A cleaner can Reroll Fear checks. Extensive research also allows the cleaner to exploit weak points, increasing the bonus damage from Called Shots by +2; this only affects Called Shots that already get bonus damage.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Research d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.uVhmPwgkTefBj93x"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Dv2OckWRK0ceOzop"}
{"name":"Piloting Test","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Maintaining this increased speed is risky, however, applying a cumulative -2 penalty to all Driving, Piloting, or Boating Tests per consecutive round the abnormal speed is sustained.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.ZRYwkwxsvGn75VZY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Dv3lpMaNjyaQGUUV"}
{"name":"Charge","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When the hero charges an enemy by Running, jumping, or riding at least 2” in a straight line to attack them in melee, he gets a free reroll on the damage roll.</p><p>If the attack provides multiple damage rolls, e.g.</p><p>Frenzy or Sweep, choose only one to reroll.</p><p>Any target (no more than two Sizes larger than the hero) hit by this attack must roll Athletics higher than or equal to the damage or fall Prone (mounted enemies fall from their mount)","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d6+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.yDLIH85MtjofQQsB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EIHpqfgJT70eJZ8x"}
{"name":"Signature Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This special wand grants its wielder a +1 bonus to their Wandslinging roll for one selected power and a +1 bonus to resist powers directed at the wielder.<p>A wielder may take this Edge multiple times, each time it applies to a different wand and power. The effects of multiple wands do not stack.<p>If the Signature Wand is destroyed or lost, he may regain the benefits by attuning a new wand or spending eight hours meditating with an already attuned wand.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.wn73525SaDQlTdS4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EUrA8dHdy6EIqJrz"}
{"name":"Test Taker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some individuals do well on tests even when they study far less than most. Those with this Edge add a permanent +2 to their Academics secondary attribute.","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Smarts d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.fuWmvYTDJ3AknUCg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EVNhcqKNDwSSiNpp"}
