{"name":"Arcane Background (Warrior Adept)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Arcane Skill: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Focus (Spirit) </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Starting Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">2<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Power Points: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">10<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Powers Available: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Boost/lower </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;\">Trait, damage field, darksight, deflection, farsight, fear, havoc, healing, intangibility, invisibility, protection, relief, sloth/speed, smite, warrior&rsquo;s gift</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Warrior adepts come from all walks of life&mdash; Shaolin monks, street toughs, cage fighters, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">etc. They have access to some powers, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">but their main function is to fight, </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">and so they are the only magic- wielders with access to Spirit Weapons (see below).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Because warrior adepts&rsquo; abilities are internally focused, powers normally usable on others have the Range Limitation of Self, which reduces the Power Point cost for activating those powers (see </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Trappings </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">in </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">). The same Limitation &ldquo;discount&rdquo; should apply to </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">smite</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">, as it can<br />only be cast on the hero&rsquo;s Spirit Weapon. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Havoc </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">and </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">fear </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">are the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">final exceptions&mdash; </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">havoc </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">can only<br />be activated using the Cone Template, emanating from the caster, and </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">fear </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">requires line of sight within the Smarts range listed (these last two do </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">not </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">count as Limitations).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 16.000000pt; font-family: 'LeagueGothic';\">SPIRIT WEAPON </span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Warrior adepts use their will to form and fight with a </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">weapon made of pure magic. They use their creativity and prowess to create a unique melee weapon, one that can neither be destroyed nor stolen, as long as the warrior adept can breathe life into it. Conjuring the Spirit Weapon is a free action. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">If a Spirit Weapon would ever be considered disarmed, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">taken, sundered (treat Object Toughness as equal to the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">hero&rsquo;s Spirit die type), or in any other way removed from a hero&rsquo;s possession, or rendered useless, it instead dissipates into nothingness for the warrior adept to re- form as a free action on their next turn. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Should a character throw their Spirit Weapon, it will </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">disappear after the attack is resolved. The </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">character can re-form their Spirit Weapon </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">as a free action on their next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Making use of the weapon requires the Fighting skill or Athletics (Throwing) if a </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">thrown weapon. Base range for throwing a Spirit Weapon is 3/6/12. Due to the &ldquo;up close and personal&rdquo; nature of Spirit Weapons, a warrior adept cannot create a weapon which requires </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">Shooting.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Spirit Weapons can take any </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">form the warrior adept can imagine, and while they typically resemble real world </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">weapons, they don&rsquo;t have to. Mechanically Spirit Weapons start out as a Str+d4 melee weapon, modified with Features and Flaws chosen from the table below. The Spirit Weapon starts with three Feature slots. More Features may be added by applying an equivalent number </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">of Flaws or by taking the Enhance </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">Spirit Weapon Edge.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">A Spirit Weapon keeps its </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">current shape, Features, and Flaws whenever formed, unless the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">warrior adept takes the Enhance </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">Spirit Weapon Edge. Due to their nature, Spirit Weapons are not subject to the Minimum </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">Strength rules (see </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Example 1: Vern&rsquo;s character is a down home country </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">girl, and she wants to reflect that by making her Spirit </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Weapon a pool cue. She starts with Str+d4 and adds the Two-Handed Flaw, which gives her four slots to work with. Vern decides this pool cue should deal Str+d8 damage (2 slots), provide +1 Parry (1 slot), and have Reach 1 (1 slot). She now has: Pool Cue (Range 3/6/9, Damage Str+d8, Reach 1, +1 Parry). </span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">Example 2: Darrell wants his hero&rsquo;s Spirit Weapon to appear as dual buzz saw shields. He takes Dual Weapon, Parry Increase twice, and Damage Increase once. He needs </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">one slot of Flaws, but the only one that fits is Fighting Only, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">which provides two slots. He chooses Armor Piercing with </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">his final slot. He now has: Dual Buzz Saw Shield (Damage Str+d6, +2 Parry, Fighting Only)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Features</h2>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Feature</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Slots</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Notes</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Armor Piercing</td>\n<td>Add AP 2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum AP 3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cover</td>\n<td>Provides -2 Cover</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum -4 Cover</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Damage Increase</td>\n<td>Increases damage die type</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum d12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dual Weapon</td>\n<td>Appears as two weapons</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>See Two Weapons and the Two-Fisted Edge in <em>Savage Worlds</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grapple</td>\n<td>Provides +1 bonus when Grappling</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum +4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heavy Weapon</td>\n<td>Counts as a Heavy Weapon</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instant Re-form</td>\n<td>Warrior adept doesn't need to wait for next turn to re-conjure weapon</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lingering Damage</td>\n<td>Continues causing damage after a successful attack</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>See Lingering Damage Power Modifier in&nbsp;<em>Savage Worlds</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Parry Increase</td>\n<td>Provides +1 Parry</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum +3 Parry; is&nbsp;<em>not</em> multiplied by Dual Weapon Feature if Abmidextrous Edge is taken</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reach Increase</td>\n<td>Provides Reach 1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum Reach 2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<h2>Flaws</h2>\n<table style=\"width: 98.8806%; height: 148px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Flaw</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 5.84906%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Slots</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Notes</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Fighting Only</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Cannot be thrown</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Reduced Parry</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Weapon has -1 Parry</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;May be taken only once</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Slow Forming</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Takes an Action to conjure</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">Cannot be combined with Instant Re-form Feature</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Two-Handed</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Must be wielded with two hands</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"column\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.59C2KcqLOYwH90A2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2ppcwdakcbx","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EY7v0aVAL7Sraboe"}
{"name":"Herbal Mastery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Through extensive study of herbal alchemical </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">components, the herbal alchemist has learned how to enhance his concoctions with greater effects. When creating a </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">concoction, an herbal alchemist can use up to 6 Power Points in components instead of 3.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Example: Laeressa is creating an entangle bag. She uses 6 Power Points in components to create a concoction that will splash a strong, sticky plant </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;\">resin in a Medium Blast Template.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy), Herbalism d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KvHtA4MkbxziVYjN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2ppcwdakcbx","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EkGaFSdl9IGq72Ew"}
{"name":"King Of The Sky","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero gains one Piloting re-roll per game session without spending a benny.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Ace, Professional Piloting"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.ewiDoxvePoL78En6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EmDj7dTmjNgeLOCw"}
{"name":"Gravitic Acclimation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your spacer knows how to operate in different gravities. She ignores the usual −2 penalty for operating in a gravity other than her own (see Zero-G, page 64).","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.wO22VmjWnBnQCTYG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Enf4VJNInVKHpSHE"}
{"name":"Sterner Stuff","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When this hero has rippertech implanted, the surgeon gains a +2 bonus to his Knowledge (Rippertech) roll due to the subject’s phenomenal constitution, raw willpower, or fierce determination.<p>In addition, the Ripper adds +2 to all Vigor rolls required when using extractions (including attempting to use multiple concoctions (see <b>Using Extracts,</b> page 47).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, V d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.H8XGEGTaDNfkvQ7Z"}},"_id":"EtaTxBwleAI3bsL6"}
{"name":"Demon Slayer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Demon slayers may come from an awakened lineage, a special blessing, or occasionally just coming in contact with the blood of a demon. Regardless of the source, demon slayers add +2 to Fear tests from demonic sources (demons themselves, their minions, or powers), and ignore the demon’s invulnerability to normal weapons.","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.7B6UJ0ETskeUYHGF"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"F4zPRt8qbj4jZTTx"}
{"name":"Super-Amalgamated","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You read a lot and tend to use large words. You live by the philosophy of why use a fifty-cent word, when a two-dollar word will do, and your voracious reading has given you a little knowledge across a broad range of subject. Once per game session, you may spend a bennie to recall a useful fact that relates to the current situation.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"WC, Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.zStAgm2DoI5rEJKs"}},"_id":"FAb9eBpjT6wPWAKa"}
{"name":"Fast Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The machines have become faster and can move more quickly. The mage can use a power at the normal range defined in the Power's description by expending +2 Power Points. ","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Veteran, Master d10 "}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.jLtEVGauQulOzYSG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_h360mwewe9","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FDNmjEyhq9eNOrxd"}
{"name":"Dreamer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Dreamers are precogs who are cultivated from the ranks of the psychically gifted and trained to examine the past and future to aid the agency. They may look into the past with a successful Notice roll and into the future with a Notice –2 roll. Each success and raise reveals one bit of information. The exact information discovered is at the Director’s discretion. Only one attempt per scene may be made.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Psionics), Danger Sense"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.8hN0pGxTnkVuHBz4"}},"_id":"FIhrdXSe3n3WTfhW"}
{"name":"Pushy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character knows a lot of people he can get to help him out when he asks. He either gives them no choice but to pitch in or he’s learned to trick them into picking up the phone or answering the door. He can acquire the aid of one additional Contact per session (see Friends of Ours in Chapter Two).","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.7Cci4WuSx9xERgL9"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FLxlNE3MuQlfmo3L"}
{"name":"Darting Shade","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Assassins must move with great stealth. By drawing upon the shadows, a skilled assassin can mask their movement towards their goal. </p><p>The assassin can move their full Pace without being seen. If the enemies are unaware of them, the movement doesn’t require a roll. If the enemy is alert, the assassin only needs to make an unopposed Stealth check. The movement must start and end with the assassin in an area of Dim illumination (or darker). If the assassin attempts a Sneak Attack (see Stealth in Savage Worlds), the target’s Notice roll suffers illumination penalty as if the lighting was one step darker (normal to Dim, etc.)","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.x80jJyYBfMWVAzsN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FS7BDnHWo1SoIVm5"}
{"name":"Alienist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A rare thing in Victorian times, a hero with this Edge is sympathetic to those who suffer from a damaged psyche. This hero can heal temporary Reason loss in a patient. See Treatment on page 31 for details of treating insanity.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Healing d6, Persuasion d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.09CiJSeX8yMoFsld"}},"_id":"FXHc808GlzSjVNL9"}
{"name":"Ride It Out","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While in a ground vehicle the hero may spend a benny when called upon to roll on the Out of Control or vehicle Critical Hits tables. On the former, the benny reduces the result by one category, whereas for the latter it allows the character to shift the category up or down one category, as desired. The benny is spent after the appropriate roll is made on the respective table.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ace, Road Maneuver, Agility d8+, Driving d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.WqGxHPCW1xEaB5Jk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FYYLhyg125ipQgfz"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7wj2fq58w9r","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Petramancy","color":"#000000","name":"Petramancy","children":["SxojPuzvHMR46aGa","Fo58nONR1qnnvYkv","9jg8XQQ5TORxciTh","8o3sghM9ZatMKBsq"],"folderPath":["temp_mipxyqx0ib"]}},"_id":"FbP708ZaZwIgVwrF"}
{"name":"Stunning Gloom","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The unnatural shadow weapon causes a weakness that can be exploited.</p><p>Any attack made with a shadow blade that causes at least a Shaken effect also makes the target Vulnerable. If you spend a Benny, the target is Stunned instead.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Shadow Blade"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.dwzQurEdr7dYKi9R"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FiGSNDvePuM2RLzD"}
{"name":"Cyber Tolerant","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The individual’s body can handle cyberware better than most. His Maximum Strain for cyberware is increased by +4 (see page 29).","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.cesROih53hfEhiTg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FiLeUUc0nd1JBHAN"}
{"name":"Lapidarist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"An experienced Petramancer can activate inherent powers in gems and crystals. This hero can spend up to three Power Points to activate an associated power from any crystal or gemstone in her possession. This allows her to use any power normally available from that type of stone of her Rank or lower in her particular setting, provided that the power costs less than 3 Power Points (including the cost of any modifiers). </p><p>Drawing out a power takes incredible concentration. While using this ability, the Petramancer can do nothing else for her entire turn but make a Petramancy roll at –2 (no Multi-Actions can be taken that turn). </p><p>The Petramancer uses her personal Power Points to activate the power, and once the power’s initial Duration is finished (it cannot be maintained) the stone goes inert (but can be used again in the future). This is the Gadgeteer edge reimagined for this Arcane Background.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Petramancy), Petramancy d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.QiGuw84dpeW13CAK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7wj2fq58w9r","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Fo58nONR1qnnvYkv"}
{"name":"Wrestler","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The contender can use locks on their opponent and leverage to punish them while grappling. They may make an Athletics check as a free action when they begin their turn in a grapple (so to improve a grapple they control or to break out) or to Crush their foe. Your hero suffers no penalty if they do not have both hands free while grappling and may choose not to be Vulnerable when your foe is Bound. Note: Remember the Acrobat edge allows for free rerolls with Athletics checks to grapple.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+, Athletics d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.8TwMPIqooraLd65R"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FvAioduwUIOhmXS4"}
{"name":"Maven","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"At the beginning of each hostile encounter, the maven may make a Knowledge (Battle) roll. For each success and raise, he receives a benny that may be used for any agents on his team. Bennies not used by the end of scene are discarded. Note: If more than one maven is on a team, the test is treated as a cooperative roll as detailed in the Savage Worlds core rulebook.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Knowledge (Battle) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.CAMX45jTxFl52fs2"}},"_id":"FyiJ3m2Nc8CjOU4a"}
