{"name":"Troubadour","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Troubadours are traveling entertainers who bring news and amusement to people across the land. Despite using the rules for Arcane Background (Miracles), Troubadours typically don’t worship a specific deity for their power. They believe in the power of the arts, so their Arcane Skill is Perform (Spirit) instead of Faith. Additionally, they don’t worry about sins, though they have to deal with occasional “strain.” Strain: Troubadours who roll a 1 on their Perform die, regardless of the Wild Die, suffer the effects as for a minor sin (–2 to Perform for a week). Should they critically fail such a roll, they suffer the effect of a major sin (complete loss of powers for a week and –4 to “normal” uses of the Perform skill). This represents terrible strain on their voice, mind, or raw nerves for the given period. The Perform skill may also be used simply to entertain instead of activating powers. In these cases, the Troubadour can earn money for his performance. A successful skill roll per “set” (usually a couple of hours) nets him $1d6 for every 10 members of the audience. Double this number with a raise. The performer may add his Charisma to the roll when using the skill in this way. This assumes the audience can tip instead of a set fee. The audience may also tip with libations, livestock, blind dates with their daughters, or local rumors that may lead to adventure, fortune, and glory.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Miracles), Perform d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.tXKOs906BfOsenRF"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"IQ42S6iqjCvICXIV"}
{"name":"Powerful Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The nanomachines have become more powerful in operation and allow the mage to be have double the range for swarm traps. ","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Seasoned, Master d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.cEF3Eip7GrndKZlQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_h360mwewe9","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"IURwiFSKU4cmLkjl"}
{"name":"Csi","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Crime scene investigators (CSI) examine locations after a crime to examine forensic evidence to gather information and discover clues. A CSI makes a Knowledge (Forensics) roll at a crime scene before the Investigation roll. Success at the former adds a +1 modifier to the latter, with an additional +1 per raise.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Investigation d8+, Knowledge (Forensics) d8+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.6ch4XwQ8CNiSovOZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"IbqJ4ZEBycKIbR3d"}
{"_id":"IlGDqTyJNXsMkHVr","name":"Moxie","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your gumshoe can cut a mook down to size with a few sharp words, or turn a goon’s threats into a laughing matter with only a sentence or two. Your hero gets a +2 to all Taunt rolls and can use Taunt in place of his Smarts or Spirit when resisting a Test of Wills.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Taunt d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.5VmQ41VRzDhnQlZO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Wheel And Deal","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Firing a weapon with one hand while driving at unsafe speeds requires fine coordination. This character can reduce Multi-Action penalties by 2 when driving a vehicle and firing a one-handed weapon.","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Driving d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.3KpfUwGQaWeFAukq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Ir027uZEPVwSfUfP"}
{"name":"Relegate","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some leaders instill fear in their underlings. This fear of failing their leader reminds them of what the consequences might be for letting him down. Such leaders don’t need to be seen to be effective.</p><p> This Edge extends the command range of Leadership Edges for Extras to within the same city.","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Intimidation d8+, Command"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.A2eRD9ry9Kk2RjE2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"IvDbU8zcMYXEkCGr"}
