{"name":"Low Profile","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Even though you have had your name in the spotlight, you have managed to downplay your involvement in events. When a roll is made to recognize you, the roll is at -4. This modifier can be doubled by spending a Benny.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.XpLQs2UdResBYlk1"}},"_id":"J1l6uhozvSuACeUl"}
{"name":"Keep It Afloat","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While in a waterborne vehicle the hero may spend a benny when called upon to roll on the Out of Control or vehicle Critical Hits tables. On the former, the benny reduces the result by one category, whereas for the latter it allows the character to shift the category up or down one category, as desired. The benny is spent after the appropriate roll is made on the respective table.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ace, Wave Maneuver, Agil- ity d8+, Boating d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.glMAoB9k2WtPaMrZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"J8jKLIsCfiagwIO0"}
{"name":"Explorer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has mastered the art of surviving in a variety of climates and environments. She receives a +2 bonus to Survival rolls. Additionally, she’s got a knack for picking the best route through rough ground. She and a number of accompanying characters treat the terrain type (see Travel in Savage Worlds) as one level better (so Hard becomes Average, for example), to a minimum of Easy.","notes":"The Last Parsec - Leviathan","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"7"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.U8mFdan6RYDteKX3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JBUOg80aq3ewJCxq"}
{"name":"Last Man Standing","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Through sheer determination, the character can push past the effects of shock and trauma. By spending a benny, he ignores the effects of wound penalties for the remainder of the scene.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"L, Grizzled"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.13ZXDzAx9QlEkmYS"}},"_id":"JCF5mmSTbMYVWgTF"}
{"_id":"JRnERV307eQsgYvE","name":"Dig In!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your soldier has learned the importance of staying down and dug in. When the warrior is lying prone or under cover, all foes suffer a −1 penalty (in addition to normal cover bonuses) to all attack rolls, and he gets a +1 Toughness bonus to avoid damage from Area Effect weapons.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.V7Y8MKPLcFNKjh2A"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Trollkin Toughness","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are exceptionally difficult to put down, and can survive what seems like a lethal wound and bounce back quickly. You gain the Hardy monstrous ability, and do not suffer a Wound when Shaken again while already Shaken. In addition, if you get a Raise on your Vigor roll after being incapacitated, you regain one Wound and are no longer incapacitated (though you’re still prone).","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Trollkin race, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.mrADYxK2JTvlTQdh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JVlfrjyFTNsuQdTj"}
{"name":"Master Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who take their study of crafting artifacts to the highest level are able to make major artifacts–permanent magic items that are infused with one or more powers and are continuously active or usable. For example, a wielder holding a major artifact with <i>havoc</i> imbued on it can blast enemies away repeatedly at-will.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Improved Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.1t6Bb015ai0UJzrC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JX7fBUl6ppGapdAZ"}
{"name":"Targeteer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot knows how to bring the vessel itself to bear during a dogfight, and as such adds Handling to Shooting Trait rolls with onboard weapons.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Shooting d6, Electronics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.YFLc37aGkpKhnWy8"}},"_id":"JeTO6lDLoSii3Puy"}
{"name":"Jink And Juke","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero may attempt a Piloting Test opposed by his opponent’s Smarts as a maneuver. If successful, the character increase’s his aircraft’s Parry by an amount equal to the Test’s successes for one round.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Ace, Notice d8+, Piloting d12+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.mFzqXLQufuHVOKps"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JpiFmhQMEXBZq8Nv"}
{"name":"Heir Of Siberys","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"An Heir of Siberys gains the Dragonmark Arcane Background, but when she activates the power, she may automatically apply a single Ritual effect as if she had successfully completed a Ritual to activate the power.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Dragonmark race, d12+ in any two skills, cannot have Arcane Background (Dragonmark or Aberrant Dragonmark) or Child of Khyber"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.RzWDgW0R22lmhG23"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JqwFvNWoMwSEoS8o"}
{"name":"Impeccable Timing","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has amazing reaction speed. Should he be dealt less than a 10 for initiative, his card is treated as a 10 of the same suit (ties are resolved via opposed Agility rolls).","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"L, Agility d10, Quick"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.skKP6FVjPakQC3Nz"}},"_id":"KKjt7YvSk9t6FD0i"}
{"name":"Gunslinger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The senior’s sidearm is like an extension of his body. He can disarm a cultist or shoot the smile off a chupacabra at 20 paces. Gunslingers reduce any and all penalties (including Fatigue, wounds, range, etc.) by 2 when attacking with pistols. GUTS Requirements: Sophomore, Spirit d6+ This cowgirl has stared the things that lurk in the dark right in the mug and learned to handle her fear. She ignores two points of Fear penalties for both her Spirit roll and any Fright Table result.","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.prf138ZH14bbhE0L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KR3GcHewFNFQANt4"}
{"name":"Deadly","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"For this agent, everything is a weapon. Any object that would normally do negligible damage (such as a paper clip or a thimble) does Str+d4. Additionally, normally non-lethal items can be used to inflict deadly damage at the Director’s discretion.<p><b>Example:</b> Jake Britain (with a Str d6) is sitting at a table in a street cafe when a Pandoran agent rushes toward him. Jake lunges with his plastic drinking straw, smashing it into the Pandoran’s throat, causing d6+d4 damage! Leaving him wheezing in the road, Jake quickly and quietly flees the scene.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 22","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Sm d8, Fighting or Throwing d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.i1ioGTruLPY01NTp"}},"_id":"KdiLAJHSCwohYyC4"}
{"name":"Hustle","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You move like lightning! Your character may roll an additional die for running rolls, the character chooses the result they wish to use. Also, your hero reduces the action penalty due to running by one. Note: Hustle combined with Steady Hands removes the Running penalty completely.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Athletics d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.NBPyZbJyFTU6V61J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KgvXEWtj5AnU3dbQ"}
{"name":"Renown","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"In Victorian society, it is most often birth and finances that defines one’s status. But great explorers, celebrated war heroes, actors, artists, and even poets may also climb the social ladder by their deeds. The character’s Status improves one step, to a maximum of +5.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.9diMVJ6XfT3mRP6C"}},"_id":"KmrLL4NUsdGS0dJR"}
{"name":"Prankster","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your criminal always comes prepared for the worst. He makes various gadgets that are harmless but can make noise, project light, or disperse smoke or odorous gas.</p><p> Once per scene, this character can spend a Benny to trigger one of his pranks. The criminal must explain how he managed to set up the diversion or booby trap. He might have had the help of an accomplice or previously visited the location.</p><p> He then makes a Thievery roll to place a Small Burst Template on the point of origin. Targets caught within the template must roll to Evade (at –2 if the Prankster got a raise). Any target who fails is Distracted or Vulnerable (player’s choice). If a target’s attempt is a Critical Failure, he is Stunned.","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Repair d6+, Thievery d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.tkvOh1M8DFDiUqxr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"L10avGU6R5AYScQS"}
