{"name":"Dabbler","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Despite a lack of any training, you have enough ex- posure to the occult that you can try and “wing” casting magic contained by an occult tome or scroll (or the like, such as magic scrawled on the wall of an ancient tomb.) Reading the scroll or occult tome and summoning forth its magic requires a Knowledge (Occult) check. Apply a –1 modifier per 3 Power Points (rounded up) the scroll (or whatever) provides for the powers. Success means the power is activated at the potency determined by the indicated Power Points, or at its minimum possible potency otherwise.</p><p>Whether the attempt to use the power succeeds or fails, a Fear check is required. Apply the same modifier previously indicated, with an additional –2 if the previous Knowledge (Occult) roll failed. This can result in Sanity loss if the optional Sanity rule is used.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Occultist *, Spirit d8+, Knowledge (Occult) d10+; cannot have an Arcane Background"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.pWG7DOpN2zc4DX6Q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LRFpgHShaEgz6H8l"}
{"_id":"LW82gWy0nv4eIDhV","name":"Hitman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This hitter isn’t your average mook. She’s got a knack for putting her shots where they count. When she rolls a raise on a Shooting attack roll, she gets a bonus 1d10 to damage instead of the usual 1d6.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Agility d6+, Smarts d6+, Spirit d8+, Shooting d8+, Stealth d8+, Streetwise d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.xGUwfW1qRc9weSDm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"The Secret Guard","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the VSG gain +1 Damage to all damage rolls against monsters and PARRY (3).","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Vatican Secret Guard, Seasoned, Vow (Catholic Church)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.R0Yk2UfrRfFHwHso"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LWnk0TjWXo8fNubi"}
{"name":"Gunner’s Mate","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to antici- pate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in watercraft. The character’s Fast Tar- gets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed watercraft.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Boating d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.zee4iJFDuqzKKpLL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LX7i3lRigmDFAmuS"}
