{"name":"Improved Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once an artificer has mastered imbuing powers into arcane devices, she can advance to crafting permanent magic items with the Improved Artificer Edge. Artificers with this Edge have the ability to make minor artifacts–items imbued with powers that can recharge their given Power Points.<p>Minor artifacts are particularly useful for equipping characters without the Artificer Edge, since unlike arcane devices, these items can replenish Power Points without the need for an artificer to tinker with it.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.pjvZ1Dt8bdwTrcf2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LaXArr8F8GJvArSz"}
{"name":"Tannis Bond","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Banshee imbues certain of her children with her phenomenal energy. Those so chosen add +2 to the damage total of any attack made with a tannis weapon, and the bonus of any armor made from tannis (such as aknouk breastplates, see page 45), is treated as additional Toughness rather than Armor (so it ignores the AP value of incoming attacks).</p><p>Both bonuses count as “magical.”","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Anouk or Banshee Born or Guardian, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.TF3HBPjry9gJgDO3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Lb2jFkyEf7HF2Si2"}
{"name":"Visions","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Dark dreams or flashing visions of doom and dread fill this person’s thoughts. While they are disturbing, they are often useful as well.</p><p> Once per game session, the visionary is granted a vision. This may be a sudden flash that can occur at any time, a nightmare that only happens when sleeping, or it may be an active process such as reading tea leaves or tarot cards. When this occurs, use the Signs & Portents system described on page 28.</p><p> Immediately after, the visionary must make a Smarts roll. If the roll is failed, the visions take their toll on her mind, confusing fantasy with reality, the past with the present, or simply straining the mind with arcane energy. The seer loses 1 Sanity point.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 7","notes":"Horror Companion, page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.bYBsQBHjWdfMGunZ"}},"_id":"Lcqwe3eweMeHKNT0"}
{"name":"Mongo-tech","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Note: Mongo-Tech replaces the Gadgeteer Edge from Savage Worlds.</p><p>A character with this incredible Edge can create a weird science device in a flash! Doing so requires parts of some kind that can be quickly jury-rigged. The player is encouraged to “explain” her device to the rest of the party in terms only scientists of her caliber would understand!</p><p>The inventor then makes a Weird Science roll as an action. If successful, she has a new device imbued with any power available to her in the setting and as many unspent Power Points as she has available to put into it. She may transfer these Power Points from her pool or other devices on her person as she wishes. (Spent Power Points may not be used!)</p><p>If the Weird Science roll fails, the device isn’t built and she loses all the Power Points she was going to transfer into it!</p><p>Once the device is drained of Power Points, or at the end of the scene, it falls apart and stops working. ROCKET JOCK Requirements: Novice, Piloting d8+, Shooting d6+ The pilot can fire one weapon system per action without incurring a multi- action penalty while Piloting or Driving a land vehicle, or aircraft.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 42","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Weird Science), Weird Science d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.NrPBdHyUSKYZdn4p"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LroppVO8jgPt0a7b"}
{"name":"One With The Land","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is attuned to their preferred terrain at an instinctual level. By noticing changes in the wilds around them, such as animal behavior, the woodsman may attempt Notice checks that span their environment for miles around (up to the edges of the preferred terrain, however.) This is only possible while they are themselves within the preferred terrain, and a –2 penalty is applied to the Notice roll per mile away the subject is.</p><p>This Edge need only be taken once to apply to all of a character’s preferred terrains (if more than one.)","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Live off the Land, Spirit d12+, Knowledge (Nature) d12+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.ymHnBk6RRRFiYzov"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Lsi2R5i2iSc916ic"}
{"name":"Gold Bug","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Treasure Hunters are those people that travel the globe looking for treasure and priceless relics. They can be found in ancient burial grounds to ruined cities. Relic Hunters gain a +2 to Academics Tests when determining the location to ancient treasures.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d6, Academics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.rLZ5CHKmjnBmnA1A"}},"_id":"M2JhYvVsHBS3XyqL"}
{"_id":"MSoVrRcjhVggH1XB","name":"College Boy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’re a University man, from Heidelberg, Harvard, or the Sorbonne. This Edge provides an extra four skill points to spend on Smarts-related skills. At least one skill must be a Knowledge skill at d6 or better. Being “at University” also gives the character informal ties to other graduates of the same school.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"21"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.kOyymo5RmymjRwxS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Hack Sensors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A crafty officer may attempt to hack opponents’ sensors and upload false readings. To do so, roll Knowledge (Computers) opposed by whomever is manning the opponent's sensors. With a success, the opponent's sensors (including targeting) suffer a –1 penalty as you fill their readout with ‘white noise’. The victim can fix the hack with a Repair roll, at –2 if you scored a raise.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Knowledge (Computers) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.ks9O88UiSJ928wKM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"MYlnsepYSXNKXUUF"}
{"name":"Spectre","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A master of infiltration, Spectre unit members gain +1 to Climbing, Lockpicking and Stealth rolls. These benefits stack with those gained from the Thief Edge.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Ag d10, Thief"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.XGBZHxuBc3BOidPr"}},"_id":"MbVVpGPt9r4JWyqL"}
{"_id":"Mcz7LP7NpC3UFSnM","name":"Virtuoso","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’ve got the kind of talent that can make you famous. Choose a Perform (Specialization) in which you already have the Talented Edge. You gain an additional +2 to all rolls with that skill. On top of that, you’re able to occasionally book gigs that bring in the big bucks, but no more often than once a month. This gig earns you $10 x the total of your skill roll. The rest of the month, you’re stuck doing club acts and the like, but hey, twenty bucks is twenty bucks. Like Talented, this Edge doesn’t ensure your performer is going to be famous, but it sure helps!","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d10+, Talented"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.vswlWDVFJLEvkuc3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Keep It Together","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot is capable of making instinctive adjustments to thrust, systems, and flight in an effort to keep the craft flying. Add Handling to the number of Wounds the craft can suffer.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Piloting d8, Ace Edge, Smarts d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.LwVm0sSv1VBLqlJT"}},"_id":"MqDjZa7bPwUUKaHG"}
{"_id":"NF7wRXHTHLnIEAYu","name":"Cry Havoc!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The general has an uncanny knack for knowing when to attack and when to hold back with his troops. Once per Mass Battle, during the Battle Roll Phase, the character may declare a total attack. He must do this before he rolls his Battle die. If the roll succeeds, his enemy loses one extra token.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.8UWdboTQfCfJRTNt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Forgettable Face","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Nothing seems to stand out about this rogue. His appearance is non-descript and instantly forgettable, granting him a +2 bonus on all rolls related to disguise or being recognized. You cannot take this Edge if you have Attractive, Ugly, Scarred, or some other ability that gives you a recognizable appearance. This Edge can only be taken during character creation.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Special"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.6KkgawHPoHv5JOFN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NJLS0rfOl52pTWVz"}
{"name":"Highwayman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This type of outlaw prefers to rob from horseback, often using their superior speed and maneuverability to outrun coaches, whereupon the victim is traditionally ordered to “stand and deliver”. You gain a +2 bonus to Riding and Stealth rolls (the latter applies even when you’re on foot).","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Riding d8, Stealth d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.nCDaCNmpocMmQRdQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NLbAy3tLZc3xJpGT"}
{"name":"Gang Leader","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You gain two more lackeys. They should be created in the same way as your other two lackeys, but all four are independent of each other, and may have different arrangements of attributes, skills, Edges and Hindrances. You can take this Edge multiple times, but cannot have more Gang Leader Edges than you have Leadership Edges.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Command, Lackeys"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.bYpdez9YDibmNIts"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NQszXZcli2HRIB7n"}
{"name":"Weapons Encylopedia","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero can recall the vital statistics and important quirks of practically all known commercially available weapons. This includes – but is not limited to – general levels of reliability, material composition, ammunition capacity, caliber, possible outfitted accessories, etc. Characters without this ability will only have such information on weapons they own or use regularly and will need to successfully roll a Smarts based Knowledge Skill check to recall important details. In addition, Weapons Encyclopedia also includes knowledge on acquiring weapons, so characters will have a +5 bonus on any Skill checks needed to locate or buy weapons.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.rjzBUDw323C3FhUu"}},"_id":"NfNIyYVvrpqZY8rT"}
{"name":"Master Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who take their study of crafting artifacts to the highest level are able to make major artifacts–permanent magic items that are infused with one or more powers and are continuously active or usable. For example, a wielder holding a major artifact with <i>havoc</i> imbued on it can blast enemies away repeatedly at-will.","notes":"Artificer's Codex page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Improved Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.artificers-codex.iGCJgfmLNWUfCYee"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tutlz90icqq","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer's Codex","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Ngy6CNOVg1Zd1bGx"}
{"name":"Dual Wielder","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Dual Wielder may cast two powers with a wand in each hand as two actions without incurring a Multi- Action penalty.<p>She may cast any power s h e knows with each wand, not only attack powers.<p>If the character has Two-Fisted or Two-Gun Kid, the second action may also be a melee or ranged attack respectively.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Ambidextrous, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.vWsr7aQWXnHhizA6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Nso6zspguXxjThu2"}
{"name":"Quick Study","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has learned to adapt his magical studies when necessary. As an action that takes up your entire turn, you can consult your spellbook and spend a Bennie to swap one prepared spell for another that you know.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"AB (Wizardry), Knowledge (Arcana) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.v54esIOv3EeDF1LD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"O19QJViGtLo6J1UY"}
{"name":"Improved Signature Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Signature Wand, but the bonuses while holding the wand increase to +2.","notes":"Wand Magic page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Signature Wand"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.XyTjS7DAiV8FXc7u"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"O3KwQ5zxwFdKXc6q"}
{"name":"Fortune Favors the Bold","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Explorers, cowboys, tomb raiders, and hired guns like Frazer’s Fighters fight creatures of darkness like all Rippers, but crave action and adventure (and sometimes treasure!) more than most other crusaders.<p>Fortune favors the bold, it is said, and those who go through secret initiations (similar to Masonic rituals) at their headquarters in Cairo are particularly blessed. The hero starts each session with one extra Benny (even if an Extra). This likely explains why so many of Frazer’s Fighters survive encounters and stunts others do not.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Frazer's Fighters)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.TVytAvupCS4kx5rr"}},"_id":"OJ1XnjKaYz6B0JmO"}
{"name":"King Of The Sky","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero gains one Piloting re-roll per game session without spending a benny.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Ace, Professional Piloting"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.F6GE8iIHxyNItCpG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OQ6bXOf1EUtJsmJu"}
{"name":"Guts","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Way Out Wester isn’t fearless, she just bucks up and gets the job done even when she’s more scared than a long-tailed chanouk in a room full of rocking chairs.</p><p>Your hero gets a free reroll on Spirit rolls made to resist Fear.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.wTtyPY7pgbsdd5JN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OT8X3PKWIWKbVXbh"}
