{"name":"Lady Luck","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"High rollers and professional gamblers like to have this character by their side when they roll the dice or play cards. She seems to bring good luck to them, and they keep spoiling her hoping that she’ll stay close. This living, breathing embodiment of good fortune begins each session with a special Benny that can only be spent on Gambling rolls. She is able to share her all Bennies (including the one granted by this Edge) with anybody she likes for any Gambling roll. She also wears an expensive piece of jewelry (necklace, earrings, watch, ring, cufflinks, etc.) given to her by a grateful gambler who considers her his lucky charm. This jewelry gives her +1 to Persuasion when Networking. If short on cash, she can sell this jewelry for $50,000. However, if she sells or loses it, she also loses all benefits of this Edge until a patron buys her another piece of jewelry of equal value.","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.TjaaTbsJbuthatKC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OYSHC3i8axpMThEw"}
{"name":"Chosen One","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Various forces of the cosmos often choose champions to serve them. Once per session a Chosen One may ignore a wound that would move them to Incapacitated. After they do so, they gain one Benny. Being a Champion of the universe is risky business, and a lot of folks will want you deader than dead. Therefore, each Chosen One also gains the Enemy (Major) Hinderance. This Enemy is an opposed faction to the faction that selected the Chosen One.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"None"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.C4EqmbUBLJbrHdEt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Oaz3IUK3WitYZst4"}
{"name":"Cyborg","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Cyborgs are humans (or other organic species) who have been augmented with mechanical parts. Sometimes this is done by choice; sometimes it’s the only way to save a badly wounded but still valuable asset.</p><p>The character’s Maximum Strain is doubled (see page 29). This does not stack with Cyber Tolerant, he may have one or the other. The individual must take an additional Major or two Minor Hindrances to compensate for this powerful Edge. Typically, this should relate to the story of how the hero became a cyborg.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.psqKksmYgCWNn3zG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OcQFHkzrubSq1FWz"}
{"name":"Extra Shifter Ability","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The adventurer come from a mixed lineage of shifters and has one additional shifter ability. They can manifest this additional ability while shifted as well.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.Lpp9eAFdriecfj8Q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OdCa0gms6N80m6Ts"}
{"name":"Combat Wizard","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The wizard is trained to maintain his mental focus when engaged. He gains a +2 to all rolls to avoid disruption of his magic.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Sm d8, AB"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.AMc8whJjmR9s4Z0b"}},"_id":"OfdhSkWCqtsk5Uuv"}
{"name":"Witch/Warlock","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"There are plenty of good witches and warlocks out there. Hopefully, this hero remains one of them.</p><p> When casting a ritual (by the time you’re a Junior you’ll know what they are), she ignores up to 2 points of Casting Modifiers. This does not apply to other participants, who still roll with the usual penalties.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.7I41rF0nxDWvauRm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OlW9BhgPhJQBEPat"}
{"name":"Banzai!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero is an expert at causing the most damage possible to other aircraft during collisions. The character causes 1d8 damage to the target per 5” of speed while he and his vehicle still suffer the usual 1d6. Passengers in the hero’s aircraft will suffer the enhanced 1d8 damage, however.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.CfUG2ztBMEDFtDGK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OmJn4Wh6tdRUnJMM"}
{"name":"Relentless","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your slayer is truly driven to defeat evil. He must seek it out wherever he suspects it lies, and brooks no interference from those he thinks bar his way.</p><p> In exchange for this dogged determination and unflinching dedication to the chase, Relentless characters who get a success to recover from being Shaken may take a single action.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.KG2YZQUCYtSpqR1z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Oo9jfcNE2cjez54y"}
{"name":"Psiforged Body","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This warforged’s body has trace amounts of psionically resonant deep crystal, providing her with increased psionic power and the ability to store psionic energy in its body. This functions as a mana stone (see Named Miscellaneous Magic in the Fantasy Companion) with 5 Power Points. A warforged with this edge is sometimes referred to as a psiforged. Special: This Edge must be taken during character creation.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.eQ13LfBjdjdwQyho"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OwwJsy3qG6URCu9T"}
{"name":"Tale-teller","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A good storyteller not only entertains, he gives hope and comfort as well. Colonists and spacers in the Way Out West can use all the hope and comfort they can find. We don’t want to say too much, but good tale- tellers are critical to saving the world.</p><p>What? The world needs saving? You bet it does. Spreading the tales of your posse’s derring-do is far more important in the grand scheme of things than the ability to fire a gun or ride a chanouk. So if you do something amazing, bucko, tell people about it!</p><p>The Marshal has the skinny on all this (see page 101), but the basics are that if you ever make a Persuasion roll to lower the local Fear Level, you add +2 to your total.</p><p>When a Tale-Teller successfully lowers the local Fear Level, he and anyone who Supports the storytelling attempt automatically earn a Conviction token (see Savage Worlds). Talk to the Marshal about this, amigo. We’ve already told you more than we should.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.YCssDnUeJo2ZN9ka"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Ozw5uKxoZifxX5P0"}
{"name":"Child Of The Draconic Prophecy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Draconic Prophecy favors the adventurer. This Edge is the Eberron name for the Destiny’s Child Edge included with the Savage Worlds Adventure Deck.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.YpCqfafctPAlOHsp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"P33eg2ktTJn4zSGO"}
{"_id":"P4W4L5UVrxrdImQa","name":"Blood And Guts","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This veteran soldier has seen so much death and bloodshed it no longer affects him. He automatically passes Fear tests caused by gore. His callous detachment also gives him a +1 damage bonus in hand-to-hand combat.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.wqCnCS6XFkZyNQOg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"P61GHpKEYcGPV9GB","name":"Improved Dig In!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Dig In!, but foes get a −2 penalty, and his Toughness bonus against Area Effect fire is +2.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.7aU9IH5aqDUFyXK5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Rich/Filthy Rich","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Although wealthy by student standards, your money comes from your parents, a trust fund, or some other source more restricted than the original Edges in Savage Worlds. Rich doubles the regular semester allowance (page 19) to $1,000. Filthy Rich triples it to $1,500.","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.HEgRBwDCqpFlMGCv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PEflf707kH0JMj22"}
{"name":"I See Dead People","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Either due to a traumatic event or spectral encounter, the character can see spirits. He ignores the invisibility effect of the ethereal Special Ability. The spirit can leave an area, but if it’s present, the hero can see it.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Aura Reader"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.wM9FW7hfeHpH7Yrc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PHdFFSxu0s3IX5tT"}
{"name":"Adapted","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Not all anouks shun technology. This Edge removes the Low Tech racial Hindrance from an anouk hero so she can operate most human technology normally.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 36","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Anouk, Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.mcTLpjluHzXTMflI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PNIegR9zDTAoJV6L"}
{"name":"Aggressive","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot puts everything they can into the fight, adding their Spirit die to onboard weapons.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Piloting d8, Shooting d8, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.PxExkYtRvgs5af6I"}},"_id":"PTlmI6L9ItUrcxOd"}
{"name":"Older Than I Look","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character has lived lifetimes, increasing his life experiences so that he adds +2 to most Common Knowledge rolls. In a pinch, he may spend a Benny to gain a temporary d4 in any normal Skill (not including Faith, Focus, Psionics, Spellcasting or Weird Science), for the duration of the scene.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Ageless"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.sZGkvFbPScCR3Tw7"}},"_id":"Pa60wnJAUHRlNtcb"}
{"name":"Techie Tinker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot is more than cable of altering and hack-rigging their vessel. The Pilot increases Handling, Toughness, or Armor by +1. This Edge may be taken once per Rank.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Repair d6, Electronics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.cFSzUUCszCTe2rVB"}},"_id":"Pb13Z2BPiKRtF9eJ"}
{"name":"Determination","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This sturdy soul carries on when others fall by the wayside. When the character takes enough wounds from an attack to be Incapacitated, he gets one free Soak roll. If the roll fails he may then spend Bennies to make Soak rolls as usual.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.e2nWxV68t24JUuAI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PcPS8wzsXoyHlCym"}
{"name":"Local Favorite","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some students were born and raised in Golan County, but this student is not only from the area but popular with the locals. He gets the best seats at hangouts in town and the locals are more willing to spill the dirt to him on at least some of the local scandals. Any randomly determined initial Reaction for an NPC local is always one level higher for this hero, and if the Dean thinks the Edge applies then predetermined Reactions may be one level higher as well. This Edge can only be taken during character creation.","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.Loqbx4UEqx2CwDnu"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PfbF4DvUTVDIT89A"}
{"name":"Jack Marshal","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have learned the intricate hand signals and voice commands to command a ‘jack efficiently without using magic. Most laborjacks, and all military ‘jacks, require complex lock codes before you can command it, and you have learned these codes for the ‘jacks you’re likely to work with (if you are in the military, this includes ‘jack codes for your country’s military, though these are changed frequently). Giving a ‘jack commands is not usually an action, but you can also attempt to direct a jack to perform better than it normally would by focusing on it. This is an action, and the ‘jack must be able to see and hear you to command it. Your hero rolls Smarts, and for each success and raise, a jack under your control can roll a Wild Die on a single trait roll on its next action. Once set to a task, a ‘jack will continue until you give it another command, or it runs out of fuel. Jack marshals can spend their bennies on behalf of a ‘jack that they control.</p><p> Finally, and perhaps most importantly, a character with the ‘Jack Marshal Edge can begin play with a light laborjack appropriate to his background.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d6+, Knowledge (mechanika) d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.jxvxV1Xzy0MnzAPU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"PgBCu3EamWfRCzNJ"}
{"_id":"PgmXbmybm2nuXVhV","name":"Hardboiled","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This bruiser is tougher than shoe leather baked in the Sahara. He adds +2 to his Toughness.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hard"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.gOxeixIvjyYrT5HQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Gut Feeling","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot knows their craft inside and out, and as such also is uncannily aware of issues or hazards. Pilot gains +2 Repair rolls.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Repair d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.p33YbAbAYLc44v2g"}},"_id":"PhNNFl1pOl0ofRZ5"}
{"name":"One Shot Left","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character will always have at least one projectile remaining for his or her ranged weapon, even after an extended combat. This might be a final bullet in a gun, arrow in a quiver, or stone in a sling. This option does not remove the need to reload weapons in a game that uses realistic ammunition rules, but rather assures that the character will not be forced to reload at a critical moment.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Shooting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.exPlVBRxvaaxujLO"}},"_id":"Pn8iw8tYKxiSd83l"}
{"name":"Elementalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Each elementalist chooses his favorite element, e.g. fire, ice, or lightning. Powers with this Trapping function as having Limitation (Element). They cost one less Power Point to cast.<p>Furthermore, the Elementalist with Living Wand does not suffer the Wandslinging penalty for powers with Trapping of his chosen element.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.y1GbiLufv51cHks0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Q1jW9OFl5NgdLhAQ"}
{"name":"Ready Rage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are a font of rage, capable of throwing yourself into a murderous frenzy. You may spend a benny to activate the Berserk edge.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Berserk"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.ulGpCWHqdYc9uepV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Q6EujG1f8cThV3hf"}
{"name":"Vermont Stump Jumpers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Vermont Stump Jumpers are a new organization,but one with much potential.</p><p>Team Members of the Vermont Stump Jumpers gain the Stubborn Hindrance, but gain Luck and Alertness edges.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Stump Jumpers"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.QZKqkJ1iBNiqxnfL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QB7NpJzykssgtRMc"}
{"name":"Veteran O’ The Way Out West","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your spacer has fought pirates in the Belt, dodged twisters in Tornado Alley, and scrapped with anouks in the Cold. There’s little in Faraway she hasn’t faced down and lived to tell about. Your character starts at Seasoned Rank, which means she has four Advances to spend immediately after character creation.</p><p>That experience doesn’t come free,however. The Faraway system has left its mark. If you take this Edge, draw a single card from the Action Deck and show it to the Marshal. There’s a table on page 105 that tells her what your character faced in the past and what effect it had on her. Here’s a free bit of advice, though—the results can be pretty harsh, anything from a lost limb to insanity or worse!","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Occult d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.BmyGqICkKSThLPkF"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QHakGYIXeONGmZbv"}
{"name":"Exceptional Individual","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Masked Crusaders are exotic individuals with a wide range of abilities akin to the pulp heroes of later generations.<p>This Edge grants a Masked Crusader any Combat Edge, regardless of Rank Requirements.All other Requirements must be met as usual. It may only be taken once (usually during character creation).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Masked Crusaders)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.ZsmOLiIPYMKmY1Qz"}},"_id":"QLqkmJ0NZ7ErNoFR"}
{"name":"Talisman Craftsman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This is a magical version of the Gadgeteer Edge. Once per game session, a character with the Talisman Edge can create a magic device and imbue it with arcane energy.</p><p> The device uses any power available to a magician or miracle worker in that setting (though this is still subject to Rank restrictions). It has half the creator’s Power Points. Once these are used up, they do not recharge. The ritual to imbue the object takes d20 minutes. Activating the device requires a Smarts (magic) or Spirit (miracles) roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Knowledge (Occult) d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.qFxzcmTkMoLStBbl"}},"_id":"QNnN3rr6rU3bLLmz"}
{"name":"Bull Rush","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero jostles his enemies harshly: “What stands up must come down” as he likes to say.</p><p>Once per round, the fighter can make a Push or Trip maneuver (see page 40) against two targets adjacent to each other. Each defender resists and is affected by the maneuver separately","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.vskzwDNzIyMQQAQH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QO42SrMvTUJAVe5Q"}
{"name":"Henchman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"No matter how tough or smart you think you are, sooner or later you’re gonna need someone to watch your back or perform a task you aren’t exactly qualified for. That’s what henchmen are for, pal! Plus, it makes you look more important when your chauffeur opens the door for you.</p><p> Your character retains the loyal service of one Follower (see Savage Worlds) per rank. Alternatively, when gaining a new rank, the player can instead decide to upgrade an existing Follower to become Resilient or a Lieutenant as per the Special Abilities. The list of potential henchmen includes, but is not limited to, harlots, goons, bodyguards, chauffeurs, lawyers or spies. They can be of different types. If they die or are dismissed, they are replaced in about a week. Henchmen are treated as Allies and can gain advances.","notes":"Wiseguys page 57","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.5ayAY3cM58Jqe8dU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QRPs9AtwXRmTAjAs"}
{"name":"Jink And Juke","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero may attempt a Piloting Test opposed by his opponent’s Smarts as a maneuver. If successful, the char- acter increase’s his aircraft’s Parry by an amount equal to the Test’s successes for one round.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Ace, Notice d8+, Piloting d12+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.90HPbvzD5INKWwDl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QdP5sQvZNlpKL5bn"}
{"name":"Fast Strike","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has learned to fight with great dexterity — moving in and striking quickly, then moving away before his opponent can react. If the character can move at least 2” before making an attack, he may strike and withdraw from combat without the target, or any other opponents, receiving a free attack. The agent is still subject to First Strike attacks from adjacent foes as normal.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 22","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Ag d8, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.fnuu1hzcdwVYBm04"}},"_id":"QdRqa1ZkBn4xiANJ"}
{"name":"Sky Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Select one maneuver with a penalty that is allowed by an aircraft. When performing this aircraft maneuver you have a +2 to your roll but only to cancel out part of or the entire penalty. This bonus cannot increase your roll beyond your normal, unmodified ability.</p><p>You cannot apply this Edge to the so-called unnamed maneuver unless an entirely new one is outright designed and named.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.zvk2iX6bvquFBNjQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QfPjBaF2lg82Zsev"}
{"name":"Wilds Runner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Increase the character’s Pace by 2” while in the wilderness. This Pace boost increases to a whopping 4” in preferred terrain if the character also possesses that Edge.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Woodsman, Spirit d8+, Survival d8+, Tracking d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.68cPCAEq101KzLb0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QfbnH9D12f95hm0k"}
{"name":"Monster Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some Rippers specialize in fighting certain types of abominations and become exceptionally adept at defeating them.<p>Pick a monster or creature type such as animals, hybrids, ghosts, vampires, lycanthropes, spellcasters, zombies, etc. The warrior is completely immune to Fear tests caused by these beings (including the fear spell if spellcasters are chosen).<p>You may take this Edge multiple times, choosing a different monster type each time it is taken.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.PhDuFq3WgMordfv5"}},"_id":"Qo6rVUP5yICipECB"}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Close fighters train to go for vital areas and weak spots for quick and lethal kills. The attacker adds a bonus to his Fighting roll equal to his enemy’s Reach +1.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.VoNNvH8DgxX0k6ge"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QtPqKeiwsbU9KXUT"}
{"name":"Night Eyes","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Although you appear human physically, your exceptional night vision borders on the supernatural, and may even be the result of a mixed bloodline in the distance past. You begin with Notice d6, and ignore all penalties for Dim and Dark lighting. This Edge must be taken during character creation.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Human, Alertness"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.3rWkPuJl0BAv0AKL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QxF3Q3hrCCTqUr7P"}
{"name":"Pugilist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Pugilists are experts at fighting without weapons. When making unarmed Fighting attacks (including natural weapons such as horns or claws), they add +1 to their Fighting rolls.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 40","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.yxKAKP7D2tYKZVAn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"R35oTml2sRnaOzQM"}
{"name":"Improved Chi","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The student becomes the master. Your hero gains another Chi point (for a total of two) to spend each encounter. The character may only ever use 1 Chi point per action. The warrior also gains additional effects to spend their Chi on are as follows: ▪ Apply AP 4 to an unarmed (or Natural Weapon) attack. ▪ Add +d6 damage to a successful Fighting or Athletics (including throwing) attacks beyond unarmed or Natural Weapon attacks. ▪ Make an enemy discard an attack against an adjacent target, then reroll it from scratch. Unspent Chi is lost at the end of the encounter.","notes":"Martial Options page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Chi"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.jp2deXDW0cuepJDV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"RPEsERtm45KydC3d"}
{"name":"Overload Metabolism","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The warforged can heal damage at a cost to his other physical attributes by exciting his warforged metabolism. Once per session, he can make a Vigor roll to repair damage. On a success, he repairs one Wound. On a raise, he repairs two Wounds. Doing this reduces his Strength and Agility by one die type for 10 minutes. If the warforged is Incapacitated and has not yet used this ability, any use of the Imbue Item Edge (i.e., Gadgeteer) targeted upon him automatically activates this Edge.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Agility d8+, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.ZyTLuHbe2PSpUBT9"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"RotyWzvDcmh3WkbV"}
{"_id":"Rue4LtFdB1CW6ltc","name":"A Few Good Men","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This leader demands the best from his troops. When the War Master checks to see which of the commander’s troops are alive or dead after a battle, any failures receive one reroll. The Edge affects up to 12 men (a typical squad), and does not stack if multiple characters have the ability. If the leader is the overall commander in a Mass Battle, roll a d6 whenever a token is lost; on a 6, the token survives.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.dQSfIFkKjHNDkyKC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Weapon Finesse","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>If this character gets a raise on her Fighting roll while usinga a light weapon, she may roll Agility (maximum of d12) instead of a d6 for the bonus damage die.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This Edge can only be used with a light, one-handed weapon, such as cutlass, hatchtet, dagger, rapier or shiv/shank.</p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Source: </strong><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">cu</span>stom</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fFC6lQJkzq1ZdFED"},"cf":{"id":"temp_09dru9b7zr1l","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Custom","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"RymLm03ziT2M6RUB"}
{"name":"Gunner’s Mate","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to anticipate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in watercraft. The character’s Fast Targets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed watercraft.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Boating d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.puWMhMLXzgpdUpDq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"S03M45AmbfBFrxxX"}
{"name":"Unarmored Body","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"To offer more versatility, House Cannith produced a line of warforged without armor like most others. Unarmored warforged do not have the Composite Plating racial ability (and its +2 Armor), but instead may wear any armor sized to fit a large human. Special: This Edge must be taken during character creation.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.1j08AAw8Li6CbmMU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"S4Jbr9vbfKpD8YYO"}
{"name":"Unarmed Combat (Basic)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent is considered armed at all times (negating the Unarmed Defender bonus) and does Str +d4 unarmed damage when attacking.<p><b>Normal:</b> A character throws a punch for Str damage and is treated as an Unarmed Defender, giving his opponents +2 to their Fighting rolls to strike him.<p><b>Example:</b> Joe has Unarmed Combat (Basic). He is now treated as armed, and with his Str d6, does d6 + d4 damage with a punch, pummel, or kick.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 25","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Fighting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.9s4LBCmKn3Gazkt5"}},"_id":"SIQLVIncvBY9ROco"}
{"name":"Conjurer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Conjurers specialize in invoking allies at their side.</p><p> Allies created or summoned by summon ally or zombie have a one die step increase in Spirit, Strength, and Vigor.</p><p> In addition, the cost of summon ally, transport (from Tomes & Prayers), and zombie is reduced by 1 Power Point.","notes":"Fantasy: Wizards and Mystics page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.gwC85uuIKk0kyrnJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"STWiIi4SSvVIIY2v"}
{"name":"Force Master","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Force is varied and wonderful, and force masters are exposed to countless tomes, powers and methods as they master their craft. Sometimes they use this knowledge to recall variations of their various powers.</p><p> A force master can spend 1 extra Power Point when casting a power to change its trapping, A fireball (blast) might manifest as a lightning bolt, for example. This can often have important consequences if a foe has a particular resistance or weakness to the power’s Trapping.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Force Use d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.j06Tp3CtyTNrVwZn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"SaAg85W7ErjcJXk5"}
{"name":"Battle Mage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The battle mage has seen many fights and learned to defend himself.</p><p> Once during his turn, he may activate a power on himself as a free action. He must be the only target of that power (no Additional Recipient or Area of Effect).","notes":"Fantasy: Wizards and Mystics page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any), Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.TFLomgEwtvHIMRXO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Sd86LSlQwjJWy0LE"}
{"name":"Fast Hands","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character may “ready” two additional items per turn (four total) as a free action. Also, you may exchange all of these free actions to ready an item from a difficult location (floor or hard to reach area).","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.nlbKNOPcFA8orwEl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"SdUY9gUTmpqRFCbi"}
{"name":"Embolden","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once per round, when an event requires one or more allies to roll Spirit or Smarts to resist a Test, power, Special Ability, or Fear check, the hero can immediately Support his allies’ rolls to resist (as a free action). This Support is generally done with Persuasion, Performance, Taunt, Intimidation, Battle, or an arcane skill (other skills are up to the GM). The hero rolls once and the result is applied to each of the affected allies","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.ixWVL4EUBPDJZ2yQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"SxQPOkWOmhm0lIb2"}
{"name":"Arcane Artisan","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once per session, an experienced Petramancer can create a jewel-adorned item with an embedded power, which he can give to someone else to use. To create the device, follow the rules for Artificer, with one significant change: unlike other Arcane Devices, items created by an Arcane Artisan do not tie up the creator’s Power Points after creation due to the mystical ability of gems and crystals to store Power Points. Such devices are very expensive and time consuming to create, however. Double the normal Arcane Device creation time. </p><p>Crafting also requires the creator to invest 5 Power Points for each Power Point that will be retained in the stone. Power Points can only be used to activate the power stored in the item and can only be replenished by a Petramancer or by leaving the device to charge in its associated element for at least one hour. </p><p>The item must be made with a stone appropriate to the power being imbued. Power Modifiers and Limitations can be added at creation but are always included in every activation. Activation works the same as other Arcane Devices. These items can also be Trapstones.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Petramancer, Artificer, Repair d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.gTVQTUVlQxp8jE7a"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7wj2fq58w9r","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"SxojPuzvHMR46aGa"}
{"name":"Survivalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your rough upbringing has taught you how to survive on your own. You can ignore two points of penalties caused by an environmental condition (heat, cold, radiation, etc.).","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival: d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.jMKXNaZnvv9Xot56"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"TFZxkbwqk9V743Ai"}
{"name":"Sonderjagdkommandos","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"SJK members gain +1 on attack and damage rolls against Vampires. They’re very good at killing Vampires.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the SJK"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.SlkR6AsWD9DZTZ1n"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"TSAL5xSLWQW30c4z"}
{"name":"Spot Weakness","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"No swordsman, whether one taught by the finest master from the mysterious east or one who developed his art on the streets of Lankhmar, is flawless. Everyone has a weakness, and this character has the training necessary to spot and exploit such a weakness. If an opponent making a Fighting attack against the character rolls a 1 on his Fighting die (regardless of Wild Die), the character receives +1 to Fighting rolls against that foe for the rest of the combat. If an opponent rolls a 1 on his Fighting die but hits the hero using his Wild Die, the character still spots the flaw. You only get the bonus once, no matter how many 1s are rolled.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Fighting d8+, Notice d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.7UZ7JvbHThm8Vr5e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"TZEWyJZicLXZOSSk"}
{"name":"Fanaticism","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge is most appropriate for members of the military, but the leader of a seasoned band of monster hunters might develop it as well.</p><p> When under this character’s command, his followers gain great courage and add +2 to their Fear checks. Optionally, the artificer can use a small Eberron shard as a source of Power Points for the arcane device instead of her own.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.XdFUXED6aenfT3JE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"TaPTZxG0iAUSdemZ"}
