{"name":"Cyber Tolerance","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are more resistant to the intrusion of augments on your body than the average person. Increase your Strain limit by +4.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.i7374iNvl7JgjmGN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Tvkq5BERHSkZT2OT"}
{"name":"Street Samurai","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Street Samurai are mercenaries with hearts of gold (not literally; golden hearts are heavy and inefficient). They aren’t as common as fiction claims, but they are trustworthy. A samurai starts with Street Cred d8 and gets a free Reroll on failures when using Street Cred.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Code of Honor or Heroic"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.eLRSaMoavk0JmDUj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"TySMaKmODbS9snRB"}
{"name":"Banzai!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero is an expert at causing the most damage possible to other aircraft during collisions. The character causes 1d8 damage to the target per 5” of speed while he and his vehicle still suffer the usual 1d6. Passengers in the hero’s aircraft will suffer the enhanced 1d8 damage, however.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.Vff8OvL7OjhlUm33"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"U479kN2m0yzp2lwA"}
{"name":"Wily","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character excels at Tricks or Tests of Will. Whenever he gets a raise and rolls on the Creative Combat Table (page 74), he can roll twice and take the result of his choice!","notes":"Flash Gordon page 41","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.suauDynblVdT97pz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"UGXUWMM2Qv1dAeVB"}
{"name":"Pathfinder","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"If a woodsman spends more time studying and looking for tracks within a confined area, the character increases their chance of a successful Tracking roll. The bonus gained depends upon the amount of extra time spent, as indicated by the following. However, the most amount of time the character may spend in this manner (and thus the highest bonus they may obtain from this Edge) is limited by the character’s Smarts:</p> <table><tr><th>TIME SPENT</th><th>TRACKING BONUS</th><th>MAXIMUM BY SMARTS</th></tr><tr><td>1 minute</td><td>+1</td><td>d4</td></tr><tr><td>2 minutes</td><td>+2</td><td>d6</td></tr><tr><td>5 minutes</td><td>+3</td><td>d8</td></tr><tr><td>15 minutes</td><td>+4</td><td>d10</td></tr><tr><td>30 minutes</td><td>+5</td><td>d12</td></tr> </table> <p>Once the requisite time is spent, the bonus obtained, and the relevant Tracking roll made, the bonus is lost unless more time is spent studying the area. The Tracking roll must be made within 1 minute of ending the period of study or the bonus is lost. Likewise, any effort spent studying the area is wasted if it undergoes terrain-altering conditions during that time, such as a rain storm or a bunch of people walking through it.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Woodsman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.pswxjJe0w11pO3hA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"UYBNirApQl14YS7r"}
{"name":"Storm Knight II","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<b>Greater Lightning Arc:</b> Your Arc Lighting attacks now deal 2d8 damage.</p><p><b>Lighting Immunity:</b> You are immune to lightning damage.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Storm Knight"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.Q0iW6M0lmKjC1Anh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"UZ86KGHAbNiL5tBw"}
