{"name":"Crowd Caller","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Sometimes what you really need is numbers on your side, and your character is able to provide. He can summon multiple identical creatures with a single casting of summon ally. This costs an additional two Power Points per additional ally, plus one for every rank of the servant beyond Novice. Each additional ally also increases the cost to maintain the Power by one.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.hd36UY7qFGcZ6DIg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v74x6k6usus","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"UhkYC2KmnYslmEIx"}
{"name":"Jedi/Sith Warrior","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Jedi/Sith face grave danger in service to the Force. To survive such hardships, they learn to channel the Force to protect themselves. They may add +1 to total of a final Soak roll for each Power Point spent, to a maximum of +4.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Jedi/Sith), Force Use d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.TLl2IwcYIrFcjs1E"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Us6UVrCXqNUpL7RR"}
{"name":"Geared Up","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge may only be taken at character creation. Your character has up to $10,000 worth of possessions each time this Edge is taken. This is a one-time only benefit—if the gear is lost, it’s lost","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.3mTIJr2EOrHJYCHk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"V7a0DQoZSVJSvnFp"}
{"name":"Aura Reader","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge allows the student to read another person’s energy—or “aura.”</p><p> To do so, the character must be within ten feet (in person—video doesn’t work) and make a Spirit roll at –2. If the roll is successful, the character knows the target’s general emotional state (happy, sad, angry, nervous, etc.) and her overall health (sick, weak, strong, etc.). With a raise, she can identify specific health conditions, such as a concussion, spirit possession, Fatigue, cancer, diabetes, etc. Failure results in a level of Fatigue and loss of the ability for 24 hours.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sophomore, Psychically Sensitive, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.BfC4aJNBFaISy4Us"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VA5uPxFTn4lPzUOz"}
{"name":"Warlock","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are a warlock, a spellcaster who has learned to channel the fury of warbeasts into himself and draw upon their power. You can bond with a warbeast that has been properly trained to respond to you. Once bonded, you have a mental link to the warbeast, allowing you to give it commands and share its senses. It’s also much more effective in everything it does, and can roll your Wild Die on any action as long as it is within your control area (1” x the sum of your Smarts and Spirit dice). You may spend your Bennies on your warbeast’s behalf. Additionally, you may push the warbeast beyond its normal limits to draw upon its magical potential. This is risky, however, and has a chance of driving the beast into a murderous frenzy.</p><p> To use this ability, choose how many Power Points you want to draw from your warbeast, to a maximum of half the warbeast’s Spirit die. You gain that many Power Points immediately (before the roll). You roll your arcane skill opposed by the warbeast’s Spirit. The warbeast gains a +1 bonus to this roll for each Power Point you gained. If the warbeast wins the opposed roll, it is Shaken. If the warbeast gets a raise on the roll, it goes berserk (as the Edge) and attacks the nearest creature on its action. To regain control of a warbeast, you must roll an opposed arcane skill check against its Spirit while it’s within your control area as an action. If you succeed, it is no longer berserk and is under your control again. Each time you reave power from a warbeast, it gains a +2 bonus on Spirit rolls to resist your control for 24 hours.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Arcane Background (any), Wild Card, may not possess the Warcaster edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.RQ4LfMwjTiGNLio9"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VESfYrw8EOiXqxZt"}
{"name":"Reactive Shifting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some shifters can activate their abilities as a reflex. Reactive Shifting allows them to begin shifting as a free action even when it's not their turn.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any), Quick"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.ZKjVDh7wqHNV8hbL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VExMJpyIqv4MhE31"}
{"name":"Symbiont Mastery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The adventurer has stronger control over attached symbionts and benefits from increased vitality from the attached symbionts. She gains a +2 bonus to Spirit rolls during any battle of wills between her and the symbiont (see Intelligent Relics in Fantasy Companion). While at least one symbiont is attached, the adventurer also gains a free reroll on Soak rolls.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 36","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.fbOYVvsvMnxlbChe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VUdAGAG4oc2VwTTz"}
{"name":"Dirty Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Honor and rules do not matter when your life is at stake.</p><p>The hero gets +2 to Test an enemy when their next action this turn (taking Multi-Actions) is to attack that same enemy","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.lYTQUdEesMkTcCd7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VZFStKRUOTCbXGaq"}
{"_id":"VbG8t8x7XWdGz8Sm","name":"Grizzled","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character is a veteran. Early in the war it means he saw service in colonial wars before 1914; later on it means he’s managed to survive the carnage on the front. A Grizzled character begins play as Seasoned, and his military grade is two levels higher than normal.</p><p>Grizzled soldiers get four Advances during character creation, as if they had earned 20 Experience Points in play, but there is a price. The character has to “pay off” these bonus Advances with earned experience, so the first 20 Experience Points earned must go for that.</p><p>An Enlisted character with the Grizzled edge begins with rank E-3; a Grizzled character with Rank (NCO) begins as E-7. Those with Rank (Officer) begin as an O-3. See the Rank Tables for grades and titles depending on nationality and service branch.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"21"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.0gnGdtezlqdMIU0N"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"King Of The Road","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero gains one Driving re-roll per game session without spending a benny.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Ace, Professional Driving"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.rwnvBg4uH77pScTe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VcBafIjmkGG4R3Q1"}
{"name":"Cleaner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character was trained to clean up crime scenes and knows forensics methods used by law enforcement during criminal investigations.</p><p> The cleaner can roll Healing with a +2 bonus to clean up a crime scene using only household products and can complete the clean-up in half the time. She can also use Healing instead of Notice or Survival to find and follow clues from a crime scene.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Healing d8+, Notice d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.ajlV1yAQ0V1O40jq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VhmqrMMMoEkXmHj2"}
{"name":"Grizzled","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent’s field work has made him tough — even his scars have scars. He gains +2 to Soak rolls.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 23","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Sp d8, V d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.5Bgc0TP4wIqoaTop"}},"_id":"VpusUgynpjo4noPj"}
{"name":"Artful Dodger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This villain was raised to a life of crime from an early age. Tutored by a master thief, this fellow is no stranger to the ways of the street. He begins play with Stealth d6 and Streetwise d6, and at Seasoned rank he can take the Urban Ranger Edge, even if he doesn’t meet its requirements (this still costs an advance). This Edge can only be taken during character creation.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, A d8, Sm d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.bGYaKvG2FUsvaHhN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"W8TRJuPTeciVP9iX"}
{"name":"Quick Draw","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You draw two additional cards when spending a Benny for an Action Card at the beginning of a round instead of one. You may choose your final Action Card from any of your available choices, including additional draws from Level Headed, Quick, etc.</p><p>You also add +2 to Athletics rolls made to interrupt others’ actions (including resisting being interrupted).","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.pn0u7KhFTCYzY3CT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"WC5IUfHlaiQEskuz"}
{"name":"VR Immersion Training","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has been implanted with a neurological data link and may take any one non-Weird Edge for which he normally qualifies. This Edge may be reassigned at the beginning of each new mission.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Improved Data Chips or Improved Skill Chip"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.OcjnS0Yv6NdL6kVD"}},"_id":"WE1o6Vn6hwMvGXKA"}
