{"name":"Ruin Rat","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is an expert at sifting through the ruins of fallen cities and abandoned buildings for items of value. Ruin Rats get +2 to their Survival rolls while scavenging, and can pick through an area in half the time of a standard scavenging attempt (see Scavenging on page 17).","notes":"The Last Parsec - Irongate","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.pAfSJ4zG1V00wHDh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"WXVVJUnG6TEmgCXJ"}
{"name":"Mobile Defense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your supple movements and agile footwork make it difficult for your foes to land a solid blow in combat. When making a Soak roll, you may use your Agility (to a maximum of d12) for the Wild Die, as long as you weren’t caught unaware. You also receive a +1 bonus to Parry when using the Defend maneuver, which stacks with the normal +2 bonus granted by Defend, as long as you move at least 1” before declaring the maneuver.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"WC, S, Ag d8, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.KU3DXTKIVdgB0ljl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"WjjyplbJ49OTxPhs"}
{"name":"Miracle Worker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can jury-rig damaged systems during combat, using a Repair roll at double the ship's current wound penalties (e.g., –4 for two wounds). For each success and raise, you repair one wound or critical hit of your choice. Once combat is over, all wounds are re-applied as your improvised fixes collapse. Note that this cannot destroy the ship; ignore all wounds after your ship's maximum (usually 3).","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Knowledge (Engineering) d8; Repair d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.cAGZSjmzaCaE29Al"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"WngsU7Y4WPH5XbZf"}
{"name":"Jack Mechanic","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A good mechanic can keep a jack functional in even the worst conditions. Your hero can make a Repair roll while adjacent to a Shaken or wounded jack as an action, with a penalty equal to the ‘jacks current number of Wounds. If successful, choose one of the following effects: </p><p>1. The ‘jack is no longer Shaken. </p><p>2. Remove one Wound from the ‘jack. </p><p>3. Remove the effects of one damaged system (see the ‘jack injury rules). </p><p>On a Raise, you may choose twice from the list. Further Raises have no effect.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d8+, Repair d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.9SaYxMvdBMjIuCDA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"WugjPGRUpF02E2eE"}
{"name":"Urban Ranger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You know how to live off the streets, and are able to navigate the alleys and sewers of the city with ease. You gain a +2 bonus to Stealth and Survival rolls, although only within urban environments.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d6, Stealth d8, Streetwise"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.ZK4vZBnYNsrECv0y"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"X0iJnPaEhXN385WG"}
{"name":"Hostage Taker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When the lead starts flying, and a wise guy’s in a tight spot, it’s good to have someone else take a bullet for him. One hand must be free to secure the hostage. Anyone attempting to shoot the Hostage Taker while he’s holding a hostage must use the Innocent Bystander rule (any missed shot with a roll of 1 on the trait die hits the hostage). Furthermore, if the Hostage Taker gets hit with an attack which causes enough damage to Wound him, he can spend a Benny to substitute his hostage as the recipient of the damage instead. Most hostages won't try to fight back or escape; the gangster can grab them and drag them around.","notes":"Wiseguys page 53","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Intimidation d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.0Rxam56eFdFylss9"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"X3PKqQGcxqQskwFu"}
{"name":"Song of St. George","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The beautiful aria known as the Song of St. George soothes nearby allies and bolsters their courage.<p>As an action, the Ripper with this Edge may sing a few lines from the Song of St. George. All allies within 10” (20 yards) immediately get a Spirit roll as a free action to recover from being Shaken.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Order of St. George)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.BBUndBMxujBfiiL6"}},"_id":"X6pNb6ub4tQ9EAqd"}
{"name":"Royal Forester","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Until recently, Royal Foresters were an elite, Arborian-only extension of the kingdom guard. With the rise of the Freemen and the appearance of Flash Gordon and his allies, the order began to accept others into the fold.</p><p>Those with this Edge have undergone rigorous training and ignore Difficult Ground when moving through the normal flora of forests and jungles (mud pits and the like still restrict movement).","notes":"Flash Gordon page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Athletics d6+, Survival d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.6aCgZGiaRlisWesT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"XBM7sAMf4GFLwMiz"}
{"name":"Living Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This natural caster is able to benefit from Power Edges and Modifications without the use of a wand. Even for him, it is not an easy task. Whenever he uses a Modifier or the Wizard, Artificer or Healer Edge (provided he has them) without a wand, he suffers a –1 penalty to his Wandslinging roll.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.ht4KdsVO0m1aoeNw"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"XGlAcnAo65qDPeF7"}
