{"_id":"YIBjGRnMncSRojvt","name":"Hard","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Maybe it’s willpower. Maybe it’s muscle density. Or maybe your hero’s just one tough bastard. Either way, he adds +1 to his Toughness.","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.8HHitbF9GKFihVA0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Shifter Savagery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Shifters from the wilds sometimes tap into their barbaric and animalistic natures concurrently. While shifting and going Berserk simultaneously, the Berserk shifter adds +1d6 to the damage dealt by his natural weapons.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Shifter (Longtooth, Gorebrute, or Razorclaw), Berserk"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.iDiuRbV5hL8TLBuS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YIINIqGIx36NQy3K"}
{"name":"Wilderness Man","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Whether a Kossite born in the heights of the Scharde Mountains or an Idrian nomad, people across the Iron Kingdoms must make their way in the wild areas of the world.</p><p> Your hero is at home in the wilds, and gains a +2 bonus to Survival rolls in the wilderness. In addition, you gain a +2 bonus to Vigor rolls made to resist natural hazards or the rigors of travel.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Vigor d6+, Survival d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.9Z2aCUmlZaFIOqeh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YOnmI05lnsR7Hfus"}
{"name":"Pack Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have a natural talent for turning overwhelming force into overwhelming damage. You add half your gang-up bonus (round down) to damage for melee attacks.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.CsEWO3F0gty8WlYG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YStOiJTqJZWCW7kV"}
{"name":"Religious Fury","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When fighting supernatural creatures, slayers with this Edge are overcome by a fervent wrath. Some evidence their emotions as ferocious rage while others seethe with cold anger.<p>The slayer adds +1 to all Strength-based damage rolls versus supernaturally evil creatures. She has also learned how to transform her pain into power, adding an additional +1 bonus for each wound level she’s sustained.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Slayers)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.UjaQiEzss6fxsZlS"}},"_id":"YTv0950q0k5czKfs"}
{"name":"Miracle Worker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"People don’t die on your watch. You won’t let them. Call it strength of will, exceptional skill, or just plain stubbornness, but you have a knack for resuscitating the dead. You can revive a person who has died by making a Healing roll at a −1 penalty for every minute that has passed since the character died (max 5 minutes). Each attempt takes a minute.</p><p>Characters that are revived are considered to be Stable (and have three Wounds) but have three levels of Fatigue (as per Savage Worlds core rules) that recovers one level per day. A raise removes one level of Fatigue.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d10+, Healing d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.mmOjztBUSXZs0Yl1"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Ya6auYTLBNcPyxa2"}
{"name":"Iron Body","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Glancing blows merely slide off your hero. The character gains the Hardy, so that a second Shaken result in combat does not cause a Wound.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d10+, Iron Jaw"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.nhZkC3rccdLoV9WC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YnhCbdb11xiqZfJN"}
{"name":"Starfleet Commander","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your training, experience, and instincts have paid off: under your command, your ship is a well-functioning machine that proudly goes where no one has gone before. Crews who serve you add +2 to their Knowledge (Starship Operations), Knowledge (Engineering), Piloting, Tracking, and Stealth rolls while aboardship. Does not apply to the ship’s AI.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Smarts d8; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d8; Diplomacy or Intimidation d8; Command; must be sole captain of the vessel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.tbXZlJbDn7mc85fY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YwibU3b3OWBpKiBv"}
{"name":"Improved Evasive Maneuvers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Evasive Maneuvers, but attackers subtract 2 from their attack rolls, and when you flee combat the length of the Chase is reduced by 2 rounds.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Evasive Maneuvers"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.OYOIyHXfwAj5YXs3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"YwqUgptAPLFKI86n"}
{"name":"Monster Slayer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Now your Ripper is a true scourge of the Cabal. Every time he defeats a monster specified by the Monster Hunter Edge, he receives a Benny! The limit is for each encounter: he may receive a number of Bennies from this Edge equal to his Reason. (Of course he may earn Bennies for roleplaying and the like normally.)<p>The whirlwind of death and destiny may take this Edge multiple times, once for each time he has taken the matching Monster Hunter Edge.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Monster Hunter"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.P5yILHnQVWxozNd5"}},"_id":"Z1bmyhmVnGIVs6i0"}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to nonlethal damage, and the effects of fatigue and exhaustion are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any fatigue or exhaustion effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Beasthide, Truedive, or Wildhunt)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.BxDt4V7C5rNnE4rq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Z58PuQYwAIFzGNgL"}
{"name":"Portable Armory","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character will always have easy access to any weapon required for a particular task, including illegal weapons and accessories not available to the general public. The actual weapons and accessories must still be acquired, but remarkably, the character can access them whenever he needs them instead of being forced to return to where they are normally stored. Characters with Portable Armory may also make field modifications on their weapons, switching options such as telescopic sights or specialised ammo in a single round. For every piece of gear beyond your starting list, you may make a Spirit check (Bennies apply to this roll) against a Target Number assigned by the Game Master. If the check succeeds you are able to own that piece of equipment.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.97TMg7EexkHmui4N"}},"_id":"ZC5nXOhM6IPCZms8"}
{"name":"Albino Sorcerer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This functions as the Wizard Professional Edge, allowing an albino trollkin to reduce the cost of a spell cast by 1 for each Raise on the initial casting roll. Albino trollkin are expected to be spiritual leaders of their people, which may incur social responsibilities like a Vow, and will probably create expectations in other trollkin your hero meets. This edge must be chosen at character creation.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Arcane Background, Trollkin race, Smarts or Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.IYP4JPdO6MOboNbN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZFXktLKfJxxxTctu"}
{"name":"Guts","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This lady has stared the things that lurk in the dark in the face and learned to control her fear. She ignores two points of Fear penalties for both her Spirit roll and any Fright Table result.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Sp d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.ycpXQddJtpY4skQ0"}},"_id":"ZLNBImI4XGd19TRi"}
{"name":"Jedi Master/Sith Lord","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While you have a Lightsaber readied. If a ranged attack fails to beat your parry you may redirect the attack at any target within 6’ of you. This does not apply to area attacks.</p><p> You may throw your Lightsaber as a Single/Multi action. A number of inches in any direction (You may change directions at any time) equal to your Force Use die and then recall your saber back to your hand. Making one Melee attack against up to 3 targets that you can see anywhere along the way. Each target you attack uses one of your actions.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Jedi Knight/Sith Knight, Improved Trademark Weapon (Lightsaber)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.7rJGhTrrWvoqJBab"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZOEsRTc4QJrWA2UH"}
{"name":"Escape Artist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This master of escapology is adept at removing handcuffs from herself, escaping from being tied up, and even slipping out of a straightjacket. She can also squeeze through small openings, although this is relative to her size, and at the Don's discretion; a character with the Small or Young Hindrance can fit through a smaller opening than someone with the Brawny Edge or Obese Hindrance.</p><p> The Escape Artist receives a +2 bonus to all Athletics rolls when trying to escape or squeeze through small openings, and furthermore, she may squeeze through tight spaces at her full normal Pace (though she may not run in such confining circumstances). She also receives a +2 bonus on Thievery attempts to remove handcuffs or escape from restraints.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Athletics d6+, Thievery d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.2p3cwKbNsxfhztbz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZPW2XGTcQTP6tKTh"}
{"name":"Rocket Jock","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The pilot can fire one weapon system per action without incurring a multi- action penalty while Piloting or Driving a land vehicle, or aircraft.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.ljQZ5wuSwXD0GIH1"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZTt5KlB2A6c4ntfS"}
{"name":"Ride It Out","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While in a ground vehicle the hero may spend a benny when called upon to roll on the Out of Control or vehicle Critical Hits tables. On the former, the benny reduces the result by one category, whereas for the latter it allows the character to shift the category up or down one category, as desired. The benny is spent after the appropriate roll is made on the respective table.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ace, Road Maneuver, Agility d8+, Driving d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.FdjmNOzYD4orUzhV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZgHgHj21TSP77fwF"}
{"name":"Master Assassin","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The +2 damage bonus from Assassin now applies whenever you attack a foe against whom you have Surprise, the Drop, or a Gang Up bonus. Furthermore, you also receive a +2 bonus to Knowledge (Poison) rolls.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Assassin, Knowledge (Poison) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.YvJVNnnmqDHgKX8E"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ZhuwSxHvDkheESmn"}
{"name":"Gumshoe","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have an instinct for spotting the clues others overlook. If you fail to spot a clue the Investigation skill would otherwise normally reveal—due to a failed roll or the player’s inattention—the Gamemaster makes a secret Spirit roll for you. The Gamemaster may apply a modifier based on how obscure or veiled the clue is. Success results in the Gamemaster informing you that “something seems amiss,” “you feel like you’ve overlooked something,” or the like. You are then allowed to make an initial or additional Investigation roll to identify the overlooked clue.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Investigator, Spirit d8+, Investigation d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.k3VOFitbJrUiOShQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Zp2Yn5xUdDEqiIRD"}
{"_id":"ZtDkgBCBAq3FNQIc","name":"Incoming!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Soldiers on the front get very good at distinguishing between the sound of shells passing by overhead and the deadly sound of an approaching round. When a character with this Edge is in an artillery attack, he can get prone before the shell hits, reducing damage from the attack by 2. This is cumulative with Dig In!","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"23"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.SGAD4z8O0eqSFqFE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Keep It Afloat","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While in a waterborne vehicle the hero may spend a benny when called upon to roll on the Out of Control or vehicle Critical Hits tables. On the former, the benny reduces the result by one category, whereas for the latter it allows the character to shift the category up or down one category, as desired. The benny is spent after the appropriate roll is made on the respective table.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ace, Wave Maneuver, Agility d8+, Boating d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.SelNBJS6lAQiU0Fj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"a4UGZHZKxdEnfEzw"}
{"name":"Grim Fatalism","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Old Worlders come from a grim, superstitious, and fatalistic land. Even children know most of the legends concerning vampires and werewolves— add +2 to Knowledge (Occult) rolls concerning such creatures.<p>More importantly, Old Worlders’ fatalism steels their mind against the abominations that stalk the tall crags and dark forests of their homes. When an Old Worlder with this Edge is Panicked or Paralyzed by fear (see the Fright Table on page 31), he ignores any movement limitations or requirements. He treats both results simply as Shaken instead.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Old Worlders)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.hnBUccEqWG8Y7rPJ"}},"_id":"a689gcyLHYW98Apm"}
{"name":"Sound Mind","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This investigator has learned to cope with the terrors he must face and the dark things that lurk in his world. Increase his Sanity by +2.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.yfmD2r0KworOzXnp"}},"_id":"aMuuhRFTDTG3etIy"}
{"name":"Danger Sense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge from Savage Worlds gains Psychically Sensitive as a requirement. The +2 bonus from Psychically Sensitive applies to the Notice roll for Danger Sense (negating the normal –2 penalty) if the danger is from a supernatural creature or source.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Psychically Sensitive"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.ffwTjmSX4quX8Rtp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"aSDlozQBSDcs0qVx"}
{"name":"Sector Cop","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Sector cops blend training and experience in getting instant compliance from anyone that hears them use ‘cop voice’. This Edge has three effects.</p><p>First, a Critical Failure never makes the target immune to this Sector Cop’s Intimidation. Second, a success on the opposed roll when using Intimidation out of combat works like a raise; the target backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills their guts, or flees with all haste depending on the situation. Third, a success when using Taunt out of combat works like a raise; the victim is cowed for the scene, departs obviously distraught, or attacks recklessly at the GM’s discretion.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Intimidation d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.moGd3vU36ICbIcsc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"aYLMXPlPnw3TlWAV"}
