{"name":"Cutter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have broad familiarity of exploits common to all Intrusion Defense Systems and use that knowledge to great effect. You may ignore 2 points of penalties—or gain a +1 bonus if there are no penalties—to Hacking rolls when attempting to gain access to a computer system. This bonus does not apply after you have accessed the system.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Hacking d8+, Hacker"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.OTfRNw603WRihME4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ajzZgqNdoSluhcOI"}
{"name":"Crystal Sensitivity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is attuned to the strange energy found within power crystals. This happens to miners who dig for the strange gems, and the Blue Magic Men of Kira who consume them!</p><p>Such individuals can detect energized sapphires within a range equal to their Smarts (a highly desirable talent for crystal miners). They can also estimate how much charge remains in a crystal (“half” or “a quarter,” etc.) and recharge them through touch. Recharging a crystal causes a level of Fatigue and refills 1d6 charges/power points or a quarter power (whichever is less) as an action. Such Fatigue can Incapacitate but not kill and each level can only be recovered after four hours of rest.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.GxezkoyIIBjWOQPZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"avNUzD7Io6nPJHJc"}
{"name":"Sage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Not only did this senior pay attention in class, he actually retained it—and most everything else he’s ever seen, read, or heard about.</p><p> The sage adds +2 to Investigation rolls and can make an Investigation roll without any source material (other than his memory) at a –2 penalty.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Smarts d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.QdHPnqLCt2HjE3OK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"b01cYZUEm6bdpPaG"}
{"_id":"b3YpURK52yEpg4FB","name":"Band Of Brothers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This group of soldiers has been to Hell and back together. That kind of bond hardens men, and makes them able to better withstand wounds that might otherwise put them out of action. Gain +1 Toughness for each other “brother” with this ability within 6”, to a maximum of +4. If four heroes with the Band of Brothers Edge fight together, for instance, they each gain +3 Toughness.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.Waaf8cQT8w5Z2Qj8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Cleaner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You know how to hide information as well as uncover it. You may make the appropriate roll to hide or obliterate evidence. Others coming behind you must make an opposed roll to uncover any trace of your presence. The agent receives an additional +1 to Investigation, Streetwise, and Notice rolls when searching through or obfuscating information. This stacks with the Investigator Edge.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Investigator"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.EXCDQpR9vTSuvfib"}},"_id":"bBuNRhChYu38wksf"}
{"name":"Brutal","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character with this Edge is more dangerous when roughed up. When determining melee damage, he adds his wound level to the roll. A hero with 3 wounds, for instance, adds +3 to his Fighting damage rolls","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.rctDeyzTKKOWR40m"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bE3mvAFnsux4WspS"}
{"name":"Carolingian Security Associates","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the CSA gain the Elan edge, and can always easily acquire silver bullets.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the CSA"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.SIRAY1eEQCzlipm8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bJSI7AqrSfvNhDf0"}
{"name":"Hit And Run","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero knows how to keep a steady aim despite moving.</p><p>He always ignores the penalty for Running on all of his actions.</p><p>And, once during a turn in which he moves and fires, he can reroll one Shooting or Athletics (throwing) roll","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Steady Hands, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.SA6TFEwcq8TT8Ghr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bT9UNtZUcGM0isfr"}
{"name":"Slip And Swish","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero may attempt a Boating Test opposed by his opponent’s Smarts as a maneuver. If successful, the character increase’s his watercraft’s Parry by an amount equal to the Test’s successes for one round.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Ace, Boating d12+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.pMMXpjoCOosMRxid"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bZYjgAg8BIvxe2Vl"}
{"name":"Power Mastery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has learned to control one of his powers and gains +2 to skill (or attribute) rolls with the chosen power. This Edge may be taken once per Rank, with the agent selecting a new power each time.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 27","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB or Innate Power"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.Dhh0S2Y8JQV6hJ57"}},"_id":"bj12xqEFWp6A6Mop"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Arcane Skill: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Herbalism (Smarts)<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Power Points: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Special<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Starting Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">3<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Powers Available: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Beast friend</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">blast</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">blind</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">boost/lower Trait</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">confusion</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">darksight</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">detect arcana</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">entangle</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">farsight</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">fear</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">healing</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">light/ darkness</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">mind wipe</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">protection</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">puppet</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">relief</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">sloth/speed</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">slumber</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">stun</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">wall walker</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Herbal alchemists are able to harvest ingredients from the natural environment&mdash; whether from flora or fauna&mdash;to create concoctions in the form of potions, poultices, ointments, edibles, and other alchemical products. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Herbal alchemists do not have their own reserve of Power Points like characters with other Arcane Backgrounds. Instead, they collect Power Points through components foraged using the Survival skill. Once per day, the herbal alchemist can make a Survival roll to forage for components.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Each success and raise provides 5 Power Points worth of components. On a Critical Failure, the herbal alchemist somehow loses, ruins, or is forced to use components worth 1d4 Power Points. There is no limit to the amount of Power Points an herbal alchemist can collect over time. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">An herbal alchemist can spend 3 Power Points worth of components to create an individual concoction. This concoction must be a power whose effect, including modifiers and limitations, has a Power Point cost of 3 or lower. Creating a concoction takes one entire turn, during which the herbal alchemist can do nothing else but make an Herbalism roll to create the concoction. On failure, the concoction is ruined and the Power Points are lost. On a critical failure, the normal rules for Backlash apply. When the item is created, the effect is fixed, including the effects from a Raise on the Herbalism roll. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Concoctions activate automatically when used. If a concoction requires a skill roll such as Athletics (Throwing) to use, the character must still roll that </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">skill.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\"> Of the Power Edges presented in the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">core rules, this Arcane Background only satisfies the requirements for Channeling, Concentration, </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">and New Powers.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O6dC4CF0V5Cc7lfD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2ppcwdakcbx","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bjifWEOvTwLRtR8j"}
{"name":"Power Trap","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has learned to create magical triggers that activate a power when another creature moves through an area, reads a magical rune, or otherwise triggers the trap. Common triggers are movement, creature type, anyone who doesn’t say a passphrase, anyone not wearing a certain symbol, or other clear circumstances based on sensory information. When the trap is triggered, it casts a Power that your hero knows against the triggering creature or centered on itself, rolling the caster’s arcane skill as normal. All the choices for this Power are set when the trap is created, and any Power Points are spent. The caster doesn’t get these Power Points back until the trap is either triggered or deactivated. Power traps can be disarmed using the caster’s arcane skill opposed by the disarmer’s Occult or Thievery skill (whichever is worse) with a penalty equal to the Rank of the Power; the trap’s creator can do this automatically.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Occult d8+, Spellcasting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.OdZrswdWzK6mAHXg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v74x6k6usus","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bjyPBX8fVm83Qyan"}
{"name":"Relentless","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your slayer is truly driven to defeat evil. He must seek it out wherever he suspects it lies, and brooks no interference from those he thinks bar his way.</p><p> In exchange for this dogged determination and unflinching dedication to the chase, Relentless characters who get a success to recover from being Shaken may take a single action.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 5","notes":"Horror Companion, page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.lw4h4qJRQZ5lPK1X"}},"_id":"bkzCoGCdyra3WK89"}
{"name":"Silent Kill","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This agent has been trained in the art of stealth assassination. Whenever he successfully kills an enemy unnoticed in a single round, he may attempt one of two actions: He may pin the body in place with a Smarts roll or make a Stealth roll to catch the body and quietly move and/or hide it with the remainder of his movement. Either choice is a free action.<p><b>Example:</b> Agent Suzuki, creeping along the rooftop of a mafia safe house, drops down upon a sentry and kills him in one blow. He may then make a Stealth roll to catch the body and move it under the bushes before being spotted. With a success, the other guard at the end of the garden path may never suspect a thing.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 24","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Unarmed Combat (Advanced)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.5ZNjE2Pq6CV85qkr"}},"_id":"bpFgkpXzWvvMNXYe"}
{"name":"Chosen","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The powers of good appreciate someone who stands up for what’s right, even when it’s hard. Sometimes they even pitch in and reward you for it.</p><p> When the character spends a Benny to re-roll a Trait test, he can re-roll twice and take the best of all the results.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.NTDvdbbr9XFg1a4y"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"c6z4kJCugf8Qrbso"}
{"name":"Cavalier","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your prowess on a mount is unrivaled. The mounted character act as if you have the Ace edge for purposes of Soaking Wounds (using your Riding) and negating penalties to control or maneuver your mount. They may use their Riding in place of Athletics to oppose weapons set against a charge. Also, your hero only needs to make a Riding check to see if you fall if you or your mount are rendered Incapacitated (barring outright attempts to trip your mount or dislodge you for the mount). Note: Use the Steady Hands edge to negate penalties for ranged attacks while riding.","notes":"Martial Options page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Riding d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.jrNJ9cUeK1pYCmSL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"cNLqKPAsHAKxEqZd"}
{"name":"Cardassian Memory Training","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"It's a misconception that Cardassians naturally have a photographic memory; in fact, it results from a school system that used classified techniques to discipline its students' minds. Since the government's collapse, these techniques have become public.</p><p>Once per session, you may \"remember\" everything that could reasonably be known about an NPC, including gossip, prior chance encounters, and classified records you have access to. This may allow you to befriend or pressure the person more easily.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Smarts d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.xTmIaQSfp9xrRHv2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"cb0TWLIquxuxbs79"}
{"name":"Engineer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent adds +2 to Repair rolls. With a raise, he halves the time normally required to fix something. This means if a particular Repair job can be accomplished in half the time with a raise, an engineer could finish the job in one-fourth the time.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d6, Repair d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.efFHlkPEEhhbIFGu"}},"_id":"chVBRZcZBwzlGWWy"}
{"name":"Glide It In","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While in an airborne vehicle the hero may spend a benny when called upon to roll on the Out of Control, Altitude Change, or vehicle Critical Hits tables. On the former, the benny reduces the result by one category, whereas for the latter two tables it allows the character to shift the category up or down one category, as desired. The benny is spent after the appropriate roll is made on the respective table.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ace, Sky Maneuver, Agility d8+, Piloting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.m47J73m3Jzcipx3n"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"crLXLtrXRsisW8zw"}
{"name":"Diviner Defense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Able to see flashes of the future, a diviner may react to dangerous situations and activate defensive powers any time during combat.<p>He adds the following Modifier to <i>arcane protection, deflection, conceal arcana, environmental protection, intangibility, invisibility, darkness, protection,</i> and <i>eleport</i>.<p><b>Always Ready (+2):</b> The caster may use this power defensively at any time outside his turn as if he was on Hold (unless he is Shaken or Stunned). If it is necessary to interrupt an opponent’s action, he gains a +2 bonus to the opposed Athletics roll. The caster does not gain an extra turn, only one action to cast this power. This Modifier (regardless of the power) may be used only once per round.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.R1drpCvaH2k4wHlh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cul0097oeo7","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"czNHS4BuKwXpz1c9"}
{"name":"King Of The Sea","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero gains one Boating re-roll per game session without spending a benny.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Ace, Professional Boating"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.U9BUe935URi8wlma"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"d2NPjdtDywFqZZPq"}
{"name":"Occultist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Knowledge is power, and occasionally the path to madness. The Occultist begins the game with Forbidden Lore (see page 25). The player may choose what it pertains to. Broad subjects such as “monsters” lead to suitably broad benefits but lack of specifics when it comes to information. More specific lore, such as “vampires” should yield appropriate levels of details.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 7","notes":"Horror Companion, page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Investigation d8+, Knowledge (Occult) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.WsRjAGf6EjOHOuL0"}},"_id":"dCGpDuFiDZmvORJf"}
{"name":"Wired Right","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot tweaked the craft to their standards and increases Handling by +1. This Edge may only be taken once.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.9siE3WSZx2VQEWed"}},"_id":"dE4ZpY5bnhDayLzI"}
{"name":"Ambusher","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Hiding in wait is this thief’s bread and butter. When he has the opportunity to identify a victim’s route and plan in advance, the ambusher’s group receives significant benefits in combat.<p>Victims of the planned ambush must make Notice rolls. Those who fail get no card in the first two rounds of combat. Those who succeed get no card in the first round of combat, but are dealt in as usual on the second round. Only those who succeed with a raise are dealt in as usual on both rounds.<p>Note that a victim with Danger Sense can still roll to sense the ambush as normal.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, St d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.UswUyaQ6UJlzW5tw"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dONmXF3M3YgRSi6c"}
{"name":"Essential Gear","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"To the untrained eye, the mundane item at the bottom of the kit bag is a roll of duct tape, a bullwhip, a Swiss Army Knife or an old tobacco tin packed with hair clips, thumb tacks, buttons and random nuts and bolts. To the agent, this little piece of Essential Gear has helped him out of many scrapes.<p>Through inventive use, usually not the intended purpose, Essential Gear gives +1 to a Trait roll to get an agent out of a desperate fix.<p>To gain the bonus, the player tells the GM exactly how the Essential Gear is helping, and the GM must allow its use.<p>The player should write a Trapping stating what the piece of essential equipment is. This Edge applies to one piece of equipment only, it cannot be a weapon, but could be something such as a Swiss Army Knife. Essential Gear may be taken multiple times.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Secret Files of Section D, page 8","notes":"Secret Files of Section D, page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Trapping"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6uwu6resjqd","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Section D","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.U0gAVYtJTjVbk9YH"}},"_id":"dUnbyAHRZpRS2htv"}
{"name":"Warcaster","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are a warcaster, a rare and powerful talent that allows a trained spellcaster to bond with mechanika, allowing them to channel their power through potent weapons and to mentally bond with the cortex of a steamjack. Warcasters are rare and valuable, turning a relatively unwieldy weapon of war into a deadly juggernaut of destruction on the battlefield.</p><p> A warcaster can only use this bond over a fairly limited distance, known as his control area (1” x the sum of his Smarts and Spirit dice). While within this distance, a warcaster can share the senses of his bonded jack at any time, allowing him to see through it. While within this area, your warjack can roll your Wild Die on its actions, and you can freely share Bennies with your warjack.</p><p> Additionally, if you are bonded to a piece of mechanika with a bond plate, you can roll your arcane skill to activate that device, possibly allowing you to get a Raise on a mechanika power, and can spend your Power Points to activate powers from it.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Arcane Background (any), Wild Card, may not possess the Warlock edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.ifETlaWlr2idOwEa"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dVwIYfRTWOwiWTPn"}
{"name":"Combat Sense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero has the perception, skill, and agility to handle multiple foes. Opponents halve any Gang Up bonuses against him (round down).","notes":"Flash Gordon page 40","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.xSeep2W4tzksgIq6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ddWTcDSE1E3XjfzZ"}
{"name":"Shifter Ferocity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A shifter with this Edge continues to fight without penalty if he is Shaken. Additionally, further Shaken results do not cause a Wound.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 30","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shifter (any), Hard to Kill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.5HW0QUJH62GzIVAE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dfYme5DEIBGBjL7D"}
{"name":"Improved Data Chips","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The refined chips replace the previous ones and store more data. The agent gains an additional 2 defining interest slots, for a total of 4.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Data Chips"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.YGHWQkdupwmMFLm5"}},"_id":"dfqJNC8zkvt7QQD8"}
{"name":"Rocket Jock","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The pilot can fire one weapon system per action without incurring a multi-action penalty while Piloting or Driving a vehicle, aircraft, or starship.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8, Shooting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.Cv2D3ggLPI5VAAel"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dg4HezCnmK8LSmjf"}
{"name":"Healing Factor","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"After the shifter’s current period of shifting ends, she may immediately make a free Soak roll to remove any Wounds taken while shifted.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shifter, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.6KB6bvvBkAO5iUZg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dhrZ4mdkdwaTnO0r"}
{"name":"Fanaticism","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge is most appropriate for members of the military, but the leader of a seasoned band of monster hunters might develop it as well.</p><p> When under this character’s command, his followers gain great courage and add +2 to their Fear checks.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 5","notes":"Horror Companion, page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.XGV5OrfeEC3XKRPy"}},"_id":"e2k2Qlj2OcTzWKBz"}
{"name":"Companion","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Whether he has great charisma, a magic attunement of some sort, received a family heritage or built it himself, your character is strongly tied to a Companion.<p>The Companion and your character are both Loyal (like the Hindrance) to each other. While they are close and usually work together, the Companion can have its own goal and agenda. It gladly helps its master whenever it can, but also follows its instinct, especially when survival is at stake.<p>Create a Companion (see Making Companions, page 8). The Companion does not talk or talks in a language nobody can understand. It doesn’t understand its master or other people either. If the Companion dies, it will come back or be replaced within a few days or weeks.<p>In addition to the Companion, choose one Companion Boons, based on the nature of the relationship between the master and its Companion.","notes":"Fantasy: Companions and Familiars page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.6SYricoZcCITo3xW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"e8mjIqpAUt3rq9GU"}
{"name":"Fearsome Reputation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Perhaps you’re a cold-blooded killer, or a ruthless crime lord, or maybe you just have powerful friends. Whatever the reason, you’ve earned a reputation as the sort of person who shouldn’t be crossed - merchants rarely cheat you, other thieves try to avoid offending you, witnesses are often too scared to testify against you, and even some members of the watch will occasionally turn a blind eye rather than risk facing your wrath. Your fearsome reputation also grants you a +2 bonus to Intimidation rolls, and if someone tries to intimidate you and fails, you can make an immediate Intimidation roll against them (this does not count as an action).","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Intimidation d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.HWaAiu9dhhH3qMBe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"eSGLiNyg7ttAZa8E"}
{"name":"Live Off The Land","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is familiar enough with a preferred terrain that they may survive within it without effort. The hero no longer needs to make Survival rolls for themselves while within their preferred terrain—they are considered to automatically succeed. Survival rolls to accommodate other people are still necessary, but the hero gains a +2 bonus that stacks with their Woodsman Survival bonus.</p><p>This Edge need only be taken once to apply to all of a character’s preferred terrains (if more than one.)","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Preferred Terrain, Survival d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.9XDpkfakCZUK0bhh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"eSvKPbVvihe58eoJ"}
{"name":"Be A Zebra","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"There’s protection in the herd! You gain a +2 to Parry if you are adjacent to at least one ally or fellow target (Dean’s call).","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.huY1nLSdVHJsNhZh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"eTnrJ7Iw57F4Pfyd"}
{"_id":"ekGScxH2HyM4hmSA","name":"Rank (NCO Or Officer)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Non-commissioned officers (sergeants) and regular officers (lieutenants and higher) get to command subordinates, but are also responsible for the success or failure of their men and their mission. They know the thrill of watching a plan come together, and the agony of watching one fall apart.</p><p>In Weird Wars, the Rank Edge allows NCOs and officers to command a unit appropriate to their rank level. Characters who purchase this Edge get an additional benefit, described below. Nonplayer characters and those who achieve rank during play do not get these additional abilities.</p><p>NCOs are the backbone of their squad, and must be tougher, stronger, and more resilient than those they lead. Noncoms with the Rank (NCO) Edge add +2 to their Toughness to reflect their hard-bitten nature. The character’s military rank is the lowest for an NCO in his particular service branch (a sergeant in the US Army, for example).</p><p>Officers are there to inspire and lead, and should definitely concentrate on Leadership Edges as they advance. To help them get there, officers gain an additional Benny per game session, and may always spend it on those under their command. (An officer with the Common Bond Edge can grant a Benny to anyone—not just those under his command.) A character with the Rank (Officer) Edge starts at the lowest commissioned officer rank in his particular service branch (usually 2nd Lieutenant or the equivalent of O-1). Tactical Command: Note that though NCOs and officers may give the orders, tactical control of Extras during play should still be split up among the players as usual. This ensures everyone gets to do something and doesn’t overburden the commanders. Remember this is still Savage Worlds, and the action should be fast and furious.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.2vXYWXqEct4NjNcp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Devout","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Devout students believe in a greater power, deity, or spirit, or perhaps just their own sense of self and willpower. They are typically religious, but don’t have to be. Devout heroes add +2 to all opposed Spirit rolls where their faith might come into play such as resisting evil powers (Dean’s call).","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.y46lgc1Ev8f7vcwp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ewpVXmxkC4mT3vnD"}
{"name":"Well Equiped","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Through favors, recommendations, past performance, or a “friend” in the department your character gains an additional 2 Resource Points. These may be used before a mission or saved for Field Requisitions as normal.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Charismatic, Tradecraft d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.Q8bha8ZI1NHPRcOY"}},"_id":"f6h9zldrupmCD1BA"}
{"name":"Sky Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Select one maneuver with a penalty that is allowed by an aircraft. When performing this aircraft maneuver you have a +2 to your roll but only to cancel out part of or the entire penalty. This bonus cannot increase your roll beyond your normal, unmodified ability.</p><p>You cannot apply this Edge to the so-called unnamed maneuver unless an entirely new one is outright designed and named.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.ySgM1UCbbVRr56gQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"f7wLmlzdT4yEzA3X"}
{"name":"Ghost","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"They call you a ghost because you’re adept at covering your tracks after you’ve completed your hacks. You gain a +2 bonus to Hacking skill rolls when attempting to securely log out of a system.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hacking d10, Hacker"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.6GgxmApDiM9abBA5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fRRWarIcgSwVcKvy"}
{"name":"Augmented Warrior","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character has learned how to use his cyberlimb for both offensive and defensive purposes. Augmented warriors increase their Parry by 1 and roll Str+d4 when hitting with their cyberlimbs. If they already have a damage die from the Brawler Edge, Martial Artist Edge, etc., increase the damage by one die type.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Martial Artist, Agility d8+, Cyberlimb"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.rhffXXQjz771ECfe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fSXq8Rk59MWdAAQR"}
{"name":"Adamantine Body","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The warforged was created from a specially designed line made with adamantine giving him +4 Armor instead of the normal +2 from Composite Plating. Special: This Edge must be taken during character creation.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.GJOZy8t6Tq8E9VYy"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fTAz0iRnYgGP7XSw"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"By putting his body in harm’s way, this hero can protect an adjacent individual. The Bodyguard can extend the benefit of the Defend maneuver to (or act as Medium Cover for ranged attacks made against) an adjacent ally.","notes":"Wiseguys page 53","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.FYolIRYxUlJj6rGS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fWoAg1LCa9uBhD7g"}
{"name":"Coordinated Firing","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This edge allows the character to benefit from gang up bonus when making ranged attacks in coordination with anyone else who also has this edge. When both characters are attacking the same declared target that round. They must make this declaration before either one acts that round. The max benefit from this is +4.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shooting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.zn28o0e1toKOqoM6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fmBj6Rh8Pz6qpXHu"}
{"name":"Shadow Trickery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"An assassin with this edge can use the shadows to provide them advantages and opportunities to escape, close, or strike.</p><p>The assassin can take one of the following actions by making a Stealth check with a –1 penalty. Range of any effect is character’s Spirit die.</p><p>• Douse a single light source, no larger than a lantern or lamp. The light source re-illuminates at the end of the assassin’s next turn. </p><p>• Create a distracting movement in the shadows causing a single target to become Distracted. With a raise on the Stealth roll, a second target is Distracted as well. </p><p>• Cause shadows to cling and pull at an enemy giving a –1 penalty to Pace and any actions taken until the end of the target’s next turn. </p><p>• Become obscured as if the illumination was one step lower (Dim to Dark, Dark to Pitch Darkness) for the rest of the encounter. This effect requires the initial illumination to be at least Dim.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.mSoZJqrwMO0Q5I2q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fmmKoUQDfeaQMKij"}
{"name":"Grit","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Through perseverance and maybe a little insanity, this hardcase reduces all Fear penalties and results on the Fear Effects table by 2. Grit also stacks with Brave.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Spirit d8+, Guts"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.pvUDk2VwNiUIA3XP"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fqewLJAQT7APdBDf"}
{"name":"Rumormonger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Heroes with this Edge have a knack for “putting the word on the street” and having that word believed as true. To spread a rumor, the ’Monger makes a Streetwise roll while talking to those to whom he wishes to spread the rumor. He gets a −2 penalty if the GM considers the rumor overly outrageous, and a +2 bonus if the rumor is similar to what’s already accepted as truth.","notes":"The Last Parsec - Irongate","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.gq8Nsy5miMzbYwaN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"g6JWLDpqcGJI1a7x"}
{"name":"Daring Strike","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your precision on strikes does not weaken your blows as much as the untrained. When performing a Desperate Attack, your penalty to damage is half the bonus to you assign to your Fighting rolls.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Alertness, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.BlOmrez52rRrtpE8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gGllm1WVgkdO9rDA"}
{"_id":"gIipRdvPJwFdXyhE","name":"Demo Man","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character is skilled with all sorts of explosives, detonators, and booby-traps. He adds +2 to all rolls made to set, disarm, or improvise explosives and booby-traps (but not Notice them). This can cover a range of abilities and skills determined by your War Master, including ordnance disposal, bomb making, or structural demolition.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.WLBEtBDaj5q6qUf8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Photographic Memory","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero can recall everything you’ve seen, read, or experienced perfectly. If you forget some detail your hero experienced, you may spend a Bennie to have the GM remind you.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 78","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 78","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_mzd2ru27sn","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pulp Fantastic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.vbJAwHxaPBZ2lvhp"}},"_id":"gQWglEWdi49IywLf"}
{"name":"Kill Shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This skilled opponent can combine the Aim maneuver and Marksman Edge, gaining a +4 bonus when a round is spent aiming and then no movement is engaged in during the round in which the shot is fired.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Marksman, Shooting d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.QSDhhwupOjrcdaDl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gV6I3tYpucwXl5DD"}
{"_id":"gj7vwLRiKAD2itsz","name":"Scrounger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some soldiers seem to have an uncanny ability to find just what they’re looking for among the mountains of equipment shipped into the theater.</p><p>A soldier with the Scrounger Edge can acquire almost any piece of equipment or luxury item. Once per session, and while in a populated area (such as a large village or town), a successful Streetwise roll allows the Scrounger to do one of the following:</p><p>• Improve one squad’s Ammo one level. • Acquire one “heavy” weapon with limited ammunition (such as a flamethrower, 1d4 hand grenades, or a machine gun—War Master’s choice).</p><p>• Improve one squad’s Rations one level. • Acquire 2d6 “refills” for a medic’s med pack. • Find 2d6 × $20 in easily-concealed cash or valuables.</p><p>• Acquire some rare but not particularly valuable item (cigars, silk stockings, fine chocolate, a needed spare part, etc.).","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.oOitC3OMtSQI8CmZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Faithful","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This hero’s faith in something—whether it’s science, God, or whatever—is so strong supernatural creatures fear her. Supernaturally evil creatures subtract 2 from any Trait roll directly affecting the character.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Devout, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.AK7GkypjMfe9l43l"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gjBSUZvGV4dh4izT"}
{"name":"Grab and Hold","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent’s intimate knowledge of wrestling maneuvers grants him a +1 to any opposed Strength or Agility grappling rolls. Additionally, he substitutes his Unarmed Combat damage for normal grappling damage.<p><b>Normal:</b> Snake has Unarmed Combat (Basic) and does Str+d4 damage with his unarmed strikes. When he grapples, he does only his Strength in damage.<p><b>Example:</b> Snake learns Grab and Hold. Now, he may apply his Unarmed Combat (Basic) damage to grappled opponents, doing Str+d4 damage to anyone within his iron grasp. Should he later get, Unarmed Combat (Advanced), it increases to Str+d6.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 23","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Unarmed Combat (Basic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.nurQpIA7thc4Jrzo"}},"_id":"h3iPM8uB3YGLt4CG"}
{"_id":"hAZz93vr8mlB2TFS","name":"Arcane Exposure","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character has had a brush with the supernatural. Perhaps you saw a ghost, or read some mystic tome. Whatever the cause, you know that strange things really can exist, and you’re more prepared than most people to encounter them. Add +2 to Sanity and Fear rolls when facing supernatural terrors.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"20"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.Y5Brd3qEAyGclQlL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Heavy-G Worlder","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character comes from a dense world with very heavy gravity. He starts with a d6 in Strength, doubles normal jumping distances, adds +2 to his Pace, his running die increases one step, and does not suffer the –2 Agility penalty for Normal gravity.</p><p>The character must take an additional Major Hindrance or two Minor Hindrances to balance out this particularly powerful Edge.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.BTwOwkZepUXHLg4H"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"hSIWh3KVTY5nDNet"}
{"name":"Grimm Berlin","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Grimm Berlin is among the best in the world, and it shows. When dealing with other Monster Hunters, they gain +1 to Persuasion rolls. They also have +1 to one of the following, chosen when they take this Edge: Shooting, Fighting, Driving, or Piloting Rolls.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into Grimm Berlin, Seasoned."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.NttTomLM5rDkZZnn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"hWLCGtTE01uIhDuk"}
