{"name":"Kiss Of Death","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Handling poisons takes years of practice to master. This exotic and deceptive assassin has learned how to deliver it in combat or by surprising her victims. Through rigorous training, the poisoner has gained Immunity to Poison. Furthermore, she carries around doses of Mild Poison (see Poison in Savage Worlds) that she can deliver with a Touch Attack in combat, or automatically out-of-combat if she has Surprise. If the victim has any reason to suspect the ruse, roll Persuasion vs. Notice. On a success, the potential victim has no idea what’s coming to them!","notes":"Wiseguys page 53","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Attractive"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.9ww71tCrzUoQ0uw2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"iUWVIt3F7wtNdqlO"}
{"name":"Associate","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character has an associate who travels with him and acts as his helpful counterpart. The associate is an Extra under your control (although the GM role-plays the Associate in social situations).<p>Depending upon who your hero is, he might have a Soldier bodyguard or use the Irregular stats (adding 5 skill points, an Attribute increase, and an Edge) to built other types of Associates with the GM’s permission such as a Fleet-Footed servant, a Rich “master” who can be talked into all manner of adventures,or a Thief henchman.<p>Other types of Associates are possible with the GM’s consent. Should your Associate perish or depart, you must recruit another through normal advancement (i.e., take the Edge again).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8, Persuasion d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.PHKR7oyw7q9CssBa"}},"_id":"ic4Pa0nFpiTlsqjG"}
{"name":"Analyze Shield Harmonics","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your understanding of electromagnetism lets you find weak spots that others don't even know to look for. You may scan an opponent’s shield frequency mid-battle by making a Knowledge (Astronomy) roll. With a success, your vessel’s energy weapons gain +4 AP against that vessel. This lasts until an officer aboard the target ship realigns their shields with a Knowledge (Starship Operations) check, at –2 if you got a raise.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice. Knowledge (Astronomy) d6; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d6."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.rnpSnP9EiJFGQlYV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"idVGWqMOgheeOt1R"}
{"name":"Shadow Blade","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As a free action, the wielder conjures a shadow melee weapon to their hand. The weapon passes through mundane objects without effect, though they offer a slight resistance. The weapon is a bladed weapon that deals Str+d4, AP 2. It can also harm ethereal creatures. While it is activated, the character is considered armed. Deactivating the weapon is a free action.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.VdubwRCcgPBGq2Ij"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o3yyzjnmbu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ijXgQjNaSwKENWuS"}
{"name":"Flexible Summoner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is familiar with a number of creatures they can summon, or their summoned spirits are unusually malleable. Instead of one ally choice per Rank, select two different allies of each Rank; your hero can choose between these with each casting of summon ally. She can also spend eight hours of work or meditation to change one of these allies out for another of the same Rank.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d8+, Occult d8+, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.mLAlTzpVvuaI3eMN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v74x6k6usus","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"isrEkOzAu0dIrnn6"}
{"name":"Daredevil","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This hero laughs at danger! He gets a free and automatic chance to reroll any failed Athletics test. If this roll is also failed he may then use Bennies for additional chances as usual.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 40","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.JGzNHsxMuKmcA1X2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"izuwvV5GVTiEFD8S"}
