{"_id":"jdbI9bQLwi9VPeNn","name":"Ceremonial Casting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who have stumbled upon the secrets of the unknown have found they can greatly increase the power of certain spells and invocations if they are more carefully and slowly cast.</p><p>To cast a spell or miracle using ceremonial casting, the character must take no other actions for 10 minutes. He must be able to speak and freely make gestures with his hands, and must not be Shaken during this period. If those conditions are met, the caster makes his Faith or Spellcasting roll as usual. If successful, he may increase the base Duration of any of the following spells to one hour: armor, boost / lower Trait, deflection, speak language, or speed.</p><p>The spells may be maintained at the cost of 1 Power Point per target per additional hour.","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"25"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.Op2toWJbR7mYmYqB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Guardian","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"On rare occasions, a colonist or anouk seemingly cheats death and returns to the land of the living. These lucky souls find themselves granted a second chance at life, but also return with a deep and profound connection to Banshee itself. This connection provides the Guardian with unique abilities, but also a responsibility to stand against the darkness that threatens to engulf the living planet. If your character is reborn into the life of a Guardian, you can read the details on it in No Man’s Land (page 69).</p><p>The Guardian Edge may only be selected at character creation, but you might become one if your hero bites the Banshee dust. See page 74 if you want to know more about becoming one of the living planet’s chosen protectors. Just realize it means taking a short dirt nap first...","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.x2zE5S0ffUmwwiDe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"jg59VEgiuQRgAe6k"}
