{"name":"Ranger Of Repute","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have made a name for yourself as a friend to inhabitants of your favored territory. Your hero gains +4 to Charisma when interacting with creatures and cultures native to your preferred terrain. However, this is only so long as the character is not perceived or believed to be working against the creatures’ or culture’s interests or well-being.</p><p>This Edge need only be taken once to apply to all of a character’s preferred terrains (if more than one.)","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Beast Bond, Preferred Terrain, Wilderness Friends, Spirit d8+, Survival d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.TZ8LtbTpXXgyTD5i"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"lKQ2opHTrHRIqs01"}
{"name":"Storm Knight","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<b>Arc Lightning:</b> When you hit a target with a melee or ranged attack, you can arc lightning onto nearby enemies. When you do, choose another target within 1” of the creature you originally hit and make the same type of attack roll against the chosen target. If you hit, that target takes 1d8 lightning damage. </p><p>This additional attack cannot generate another Arc Lightning attack.</p><p><b>Lightning Resistance:</b> You take half damage from lightning-based attacks (before comparing to Toughness).","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+ or Shooting (or Throwing) d8+, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.gkC8FFG3A8u37nRz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"lpin5aTGBRopzwYZ"}
{"name":"Sucker Punch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character doesn’t know the meaning of the words “fair fight.” If he succeeds in a Test of Will against an adjacent opponent, the character receives a free Fighting attack. This attack does not incur a multi-action penalty.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d6+, Fighting d8+, First Strike"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.gawlsUKxWKOwbH6J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"lpopTOwgTcSUpTtx"}
{"name":"Team Leader","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Allies under a Wild Card sent to complete an assignment need to be reminded of the consequences for failure. This works like the Common Bond Edge, but a team leader can share her Bennies with the team even though she can’t directly communicate with them. This helps ensure the success of the team under her supervision and minimize losses.","notes":"Wiseguys page 54","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+, Intimidation d6+, Command"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.xe000TeFLiHvrNII"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"lsEycoR8NHsCiSNz"}
{"name":"Storm Knight III","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<b>Lightning Storm:</b> Your <i>Arc Lighting</i> attacks now all affects all targets within a small blast template centered on the original target.  Each target can roll an Agility test to see if they dodge the effect.</p><p>If they succeed, they are moved out of the blast range and take no damage, but become Distracted.  If they get a raise, they are still moved with no damage, but are not Distracted.</p><p><b>Greater Lighting Immunity:</b> Friendly creatures within 5” of you are immune to lightning damage.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Storm Knight II"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.sA9u4VlcUNKl4HDW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"m3otzzPcHeF29wmv"}
{"name":"Gravity Defying","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This fellow is very much at home on vertical surfaces. He receives a +2 bonus to all Athletics rolls related to climbing, a +2 bonus to Athletics rolls related to avoiding or surviving a fall, and if he does fall he ignores one die of falling damage.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Athletics d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.8o05R2qdjO89Qx6J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"m5jfSOduEoFBuwDx"}
{"name":"Savior Of The Universe","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Whether a brave leader of the Freemen or a benevolent noble, the character has been elevated to the status of a living legend, a “savior of the universe,” by the people of Mongo.</p><p>Savior of the Universe should only be taken after a character has performed a great and heroic deed. The deed must also have been performed where others witnessed it and can spread her fame throughout Mongo.</p><p>If this is true and the Edge is taken, the hero may forever after convert her own Bennies to Conviction tokens on a one-to-one basis. Even more importantly, she may spend Conviction on <i>others</i> as well as herself. Conviction is explained on page 73.</p><p>Unlike all other Edges, the Born a Hero Setting Rule doesn’t apply to Savior of the Universe. It may only be taken at Veteran level, and only after performing an epic deed as mentioned above.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 42","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, an epic and heroic deed"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.2QgO6lfU3gaoL83T"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"mtroGRAGSHgzBe0f"}
{"name":"Gravitic Acclimation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The spacer knows how to operate in different gravities. He ignores the typical –2 penalty for operating in a gravity other than his own (see Gravity on page 27).","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Ag d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.z2riR4zYYyOFQYc8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_yfwlzrgauop","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"mzfgAQj7YIWipN2y"}
