{"name":"Pla Paranormal Combat Unit","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Members of the PLA-PCU are the best of the best in China. As long as they are operating in China, they gain +1 to Persuasion rolls, and the benefits of the Luck Edge.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the PLA-PCU."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.VLkH0x2jETV9QkX3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"o7i3hN8g4lYoG5eI"}
{"name":"Lay Of The Land","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is entirely at home in the wilderness, allowing them to move through it soundlessly and with nary a trace. While in the wilderness, the character is always considered to automatically be hiding their tracks for the sake of Tracking rolls made to follow them, and increases their Woodsman’s Stealth bonus to +4.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Woodsman, Knowledge (Nature) d10+, Tracking d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.75NLZNw0A64xB4cO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oDqqWhKTmoxf9qXj"}
{"name":"Clinch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This pugilist makes full use of their martial training when grappling and to pulverizing their opponents. Your hero may use their Fighting in place of Athletics to Grapple opponents as well as their unarmed damage when performing the Crush option. The Martial Artist and Martial Warrior edges gives bonuses to unarmed Fighting rolls, these bonuses apply in conjunction with this edge.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Martial Artist, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.g1xRmlcwC7mEW29Q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oPqivVyb3mXtr7mR"}
{"_id":"oYu4R6aj9zKQDkiv","name":"Mechanically Inclined","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Great War was the first war of technology, and armies quickly discovered the value of trained technicians. Your character is good with mechanical and electrical devices, and can easily figure out how to use and repair them. He gets a +2 bonus to Knowledge or Repair rolls required to use, design, troubleshoot, or repair such devices (engines, wireless sets, encryption devices, field telephones, electrical and hydraulic systems, machinery, etc.).","notes":"Weird War I","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"24"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.weird-war-i-edges.ZzK3shA7vFo4177J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6j8uzj9fx9s","path":"Weird War I","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Defensive Expertise","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character has trained to maneuver while being on guard against enemy blows. The hero’s Parry bonus is increased by +2 (to a total of +6) when using the Defend option and they may also Run. Alternately, you may decrease the Defend Parry bonus to +2 as an action (instead of your entire turn), which allows your hero to use the Multi-Action rule (at a –2 for one other action, or –4 for two additional actions) on their turn. The reduced Parry bonus still lasts until the beginning of your next turn.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.GoWp6qF1zxXYHJ3F"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"omMhSEO2RNdIyvBq"}
{"name":"Lackeys","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You gain the services of a second lackey. They should be created in the same way as your first lackey, but the two are independent of each other, and may have a different arrangement of attributes, skills, Edges and Hindrances.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 10","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Lackey"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.994DchpsiUH6OuPS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oqAryLXTn7ZmDJrM"}
{"name":"Gunner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to an- ticipate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in ground vehicles. The character’s Fast Targets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed for ground vehicles.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Driving d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.QtfncJpWcLXKcSFL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"otzNXATHd2Z6cs3j"}
{"name":"Uwharrie Special Security Services","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"USSS has a depth of knowledge related to occult lore due to their founder being a rare book dealer. They gain +2 to Occult and Academics rolls.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into USSS."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.Bm9vX77XGzWVk2Jf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oz1Et7pUSl2Qe4XZ"}
{"name":"Reroute Auxiliary Power","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When rerouting power, you trade energy “at cost” rather than at one-half. For example, draining 8 Shields can energize the Targeting Computers by +2, instead of +1. In other words, a Half-Step is traded for a Half-Step, and a Full-Step is traded for a Full-Step. (See ‘Reroute Power’ in Setting Rules for more information.)","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d8; Knowledge (Engineering) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.uIWKXEIlCnAsjoPR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pGnFNUzsvjV5mwlB"}
{"name":"Power Attack","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You know how to hit and when you do you hit hard. The hero’s Strength is counted as one die-type higher when making Fighting damage rolls. This bonus applies to minimum Strength for weapons as well.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.lmePnSAyOqGMYDkX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pKcYmXyGo9O3kx03"}
{"name":"Wave Maneuver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Select one maneuver with a penalty that is allowed by a watercraft. When performing this watercraft maneuver you have a +2 to your roll but only to cancel out part of or the entire penalty. This bonus cannot increase your roll beyond your normal, unmodified ability.</p><p>You cannot apply this Edge to the so-called unnamed maneuver unless an entirely new one is outright designed and named.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Boating d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.wMtqKVUr9ExgK0NW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pTcB1niR2pe34qNX"}
{"name":"Wilderness Friends","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is exceptionally familiar with the ways of beasts native to a preferred terrain. The character gains +2 Healing, Persuasion, and Riding with regards to such creatures.</p><p>This Edge need only be taken once to apply to all of a character’s preferred terrains (if more than one.)","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Beast Bond, Preferred Terrain, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.GBRXVWXCaFIVLNWC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pfxBk6h2Z9k4sNdB"}
{"name":"Flexible Caster","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero has mastered how to modify his powers to adapt to various situations.</p><p> Whenever the hero activates a power with at least one Power Modifier selected (with a cost of 1 or higher), the total cost of the power is reduced by 1.","notes":"Fantasy: Tomes and Prayers page 47","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any), arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.AJD4YSx8CPXRNe9s"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pl6yyG9NtZrOKje1"}
{"name":"Cold-blooded Killer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Stealing is one thing; the gruesome reality of death can rattle most individuals. A Cold-Blooded Killer isn’t disturbed by the grisly sight of mutilated bodies or vicious torture. His heart doesn’t beat any faster. The sight and smell of dead bodies don’t bother him. When confronted with what he’s done, he shows no remorse. As such, he is immune to Fear of the Nausea variety and a polygraph has no advantage against him.","notes":"Wiseguys page 52","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Ruthless (Major)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.9wcyZb5IyMC3MiGE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"psMmoDefbWcihf4q"}
{"name":"New South Wales Expeditions","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Team Members of the NSWE gain +2 when attacking or dealing with enemies from other planes of existence.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the NSWE."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.KeBKmn8amj8yCVvI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"q3NTffz70oksRUj4"}
{"name":"Alternate Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have another identity you are known by, airtight with background, job history, computer records, official documentations, etc. This lets you operate under an alias that cannot easily be traced back to you, since everything checks out for all but the most persistent snoop. If the character’s identity is ever revealed through his actions (or inactions), he loses the benefits of this Edge. This Edge may be taken multiple times, each time the Edge is taken the character gains a new identity.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.7B9Svgfu0j0wD7Si"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"q3hedifMW7xwDfBh"}
{"name":"Drunkard’s Luck","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When the hero is under the effects of Liquid Courage in combat, he gains a Benny. If not used, that Benny is lost at the end of the combat","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Liquid Courage, Luck"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.kKgZooTWyTxDjPSV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"q4lUWHqIZoF9LEWX"}
{"name":"Cooker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This criminal knows how to brew ale, distill alcohol, or manufacture drugs. Pick one that is currently illegal. The Cooker has a laboratory and an assistant (Follower with the Lieutenant Street Ability) he may employ to produce illegal goods ready for distribution. It takes a week to rebuild his laboratory or still if it’s destroyed. Double the amount of money raised this way (see Racketeering on page 51). This stacks with other Edges.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Science d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.bnfgOVze7grIwdHR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qES2cga55Bx5mKrg"}
