{"name":"Cavalryman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While riding, the hero ignores up to two points of penalties to any Riding roll and may spend Bennies to Soak damage for their mount using her Riding skill instead of the mount’s Vigor. Each success and raise negates a Wound.</p><p>Also, if the hero has the Block, Dodge, or Extraction Edges (and improved versions), they also affect the mount she is riding. And with the Counterattack Edge, she can riposte failed attacks against her mount","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Riding d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.zq1wR26HQZaqj2iZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qFwBBJDYevVnb5uK"}
{"name":"Carnivore","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As a free action, the agent may make a Spirit roll to voluntarily go berserk. He may also go berserk automatically by spending a benny.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 22","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, St d8, Berserk, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.JVMGS6Gg6fk8PRI8"}},"_id":"qKFvKpGDb1JnJxJg"}
{"name":"Cairo Paranormal Investigations","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Members of Cairo PI are adept at investigation, subterfuge and intrigue. They gain +2 to all Persuasion rolls when in disguise or acting, and can spend a Benny to gain entrance to any location they wish (GM’s discretion. Some hyper-secure facilities might be too far, even for Cairo PI.)","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Cairo PI."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.BL8rcC0JkFDJS4sZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qMDqqa2GzD9lHEXZ"}
{"name":"Armor Of The Wilds","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You never need be without protection while within the wilderness. Given a few minutes, the hero may attempt a Knowledge (Armorsmithing) roll to create crude armor or shield from what they find in the wilds (the Gamemaster should place logical restrictions on the armor and shield type to suit the resources available.)</p><p>The armor can be a skinned vest or bark shield, for example, and will function in that respect except it will result in a –1 penalty to Agility based rolls due to encumbrance. (It is considered fitted to the hero who made it, but not for anyone else.) Furthermore, the armor is fragile and will fall apart or break on a natural 1 on a soak roll. A raise on the Knowledge roll to create the armor allows the hero to remove this penalty. Regardless, the armor or shield will only last for one fight / encounter, after which it is useless.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Woodsman, Knowledge (Armorsmithing) d6+, Knowledge (Nature) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.Jdjez9vYsnlMBi5J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qNeEGjmJIKshN9MM"}
{"name":"Improved Hack Sensors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Hack Sensors, but you may also create a false image of another ship, up to one Size larger than your own (a sudden reinforcement, a mutual enemy, even a mirror image of your own vessel). The phantom is dispersed when the computer hack is fixed.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Hack Sensors"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.8OxuvGWrRsgZg8xI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qPKki2gTrO31tN42"}
{"name":"Elite Shifter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Either inherently or through conditioning, the shifter’s ability is enhanced beyond its normal abilities. All abilities are in effect only while shifting. Beasthide: The shifter gains +2 Toughness. Cliffwalk: The shifter adds an additional +4 to Agility (climbing) rolls. Dreamsight: The shifter can spend a full round to gain extraordinary visual power, gaining a +2 bonus to Notice rolls based on vision and can see creatures and objects under the influence of the invisibility power. Gorebrute: With a successful charge attack, the shifter may use the Push action as a free action. He may use any of the options available except shield bash. The Push action still requires an opposed rull. The effects of the Push action are in addition to the damage dealt by his horns. Longstride: The shifter’s Pace increases by an additional +2, and her running die increases by another die type. Longtooth: Wounds dealt by the shifter’s bite attacks bleed copiously. Whenever the shifter makes a successful damage roll from a bite attack, she adds +4 to the damage. Razorclaw: If the shifter can charge at least 6\" before attacking a target with her claws, she can make two claw attacks at the end of the charge. The shifter also adds +4 to damage rolls for each claw attack. Swiftwing: The shifter can fly at a Pace of 12”. Truedive: The shifter can swim at twice his Pace. Wildhunt: Non-visual senses improve to such a degree that the shifter’s Notice skill increases by one die size. This increase applies to non-visual senses only. Winterhide: The shifter’s bonus to resist cold environments increases to +16. Cold Damage is also reduced by 16. Special: Shifters with the Extra Shifter Ability Edge may take this Edge a second time to enhance the second trait.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"e