{"name":"Surgeon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This hero is skilled with a scalpel. She may attempt one Healing roll on a character to remove wounds after the Golden Hour or to repair a permanent Injury. When installing rippertech, the patient gets a +1 bonus to the Implant Table roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Healing d8, Knowledge (Rippertech) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.MpQVPQVVWQFh99VI"}},"_id":"rDxY8TLZC4Z4awni"}
{"name":"Scientific Insight","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can spend a bennie to ask the GM for special insight into the current problem or situation. This can be the answer to a yes-no question, or some simple facts—GM's discretion—but it should be relevant and useful information. You should come up with some scientific basis for your new burst of insight.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Scholar applied to any two purely scientific disciplines (e.g., Computers, Astronomy, Biology, but not Jazz or Tactics)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.HAanr05Rd1J3HUUY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rGqb2iFUVUqpyrup"}
{"name":"Card Shark","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This swindler’s been practicing scams and sleight of hand his whole life. He usually has someone else in the room working the scam with him or knows the game so well that he can exploit people’s weaknesses and bleed them dry. He knows all the tricks.</p><p> A Card Shark gets +4 to Gambling instead of +2 when cheating at a game of cards and can spend a Benny to reroll a Critical Failure. He can also use Gambling instead of Thievery when performing sleight of hand tricks with gambling implements such as cards or poker chips.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Gambling d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.rTxlY4O0lmjnkvqY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rR3gpFIbb86OpyzP"}
