{"name":"Arcane Assassin","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Most common among the mage hunters of Ios, this edge allows your hero to ignore attack penalties and bonuses to Armor caused by an active spell or magical effect. Typically, this will include any variations on the Armor and Deflection powers, but not indirect effects like Obscure or an increased Parry as a result of Boost Trait.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d6+, Knowledge (Arcana) d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.9wH6kHSFBceU1IsO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"radtZMxyFEc3dZuF"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Nano-Mage)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>&bull;Arcane Skill: Master (Smarts)</p>\n<p>&bull;Starting Powers: 3</p>\n<p>&bull;Power Points: 10</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>The nanomachines have limited locomotion so they only have a range of touch or self. This decreases the power point cost by 1 as normal. For example, the caster desiring to cast Entangle on a foe would need to perform a successful touch attack.</p>\n<p>This limitation is offset by the ability to set a \"swarm trap\". The cost of the swarm trap is the same as the normal casting cost. A swarm trap is where part of a swarm lie in wait for something to come within its radius of affect. This is either the spell's normal effect or small blast template, whichever is larger. Spells that have a range can typically be used as a swarm trap.</p>\n<p>The caster stands at the center of the desired area of effect and casts the spell as normal. However, it does not go off immediately as the swarm simply stands in place waiting to be triggered. The swarm trap lasts as long as the caster stays within the range of the spell (for example, 2 x smarts for Blast) or dismissed. The caster may decide when the swarm triggers by setting a condition( for example, \"Someone enters the room\", \"Three bandits are by the tree\"). However, if the mage wishes to trigger the trap before the condition is met, the triggering uses the same rules as someone on Hold performing an Interrupting Action (Nano&shy;Mages also need to have Athletics to be successful). The mage's can recover invested Power Points when the trap triggers or when dispelled.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 3\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><em>For example, A Mage wishes touse Blast to take out a rushing group of Bandits. The caster casts the Power where they stand. The cost is 2 Power Points (3 normally minus the 1 less Power Point cost for no range). The caster decides it is best to be careful and uses the Selective (+1 point for a total of 3 points) modifier to only affect the Bandits. The mage decides to trigger the trap when three bandits enter the blast radius of the Power. After casting, the Mage moves away 6 paces. Two Bandits stop to fire their pistols and another runs into the radius of the Blast Power. Since none of the bandits triggered the spell last round, the Mage decides to move another 4 paces and maintains the trap. Since he is within his Smarts X 2 (d10 Smarts) range of the Blast Power, the trap remains in effect. This round another bandit advanced into the blass area. The Mage decides to trigger the trap immediately instead of waiting for the condition to be met. The Mage rolls a 10 for Athletics check. The Bandits roll only a 5 and the swarm's Blast effect is triggered before the bandits can react. The Bandits take 2d6 damage! Now they know there is a Mage to contend with! </em></p>\n<p>A swarm trap cannot be noticed or detected under normal circumstances (the GM may decide if Detect Arcana will discover traps). The trap also cannot activate until the mage moves away from it (they cannot get around the touch requirement by casting a trap and then triggering immediately) .</p>\n<p><strong>Source:&nbsp;</strong>Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 2</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2pQIprovBCT0uiKt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_h360mwewe9","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rc17vCSE8G4LMQUQ"}
{"name":"Triage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Allows a doctor to heal characters during combat. Wound penalties are doubled; e.g., a penalty of –4 to heal a character with 2 wounds. After combat is over, Wild Cards suffer 1 level of Fatigue per wound healed (cannot Incapacitate; requires 4 hours of sleep to recover 1 Fatigue level).","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Healing d8; Knowledge (Biology) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.oBDc0j4RJaCaSzGX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgph7dksida","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rsxfYtHRxKDyX0iT"}
{"name":"Jedi Knight/Sith Knight","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While you have a Lightsaber readied and you are aware of a ranged attack, the Target Number for the attacker equals your Parry score. This does not apply to area attacks.</p><p> You may throw your Lightsaber as a Multi-action in a straight line a number of inches equal to half your Force Use die and then recall your saber back to your hand. Making one Melee attack against a single target that you can see anywhere along the way. This takes all three of your actions. (one to throw it, one to attack, one to call it back) This attack does not suffer from MAP.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Force Sensitive (Jedi/Sith), Trademark Weapon (Lightsaber)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.GLG1bp4qWZ9mH2aE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"s5pHAMMlw3M4KjMx"}
