{"name":"Courage Of The Wilds","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Drawing strength and confidence from the wilderness about them and the ease it grants, the character gains a +2 bonus to fear-based Spirit checks within such an environment.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Woodsman page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Lay of the Land, Spirit d10+, Survival d12+, Tracking d12+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-woodsman.DfmpBsYrYFEEAcXa"},"cf":{"id":"temp_96k47jwnygb","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Woodsman","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"sD7qZtwRQbnyzNpC"}
{"_id":"sHsAkE8LDfJ8PehF","name":"Hedonist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character can binge on his vice to quickly recover some Power Points. This requires him to overindulge in his bad habit (which takes 10 minutes’ worth of time). A grifter addicted to alcohol, for example, might chug half a bottle of whisky. A smoker might cough up a lung going through an entire pack in 10 minutes. Or a gambler might risk way more cash than he can afford on a single roll of the dice with someone who must definitely be paid. Whatever the binge, when it’s over, the grifter recovers 1d6 Power Points.</p><p>The bender comes with a price—the hedonist suffers Fatigue until he can rest up for at least four hours. The grifter can repeat the trick unless he’s Exhausted (he cannot Incapacitate himself).","notes":"Deadlands Noir page 11","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Grifter), Smarts d8+, Spellcasting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"RX3k8ETYyqlbZDTC":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-noir-edges.16AoSuNgpMem0uhc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v","path":"Deadlands Noir","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Technomancer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The operator is a rare aberrant, an individual who can manipulate cyberspace without the need of a cyberdeck. This allows the operator to use technomancer abilities, above.","notes":"Sprawlrunners - Technomancers page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.sprawlrunners-technomancers.xQ191diaye8aUd0d"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2v6g1l9drn8","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Sprawlrunners: Technomancers","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"sJxkEyIHsnzdEnJO"}
{"name":"Ram ‘em!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero is an expert at causing the most damage possible to other watercraft during collisions. The character causes 1d8 damage to the target per 5” of speed while he and his vehicle still suffer the usual 1d6. Passengers in the hero’s watercraft will suffer the enhanced 1d8 damage, however.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Ace, Boating d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.38UI65wI5731mJKm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"sNqcXyeVO3O7sFeh"}
{"name":"Exorcist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is a member of the clergy trained to drive demonic spirits from human bodies. Anytime he makes an opposed Spirit or Faith test versus demons or supernaturally evil forces, he adds +4 to his roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 5","notes":"Horror Companion, page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Miracles), Spirit d8+, Faith d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.Wm9sDwOrYjEjm1ta"}},"_id":"saTCnsRhzBmDKdu0"}
{"name":"Precognitive Flashes","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You occasionally see visions of the future. They happen quickly, are almost always vague and hard to decipher, but they usually warn of some dangerous event that might save your life—and your friends as well. Once per session, when it seems most appropriate, the Dean will describe a likely upcoming event or scene. The future is mutable, so it may not come to pass, but it should be a likely course, or perhaps the vision depicts a path not to take and won’t unless your student ignores the warning.</p><p> Make a Spirit roll immediately after seeing the vision—the Dean may modify this depending on the severity of the vision. If the roll is failed, your character is Fatigued for the next eight hours. This might manifest as violent nosebleeds, migraines, or simple weariness. PSYCHICALLY SENSITIVE Requirements: Freshman, Spirit d6+ Something about this student gives her an affinity for paranormal energies and beings. She adds +2 to all rolls made to sense or communicate with supernatural beings. Of course the downside is that if such a creature knows the person is receptive they’re more likely to actually attempt contact. That may not actually be something you’ll want to happen at ETU.","notes":"East Texas University page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Psychically Sensitive, Danger Sense, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.DMzFnFdvYKr79F77"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"sbDvQ6WNWguRAOGe"}
{"name":"Dogfighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero’s hand-eye coordination and ability to anticipate his foes is such that he can better compensate for the effects of speed while in aircraft. The character’s Fast Targets penalty is reduced to –1 per 25” of speed for aircraft.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Ace, Piloting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.rHP7OfxmdGaNmvbF"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"schMrqn4XeE1IZwU"}
{"name":"Colonial Ranger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Colonial Rangers are the law enforcement arm of the United Colonial Assembly, a body currently led by former corporate shill turned people's champion JJ Lasster.</p><p>Officially , the Rangers’ jurisdiction only encompasses Banshee and any vessel or station in orbit around it. Since Operation Typhon and colonial revolt against EXFOR, the Rangers have carefully extended their reach further into space.</p><p>Most settlements on Banshee have Town Marshals, with the Rangers acting as traveling supervisors and judges. Space colonies have a Station Marshal that fulfills the same purpose. (EXFOR ships and HI-dedicated stations furnish their own security.)</p><p>The Rangers tend to stay out of system politics, however, leaving that to the Colonial Assembly and Chairman JJ Lasseter's capable mind. Most of the law dogs' time is spent keeping humans and anouks from killing each other, a constant and thankless task.</p><p>Colonial Rangers receive the title and badge but actual authority comes as it always does—with attitude, willpower, and occasional violence.</p><p>Rangers also get a uniform (which few wear), a Dragoon pistol with two full loads of ammo, their choice of six mini-grenades (see page 47), and body armor (page 45). Basic equipment damaged in the course of duty can be replaced free of charge at any Ranger station (found in most settlements over a few hundred).</p><p>Mission-essential equipment, such as a Stallion (page 60) or other vehicle, may be assigned by the hero’s superior officers on as-needed basis.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Common Knowledge d6+, Language (Anouk) d4+, Intimidation d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.3YtccYjLxbB1mjHM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"sgPLwFOo4AV51O6Q"}
{"name":"Challenging Cry","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The first time each round the hero Wounds or Incapacitates an enemy with an attack or power, he gets a free Intimidation or Taunt Test targeting (at least) that enemy or another enemy (of his choice) who saw his comrade take the blow","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Intimidation d8+ or Taunt d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.pkoxV8ASD4rMlDn5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"shMRYCBz2cyN93u9"}
{"name":"Takedown","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent is trained in how to throw or trip an opponent. Make an opposed Fighting roll versus the target. Each Size category difference incurs a –2 penalty. With a success, the now prone opponent may be placed in any spot within 1”of the agent. With a raise, the opponent is prone and Shaken; if already Shaken, he takes a wound.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 24","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.pNZaAHJdvbhAWuQP"}},"_id":"sqzu4nowHm6O632E"}
{"name":"Explosives Expert","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character loves it when things go boom! It doesn’t matter whether she’s working with commercial or household explosives, the Explosives Expert can make it happen. Nothing sends a message like a well-placed bomb. While anybody with the Repair skill can set explosive charges, the Explosives Expert can take things further. This virtuoso sees her talent as an art form.</p><p> This Edge grants the character +2 to Repair when manufacturing or setting explosives. She is also +1 to Notice hidden explosives.</p><p> Each raise on the Repair roll allows the character to select one of the following modifications. Unless otherwise specified, modifications can only be taken once.</p><p> • Potency: The explosive causes +d6 damage.</p><p> • Breaching: The explosive gains 2 AP. This modification can be taken more than once.</p><p> • Area of Effect: Can be increased or decreased by one size. Personal, SBT, MBT, LBT. This modification can be taken more than once.</p><p> • Concealment: The default size of the explosive occupies the size of a suitcase. Each raise increases the Notice penalty to discover the explosive by –2.</p><p> This modification can be taken up to twice. Alternatively, the Explosives Expert can roll with a –4 penalty for every modification she wants to give to her explosive device.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Repair d8+, Science d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.GULMiEBy4LcEReRM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"suPcXqZiAGkrFSi2"}
{"name":"Rapid Reload","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Be quick or be dead. A weapon’s Reload characteristic in your hero’s trained hands is reduced by one action, two if you do not move on your turn. If you run while reloading, then no check is required.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Athletics d6+ or Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.BgKT1DQHwuqymD4e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"t39H3GCNez1BRrem"}
{"name":"One Of The Chosen","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your investigator gains either a +1 to attack rolls vs. supernatural evil or they suffer a –1 penalty to attack rolls to hit him—your choice. You may take this Edge a second time but only after achieving a new Rank to gain the other ability.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 36","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.C8HPNYTmMVw2pF2v"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"t8tsQGe9O4sANjwf"}
{"name":"Determination","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This sturdy soul carries on when others fall by the wayside. When the character takes enough wounds from an attack to be Incapacitated, he gets one free Soak roll. If the roll fails he may then spend Bennies to make Soak rolls as usual.</p><p><i><b>Example:</b> Prince Barin already has 2 wounds when two vicious wolvrons sink their teeth into his flesh. They inflict 2 and 3 wounds respectively. Barin may make one free Soak roll against each attack.</i>","notes":"Flash Gordon page 40","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.2fWhVmuz4z1aQdHQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tHCiwgXadq0B0HLZ"}
