{"name":"Sunder Training","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has drilled and learned to defeat armor and destroying objects. All your Fighting attacks increase their AP by 2. They also get the bonus damage from raises (but still none of these dice can Ace) when Breaking Things.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+, Fighting d6+, Notice d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.AIPauSsbGbOXCbu6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tiqEi06GA8Eh69fb"}
{"name":"Extra Effort","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some Force Adepts can dig deep into their souls to significantly boost their powers.</p><p> Extra Effort increases a Force Use total after it’s rolled by +1 for 1 Power Point or +2 for 3 Power Points. It may not be used to improve a Critical Failure.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Force Adept), Force Use d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.JhIrh2j2IaqxoQ7g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tjXvH8PP83b8g8ac"}
{"name":"Enlightened Gun Fu!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Integrated training has honed this warrior’s reflexes to the point that pistols are an extension of her body. She may fire pistols when using Combat Edges such as First Strike, Frenzy, and Sweep.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Gun Fu!, Fighting d10+, Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.g1vrlnIgwUY78QkG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"twRGbkgqRsDXAe7M"}
{"name":"Slip And Swish","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero may attempt a Boating Test opposed by his opponent’s Smarts as a maneuver. If successful, the character increase’s his watercraft’s Parry by an amount equal to the Test’s successes for one round.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Ace, Boating d12+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.K0q8pWDDESoZLvS8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_sebdvv9ult","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - The Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"u2qCQfPLejOplEnh"}
{"name":"Vanishing Act","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The art of using moving objects, people or vehicles, as cover to make good a getaway. This operative is practiced in crossing the street at just the right moment, timing a dash across the rail tracks or maximizing a distraction in order to vanish into thin air.<p>To use this edge, the agent must make a successful Notice roll as an action to spot an opportunity to vanish. When a vehicle, two men carrying a sofa, or some other cover comes between the agent and his pursuer, the agent can make a clean getaway with a successful Stealth roll. Vanishing act may only be used to escape when the agent is on foot.<p>In a Chase situation, the agent may perform a Flee action with a distance of two cards between himself and his pursuer at –4 to the maneuver roll and escapes if successful. The penalty is reduced to –2 at a range of three cards and 0 when there are four cards between the agent and his pursuers.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Secret Files of Section D, page 8","notes":"Secret Files of Section D, page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, St d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6uwu6resjqd","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Section D","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.n1qGe0hbv0RqkeGT"}},"_id":"u4FJeBipsrmWHVR6"}
