{"name":"Improved Marksman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The weapon is one with your hero, they may perform feats with it that will amaze onlookers. Your character reduces the risk of hitting an Innocent Bystander by one, so most ROF 1 weapons do not threaten Innocent Bystanders. Weapons with ROF 2+ and shotguns only threaten Innocent Bystanders on a roll of 1 on their skill die or dice. You may use weapons larger than a pistol when using Ranged Weapons in Melee, and do not become Vulnerable when targeting non-adjacent foes. An adjacent defender’s TN is still their Parry.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Marksman, Athletics d10+ or Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.1yBz08srhujvrPs0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"u9o5zw6pYMeU8DjZ"}
{"name":"Gun Fu","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent is able to maneuver well enough to continue using any firearm in close combat.<p><b>Normal: </b>Agent Rook has an M-16 and is rushed by a werewolf. He can club the beast with it, but is unable to get a bead on the creature as it bites and slashes at him.<p><b>Example:</b> Agent Rook, having survived his close encounter, learns Gun Fu and takes point. The next lycanthrope to jump down on him from the shadows is in for a nasty surprise, as he unloads his clip into the creature at point blank range.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 23","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Unarmed Combat (Basic), Shooting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.XkFpgiJWMGFpFzwD"}},"_id":"uB5iTcZONDtAIduB"}
{"name":"Technical Journals","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character researches or finds a technical journal which allows him to fine tune a gizmo for superior reliability. The Edge applies to <i>all</i> the character’s powers. When he rolls a Critical Failure on an arcane skill roll, roll a die. Odd, it malfunctions as usual. Even, it simply fails to work. Either way, only 1 Power Point is spent.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, AB (Weird Science), Weird Science d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.8hGmWJVLcR0CylNV"}},"_id":"uFDvJEuOi5YEUI6K"}
{"_id":"uIeacYXg10Fo7nKG","name":"Comfortable","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 12\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Your character is a hard-working Joe who watches his wallet. He begins with the normal starting money funds ($150) and doesn&rsquo;t have to halve his total funds each game week. Things are rough enough in the Big Easy that just having a steady income is an Edge! </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Comfortable is a requirement for taking the Noble </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">and Rich Edges in </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Deadlands Noir</span><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">. </span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.U5lRBa9hU6eCFwug"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dwi1jwgfw7v"}}}
{"name":"Infused Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The mage is so connected with the machines that he can leverage them for soak rolls. Each PP provides a +1 to Soak Rolls to a maximum of +4.","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Seasoned, Master d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.7cISEWIOMncYQMpU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_h360mwewe9","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"uJXbqR0ArshhTCjv"}
{"name":"Forger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent makes excellent forgeries. He receives +2 to all Forgery rolls and +2 to Notice rolls to detect fakes (Forgery vs. Notice).","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8, Forgery d8, Notice d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.XpQD4IXRstgWjY1Q"}},"_id":"uMlTP0qNsKLnY0h9"}
{"name":"Aggressive Driver","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This driver is adept at using her vehicle to drive others off the road. During a Chase, an Aggressive Driver can perform the Force and Ram maneuvers against vehicles one card away instead of on the same card.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Driving d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.lgDgXwukFLguscJz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"uXdlZDUu7jeJRt4U"}
{"name":"Speed Freak","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A hero may attempt a Driving, Piloting, or Boating Test (as appropriate) with a -2 penalty to coax more speed out of a vehicle. Success increases the vehicle’s Top Speed by 10% (rounded down to a minimum of +1”) and Acceleration by +1” for the round. If used during a chase, the hero may attempt to gain 3 additional Range Increments with the Push maneuver by accepting a –6 penalty to their Driving, Boating, or","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Ace page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Ace"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-ace.1HpGwGtA5hbD4fiX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4q51ympbhi4","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Ace","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ujbo6TyWsNgitDGu"}
{"name":"Improved Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once an artificer has mastered imbuing powers into arcane devices, she can advance to crafting permanent magic items with the Improved Artificer Edge. Artificers with this Edge have the ability to make minor artifacts– items imbued with powers that can recharge their given Power Points.<p>Minor artifacts are particularly useful for equipping characters without the Artificer Edge, since unlike arcane devices, these items can replenish Power Points without the need for an artificer to tinker with it.","notes":"Artificer's Codex page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.artificers-codex.WuVA4HdITXo2jRml"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tutlz90icqq","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer's Codex","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ull4uxNNO71dbRnT"}
