{"name":"Jai Jiwan Security","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the JJS have the ability to acquire most equipment they want or need for monster hunting. They gain +2 to Subterfuge and Thievery.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the JJS"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.vVX1PfX0CIwFRdC6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"uypI8hkOuNwgdXWk"}
{"name":"All The Senors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot uses caution and craft positioning to produce the best sensor results. Add Handling to Notice Trait rolls with craft scanners.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Electronics d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.cbtCA1cqPEpkiuXo"}},"_id":"uzSmTXt3fLkOAOng"}
{"name":"Defender","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"There is no more noble sacrifice than risking one’s life for another. This Edge allows a hero to do just that—take an attack meant for one of her companions. Any time a victim suffers damage within 6”, the hero may take the intended damage herself by making an Agility roll at −2 (no penalty if she was on Hold in combat). If using minis, the GM can move the characters as makes sense for the situation. </p><p>If the hero rolls a critical failure on the Agility test, she and the original target are hit by the attack (if it makes sense in the particular situation, Game Master’s call).</p><p>If successful, resolve the attack against the Defender instead, who then gets one free Soak roll just as if she’d spent a Benny to do so.</p><p><i><b> Example:</b> Princess Aura is hit by an Imperial soldier in the thick of combat. Barin is within range and has the Defender Edge, so he makes an Agility roll at –2. He’s successful so he takes the damage meant for his troublesome beloved and gets an immediate Soak roll for his noble sacrifice.</i>","notes":"Flash Gordon page 41","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.IoaVahMTbgBwucpG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"v84AN4X8mING7mc9"}
{"name":"Behind The Eight-ball","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Luck tends to smile on you when you are hurt, and things seem at their worst against the Things that Man Was Not Meant to Know. Gain +2 to recover from being Shaken. Also, you can use Spirit instead of Vigor for rolls related to damage (e.g., the Vigor roll made upon becoming Incapacitated) you suffer as a direct result of an investigation you are pursuing.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Investigator, Luck, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.JEXX9YnRAdUAuHum"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vEEJFqTbVsbi46PR"}
{"name":"Shove","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Opponents are ragdolls in your hands as you move them about the battlefield. You gain one free reroll when using the Push option. If you gain a raise over your opponent, they become Distracted or Vulnerable to the end of their next turn in addition to any forced movement. Finally, you may choose to move with your opponent if you wish when repositioning them. Note: The Push option can also be used to reposition a target through tosses, checks, or drags. Also Push says you can move your opponent up to 1” (or 2” with a raise), so you may choose 0” to just knock them Prone as a trip maneuver.","notes":"Martial Options page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.lfXBJQeDz6XOv2oV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vHn87vgmRYaNYry6"}
{"name":"Need For Speed","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot knows how to push their craft beyond design specs; they may add 1/2 Speed on a Success or double speed on a Raise for the next round.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sjpwsdmxupa","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Pilot Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.bJqdsU5FOjwSMXkl"}},"_id":"vIqzTFXwZVk7GPfP"}
{"name":"Demolisher","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent receives +2 on demolitions rolls when placing charges, and damage with explosives may Ace.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8, Demolitions d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.FBEncVUNpNCleVKn"}},"_id":"vP51g9dbIZeQ8D9U"}
{"name":"Necromancer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p><p> The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the zombie power at Novice level (rather than its normal Veteran Rank requirement).</p><p> Second, when casting zombie, the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p><p> A Necromancer may never have more than twice his Spirit die in permanent undead servants.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 33","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.QH5KkxjBn9qsuPM2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vcNFa17FUor3r4oZ"}
{"name":"Blind Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When his vision is impaired, the fighter’s other senses step up. He hears or smells presences around him, he senses or anticipates where they stand, when they are about to act, and in which direction they move.</p><p>The blind fighter ignores all Illumination and blindness penalties to attack, Test, Support, or activate powers on targets up to 3” from him","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.dG2dyTQPQUWvUj5W"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vcQiPRWIIeOYaHtQ"}
{"name":"Disguise Artist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This chameleon can walk through a crowd while shadowing someone undetected by grabbing a hat, newspaper, or a prop. He owns a trunk full of various costumes, wigs, and a professional makeup kit. Given enough time to prepare, or with access to the right props, he can pass as anyone he wants.</p><p> A Disguise Artist gets a free reroll with Performance whenever using a disguise.","notes":"Wiseguys page 55","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d8+, Persuasion d6+, Stealth d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.8sbS9HV95TQQiZTV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vgTbrOWZKXwV2yA8"}
{"name":"Back From The Dead","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character was dead, sort of. Maybe she got in over her head with the Triads or discovered information that was better left secret, and a megacorp took out a hit on her. Heck, maybe she was just in the wrong place at the wrong time. The streets are fickle that way. Cross the wrong group of people, turn down the wrong alley and it can end your life. Whatever the case, everyone thinks you are dead, and you like it that way. The rat bastards who took you out won’t ever see you coming.</p><p>Whenever your character confronts someone involved in your death, the NPC starts the encounter either Shaken if combat occurs, or she has a −2 to Social Conflicts if not in combat. This Edge doesn’t last forever, though. After your character has confronted everyone involved in your untimely demise, the Edge no longer provides its benefit. At that point in your story, you can choose a new Edge without having to spend an Advance. You must still meet the requirements to choose the Edge, though.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.q9fUzqk7nUumyF3E"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vhpR2MlM45fuEfJM"}
{"name":"Forger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"It takes a particular skill to make a perfect copy of an object. Whether it is to forge a perfect copy of a painting, a key, or identification papers, the scoundrel gets a free Thievery reroll to forge the desired item.","notes":"Wiseguys page 56","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Thievery d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.I8HuqOZm4X2xwLk0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vjecX7dxEgTJAP9Q"}
{"name":"Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Choose a group of creatures like undead, demons, dragons, beasts, or a subgroup of humanoids, like cultists or criminals. The hero is trained to track, hunt, capture, and kill such targets.</p><p>He gains +2 to knowledge and Networking rolls to get information about creatures from that group.</p><p>He also get +2 to resist Intimidation, Fear, and Special Abilities from such creatures.</p><p>This Edge can be taken multiple times, each time for a different group of creatures","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Common Knowledge d6+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.XFSUCWMLgZlomExJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vlJjM6KfIdRkmEug"}
{"name":"Ranged Pin","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent may use certain missile weapons (knives, arrows, spears, etc.) to pin opponents to nearby surfaces. The opponent must be within 1”of a wall, tree, or similar surface. Make a Shooting or Throwing roll at –2. If successful, the target takes normal damage and is pinned, requiring a successful Strength roll to break free. With a raise, the opponent must make his Strength roll at –2 or remain pinned.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 24","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Shooting or Throwing d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.s8moFzbVMWFMAC4Z"}},"_id":"vmIj1JxyDXUfWV8W"}
{"name":"Tannis Touch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You hero is “attuned” to tannis. He can automatically identify where on the planet it came from, and if it’s a tool or weapon, gets a sense of any former owners, great deeds performed with the object, and so on.</p><p>The anouk can also merge tannis with other samples and shape it into simple tools or any of the anouk weapons listed in the Gear chapter. The stone slowly takes on the consistency of clay as he does so, then slowly hardens back to its natural hardness. This process takes an hour per pound of stone worked.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Anouk or Banshee Born or Guardian, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.ZtPoZDNeSuR8rvBo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1cc60fpot1k","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vrUiyRSLFHyn7yZa"}
