{"name":"Oversized Weapon Master","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character may use two-handed melee weapons with one hand. He must still meet the minimum Strength requirement to use the weapon.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.4tofYvTlFaaw4bMK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wG4VV6qlsaBjjThu"}
{"name":"Arcane Mechanik","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has learned the intricate and painstaking skill of inscribing magical formula into runeplates, allowing him to create new runeplates from existing formula or invent his own. Creating a runeplate works just like the Crafting skill, and requires a number of successes equal to three times the Rank of the power to be inscribed. Runeplates require raw materials worth 100gc per Rank of the power built into them. Arcane Mechaniks also gain a +2 bonus on Repair rolls to fix mechanika.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d8+, Crafting d6+, Knowledge (Arcana) d6+, Knowledge (mechanika) d6+, Arcane Background (any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.2X9SVZu3omlU0WKc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wREkv93ivCguuAjo"}
{"name":"Attune Arcane Weapon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some artificers become adept at eking every advantage out of an arcane device’s enchanted qualities. When wielding a weapon that is an arcane device, artificers with this Edge gain a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls. They must spend 24 hours with a newly acquired magic weapon before they can gain this benefit when wielding it.","notes":"Eberron Conversion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.eberron.QjnGTWQaPGysGfSG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_hgfoxjk4syj","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Eberron","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wWM6Xj3DU5WdTtdg"}
{"name":"World Traveler","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character is familiar with other nations and cultures, and  ignores the Outsider penalty when dealing with locals (see Setting Rules, Outsiders, in the Rippers Resurrected Player’s Guide).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.aKovTMbPzfmUU53V"}},"_id":"wX0t4Dt2tqVJyhlC"}
