{"name":"Hardened","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This monster slayer has seen things that would make most men lose their minds. Somehow he’s hardened himself to it and can live with it. If the hero makes his Smarts roll, he gains one extra point of Sanity during “down time” (see page 23). This is usually between adventures, and is entirely at the Game Master’s discretion (a character who spends his time researching monsters shouldn’t get the bonus, for example) and is in addition to any he might gain for other reasons.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_326x64cfav4","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.HhikeIyGWXvZNoKA"}},"_id":"wrDHnnJWh3vn239A"}
{"name":"Innate Power","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent was born with a genetic mutation that manifests as a power through force of will (Spirit). He chooses one power regardless of Rank and may also take Power Mod Edges, as normal. The penalty to use this power is the difference in the agent’s Rank and the power’s Rank. When he rolls a modified result of 1 or less on the Spirit die, regardless of Wild Die, he suffers a level of Fatigue. A critical failure causes a wound.<p><b>Example:</b> Sebastian, a Novice agent, knows bolt II, a Seasoned power. His attempts to use it are at –1 until he achieves Seasoned Rank.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 21","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.DklptblqecLqiCtO"}},"_id":"x2BHCVp5O5HMSfUm"}
{"name":"Know Your Enemy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Repeat encounters with a certain type of monster has honed this fighter’s defenses.<p>Pick a monster type such as vampires, lycanthropes, animals, demons, etc. (anything but humans). Increase the character’s Parry by +2 when attacked by those abominations. (The increased Parry does not apply to other types of foes, even if they attack simultaneously.)</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Fighting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.RtK5LD6vfm9Xuobz"}},"_id":"xi0mg9xNJUrFkuu0"}
{"name":"Disarm Tactics","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You love to deny your enemies weapons in a fight. The character ignores 2 points of Called Shot or Scale penalties when attempting to Disarm. Additionally, if your opponent drops their weapon, your hero (if they have a free hand) may opt to have their weapon in their hand now. Otherwise, the item is displaced 1” from their foe in a direction of the hero’s choice.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.6c39j0CQUjAcad05"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"xlmqq8jKMmsZOTYz"}
{"name":"Wheelman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This agent is a demon behind the wheel, able to fire any one-handed weapon while driving without suffering a multi-action penalty. When using the Chase rules, he receives an additional Action card with a success or better on his Driving roll when he’s the driver.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 25","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Ace"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.lcTGnqhjzMoYbDJx"}},"_id":"xqdGH22IwuOZQ24p"}
{"name":"Paragon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The greatest Rippers are righteous individuals and fierce protectors of the innocent. They lead by their austere example and are willing to aid any who fight the dark powers of the Cabal.<p>When this character gives a Benny to another who uses it to make a Trait roll (including Soak rolls), the recipient adds +2 to the final total. This stacks with Elan if the beneficiary has the Edge.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Common Bond"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.flptzw40C1bF5gG8"}},"_id":"y3qAhE0HuIXTygbo"}
{"name":"Mandalorian","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Mandalorians are trained from a Young age to be ready for combat at any time. They get a +1 on all Fighting and Shooting Rolls. They also receive a +1 to any Piloting Roll made to use a Jetpack.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Soldier"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.0nGFgm0SxqMYhkXk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qmidvk34a6q","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"yE8Q6uJoEtHRDeuX"}
{"name":"Master of Disguise","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character is able to easily throw together a disguise at a moment’s notice and receives a +4 to Persuasion rolls to pass himself off as another.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"L, Persuasion d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.cavkDL2BW5P791Co"}},"_id":"yGYyIEKUdL61WGgo"}
{"name":"Fearless","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’re not actually fearless, but you’re as close as it gets. If you fail a Fear roll, the GM rolls a d12 for the Fright Table result instead of a d20.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Brave, Guts, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.WxKUIzlY7eq7d4RU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_j3gsmia1ap","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"yHfGEZ3Kkhj6gP9V"}
{"name":"Mystic Pact","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Though the Rosicrucians are dispersed at this time in the world of Rippers, a few individuals remain and continue to espouse the cause.<p>When the order was active, new recruits were often taught mystical symbols and practices that enhanced their magical abilities.<p></p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Rosicrucians)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.lBz1x2B7djCS4gsW"}},"_id":"yQoxZ3z8Tulu65nn"}
{"name":"Psychic Detective","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your psychic abilities are uncommonly in tune with your instincts, providing unnatural situational aware- ness. This grants a +2 on any Psionics roll for the detect arcana or divination powers. <i>Also, any time a Notice or Investigation roll to spot a clue fails, as a free action the Gamemaster secretly makes a Psionics roll for the same purpose on the player’s behalf. This represents your psychic instinct’s ability to spot what your training missed.</i>","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Psionics), Investigator, Notice d8+, Psionics d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.HGKWSMwKAlbodhxd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"yWogs4ZuuajZOSjR"}
{"name":"Reputation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character managed to impress the masses with his ability to get things done. His Street Cred die type is increased by 1 to a max of d12+2. This Edge may be taken up to three times. The Edge may only be taken a second time when the character is Veteran or a third when he reaches Legendary.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.tE6cxbvGxAFtW4lB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zys386iohka","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ybtra10sJYTBlRxj"}
{"name":"Blessed","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The agent has been righteously blessed by the faith of his convictions. He receives a +2 bonus to damage when attacking supernatural evil, as well as a +2 to his Toughness when defending against it.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d9, AB, Channeling d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.ffHWFarJn8dUEUK3"}},"_id":"ydxDdUcsR6XpsA5c"}
