{"name":"Flash and Panache","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You know how to get the most bang for your buck. You gain an additional +2 bonus to reaction modifiers and related skill rolls (such as Persuasion) when throwing money around.","notes":"Agents of Oblivion page 31","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Charismatic"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tjb1fblf39r","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Agents of Oblivion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.agents-of-oblivion-edges.PqCa07xxvexAsomi"}},"_id":"zFN5hqMv6WPftxqU"}
{"name":"Hit The Streets","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You can smooth talk yourself into new social circles with a bit of work. Make a Persuasion roll, as per the Connections Edge, with members of a group you do not have the Connections Edge applied to. The Persuasion roll is made at –2 if this group is closely related to contacts you do have a Connection Edge for; this modifier worsens the thinner the relationship is (Gamemasters use your discretion.) Doing so first requires a successful Investigation or Streetwise roll to find the right sort of contact to make, as the Gamemaster deems suitable. The same penalty is applied to this roll. Treat as though having the applicable Connections Edge if both rolls succeed.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Connections, Investigator, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.6L2xCubpL0V571Ls"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zUPjWow8MNzDXNJU"}
{"name":"Flurry Of Blows","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When wielding Double Weapons (staves, spears, polearms, see page 5) with both hands, the fighter lands consecutive rapid strikes with any end of the weapon.</p><p>He ignores 1 point of Multi-Action penalties for Fighting rolls made with those weapons","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.NSjsS4wjC4ksJKOP"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bseilocyflu","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zXNisbv7wAZUOCea"}
{"name":"Fame/infamy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"“Hold everything, men! It’s Flash Gordon!” Logun grips Flash’s hand—”We were your Freemen—thought you were dead—lost hope—turned outlaw to keep alive—will you lead us again?”</p><p>This individual is well-known for her words and deeds, whether a hero or villain! Her very presence affects those she meets face to face. Unless the others are already hostile, their reaction level is one step higher, out of respect for Fame or fear for Infamy.","notes":"Flash Gordon page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.flash-gordon.Yk5IGwJaQsLxT99q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zc5n98io8as","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/Flash Gordon","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zcultgSyYXUaShk6"}
{"name":"Underdog","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"No one should count you out, no matter how stacked against you the odds may seem. Gain a +2 modifier to any opposed roll against an opponent with 2 or more die steps higher than you for that particular chech. However, this is only if that opponent has inflicted a shaken or wound outcome upon you during the same encounter.","notes":"Expanded Profession - The Investigator (General) page 2","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Luck, Spirit d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.expanded-profession-investigator.RSUHXsG2n6YBzf4j"},"cf":{"id":"temp_efc2gvezw4v","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Expanded Profession - Investigator","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zfSRjwWjLPTDbziE"}
{"name":"Alternate Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your Ripper has another identity she can assume. The identity must be of lower Status than her own, and when assumed, incurs the relevant modifiers and station as usual.<p>People who know the individual in one identity and encounter the other make a Notice roll at –4, opposed by Stealth, to determine the truth. People who are more intimately familiar may suffer a reduced penalty, or none at all, at the Game Master’s discretion.<p>Scandals that affect the alter ego don’t affect the real individual. Also, since certain eccentricities are expected of such do-gooders, covering up Scandals (see page 34) costs one less Favor than usual.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Performance d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j4zzdol93ta","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.SbI5rmok5lHU2YAe"}},"_id":"zg5jVl34BVLwDmzw"}
{"name":"Document Forger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You are a skilled forger, capable of producing false documents such as government papers, military orders, legal decrees, and so on.<p>The first time someone examines a particular forgery, make a Repair roll to see how well you did: viewers must equal or exceed your roll with a Notice roll in order to recognize the document as a fake. Should your forgery copy a specific individual’s handwriting or seal, the viewer receives a +2 bonus if they are familiar with the handwriting or seal in question. Otherwise they suffer a –2 penalty if they are unfamiliar with the general type of document, and a further –2 penalty if they only glance at it.","notes":"Guild of Shadows page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8, Repair, d6, Stealth d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.guild-of-shadows.IsF0NQTHMvWJhntH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8m8awrrszmi","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Guild of Shadows","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zgyhU3iebtd9zDsK"}
{"name":"Watchful Warrior","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You’re good at keeping an eye on your opponents, and have learned to fight several at once. Opponents in melee combat never benefit against any gang-up bonus against your hero.","notes":"Iron Kingdoms Conversion","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Fighting d6+, Notice d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.iron-kingdoms.xfcl2jiPsSSKXlwj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_og0np7k2v8","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Iron Kingdoms","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zhufEnLtVkGFBngG"}
{"name":"Balak Brigade","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the BB gain TOUGHNESS (3) and +1 to damage rolls.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the BB, Seasoned."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.pvQ1T5JSalpP2xoi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mt92hgg82to","path":"Horror Edges#/CF_SEP/Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zmOlcQ3uvJrIDCcZ"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Shadowcraft)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Arcane Skill: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Umbra (Spirit) </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Starting Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Gloom touched </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">+1 additional power </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Power Points: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">15 </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Available Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Blind, bolt, damage field, darkness, darksight, deflection, fear, gloom touched, invisibility, intangibility, shadow jump, swirling shadow, umbral hand</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">. </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Gifted: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Shadowcrafters may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Gifted). </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Backlash:</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Standard as per </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">. </span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Shadowcloak: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Characters with this Arcane Background gain a bonus +1 to Stealth rolls whenever they are in </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">areas of Dim or darker lighting.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Trappings: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">All of the powers used in Shadowcraft </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">involve the manipulation of shadows and darkness. In general, these powers can only be used in areas of Dim illumination or darker.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Limited Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">The power of Shadows is particular and personal. All of the powers have a Limitation of Single Target (for offensive powers) or Self (for defensive powers). These powers cannot use Modifiers to affect additional targets or be shared among allies. The only exception is the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">darkness </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">power.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> Shadowcraft</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rPj8dHI388yTZCBU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2ppcwdakcbx","path":"Fantasy Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zs1aGIvbLmjjwKKA"}
{"name":"A Friend Of Mine","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character makes friends of all kinds and takes great care of cultivating assets. A vast and robust network is a commodity in the Underworld.</p><p> Once per session, the wise guy may call upon a Favor without spending a Benny. The player character must give the Don at least basic information on the acquaintance who owes him the Favor. It could be a forger, a politician, an arms dealer, or a witness, etc. (see Favors in Chapter Two for more information).</p><p> Once the Favor is done, the acquaintance automatically becomes a permanent new Contact—again, no Benny need be spent.","notes":"Wiseguys page 56","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Streetwise, Persuasion d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wiseguys.KSMh8kuqw6uza4WC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_o9gz86yz6om","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Wiseguys","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zssZiFXX92vbM2SS"}
{"name":"Floor Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is at home on the ground as they are standing. The fighter ignores the penalty to both their Parry and Fighting rolls while Prone. Additionally, it does not cost any movement to the character to stand.","notes":"Martial Options page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.martial-options-edges.5r4HILmNf95YOcwO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mbkkcfizj8g","path":"Core Edges#/CF_SEP/Martial Options","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zuaItpLyUBwvEa7G"}
{"name":"Improved Gravitic Acclimation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero with this Edge hasn’t just acclimated to zero-G, she’s virtually an acrobat. She can move swiftly in such conditions, and vault between surfaces to great effect. In zero-G she adds +2 to Agility rolls made to perform acrobatic maneuvers (including Tricks) and +1 to Parry.","notes":"The Last Parsec - Eris Beta-V","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.the-last-parsec.MvW3slrqkgJsdiq8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mq9ry8vd5ci","path":"Science Fiction Edges#/CF_SEP/The Last Parsec","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zvd9VwIsO9Q0NzAq"}
